text_review: the fact that this product spawned my inaugural amazon product review gives you an indication of it is impression on me overwhelmed by how awesome this lens is for the price i bought the rebel t2i at christmas for pics of our forthcoming baby but i found that the kit 18-55 lens very underwhelming for portrait photography understandably now it is hard to believe that the images produced by this lens came from the same camera other than the delightfully narrow depth of field the performance in low light is amazing with the large aperture this lens has not left the body since purchase and i even find myself using it for landscape shots too if you are on the fence about this just get it the lack of is has not been an issue at all for me i guess the larger aperture means it can shoot pics at faster shutter speeds to compensate also the older af mechanism does not even seem much louder than the latest usm system on more expensive lenses at the moment i simply find myself running this lens in av mode with the aperture ramped right up and the camera choosing an appropriate shutter speed amazing

text_review: i am not one for traditional alarm clocks but it just was not working relying on my cell phone all the time anymore so when i got a new iphone i decided to get an alarm clock that would charge my iphone play music and more importantly wake me up this clock is great the ihome app that you use is very customizable and simple to figure out i can set a million okay maybe not that many different alarms for different days and each of them can wake me up in a different way it is easy to choose between the standard buzzer sound or one of the stock sounds the radio an ipod playlist or just a specific song on your ipod iphone it is wonderful my only issue with it is the fact that i cannot change the volume of an alarm while it is going off i can hit snooze a ton i can have my favorite songs wake me by gradually getting louder before playing at the level set but once on pushing the volume buttons on the alarm or my iphone make the device get quiet while i am pushing the buttons but then it goes right back to where it was set it is fine but just takes time to get used to so make sure you do not set your alarms to max volume if you have anyone else you are trying not to wake up this has been a wonderful product for me and i am very happy with the purchase

text_review: all the publicity controversy identity changing and bizarre personalities aside prince is one of the greatest musicians alive today yet when this phrase is uttered people immediately think that i must admire his ambiguous image and his funny dress-code instead of respecting his musical genius even though i have read as many articles and biographies about him i could find still i do not know him so i am not the one to discuss the real reason behind all the fuss he has been putting out since one thousand , nine hundred and ninety-two not that it matters much since to me the name prince stands for one thing music prince writes music he performs and on this department i absolutely love him simply put no one else i have listened to could flirt across so many genres of music and nail them being incredibly diverse yet so uniquely sounding more than often he surprised me with a song which i initially hated and ended up listening to the most while prince is celebrating his emancipation from major record label it has been increasingly difficult for the casual fans by all mean it does not imply we are any less enthusiastic about his music than the so called diehard fans since we either need to join the music club or having to constantly go on internet and track him down about his latest music venture and more than often realizing that he has changed his mind again call me old-fashioned but i still prefer to go to a music store pay for a well-packaged cd open it and put the cd on while i read the insert as easy downloading music on the computer is i much rather collect a genuine article from an artist on the other hand though i strongly disagree with record label alas film studio interfering with the artistic freedom i do believe the one thing they serve as a certain level of quality control while not saying prince's music released under warner bros are necessarily better they do feel more polished and easier to the ears and those are thesongs that game him the status he has today i do not agree that prince is a washed-out has been as many would claim cynically because i believe this is what prince is aiming for to evolve and mature out of the pop-culture domain what i do agree is if prince continue to change his music releasing scheme strategy he will soon lose more of the even most devoted fans.one reviewer said anyone with half a brain can tell one nite alone ... live is a pretentious album consists of studio overdubs i should really start searching around the house for that half a brain however i do think it would be much better if this box set is titled one nite alone tour collection instead of the misleading word live giving people impression that this is a single live performance other than that the songs that played here are stunning mostly jazzy-funk but there are some true gems on disc two where prince hugs the piano himself playing some of his most beloved hits like adore nothing compares two u and do me baby one of the biggest let down is that according to the accompanying booklet there are plenty more rare and great live performances which are sadly missing here live version of power fantastic is available somewhere but songs like bambi and paisley park where we would have gotten a chance to hear the man himself jamming up the guitar are extremely difficult to find with a box this size three more cds would not be redundant.even though most of the materials here are recycled pasted together from many different sessions of the tour and with the issue of overdubs in question i have to say this is one of the most satisfying listening from prince since a long while ago if you are a jazz funk music fan you will enjoy this if you think the man has lost the touch please stop dwelling on the age of sigh o'the times you might just learn to love prince again

text_review: the nice feature about this silicone case is the black bands at the top and bottom of the screen i tried a couple other case designs because i was having a hard time locating this one some of the other case designs have an opening the size of the entire front glass surface even though not all of that is viewable screen this is too large an area to have open and the sides of their cases fit sloppy and loose the iskin touch fits much tighter because of the black bands of silicone making the front window cutout smaller and the case fit better i am six two and i had my 32gb in my lap and stood up fast ... which was like launching not just dropping my ipod out and down at concrete from three feet in the air time stood still it landed edge-on and then bounced ... doh thankfully i had my pod in this case the ipod landed on it is edge but more towards the front side and near a corner the force of the ipod edge slamming on concrete from that height cut the silicone like a blunt knife it pinched the silicone case enough that it put a small cut crack in the silicone that does not go all the way through the ipod bounced and the case received a pinch cut so clearly this case absorbed much of the energy of that impact the ipod works fine and you can barely see where it landed when i pull it out of the silicone case disclaimer i also have my ipod wrapped front and back in the zagg invisible shield i can see just the slightest concrete kiss in the invisible shield and the very edge of the beveled glass best protection for you ipod touch is to wrap it front and back in the invisible shield and then stick it in the iskin touch i also have the evo three on my 80gb video iskin cases rule i never use the clips though just the silicone case

text_review: notice do not buy this title w o going through the first one it will make this game way more enjoyable and you will understand the beginning you can consider this title as a 14th century gta tons of stuff to do outside of the main story tons of places to explore same engine used in the cut-scenes is used in the game tons of hidden things insane ways to kill enemies and screw around with the pedestrians they also react very well to your actions the peds improvement over the first title are massive though the xbox version actually runs and looks a hair better than the ps3 version it is still very enjoyable and a full fledged ride of fun and beauty against a gorges score which i think is available on cd i will definitely pick it up very memorable melodies epically that villa one it is technically more difficult to make a transfer of a game onto the ps3 platform for some reason this title on the ps3 has a very light blur glow filter throughout the game it gives it a nice wary warm feeling but it seems to be an attempt to hide other visual issues in the game again the xbox transfer does not have this effect i think still like i said it is really fun pop-in galore the major downfall of this game it is not occasionally it is all the time seems to be more so with vegetation it is very bothersome sometimes like when you are flying through the country side on horseback you see chunks of grass weeds bushes pop-in right in front of you then these pop-ins have a second more detailed layer that overlaps these pop-ins and it is just annoying sometimes this was not common on the previous title this is why i gave a rating of four stars many of the ps3 frame-rate issues from the previous title are fixed in this sequel which is evidence the developers are listening i believe though some horizontal screen splitting is still there when you rotate your camera around ezio on a tall building not too annoying though i was hoping this was fixed because it was in the previous title a-lot everything else is hella fun and amazing great story directly related to the previous game italian renaissance for the first time in games is absolutely beautiful and you feel the atmosphere seriously just simply walking around is entertaining partial spolier :: double-blading an enemy in the eyes makes you quiver and also when you smash in a guys balls while he is on the ground made my jaw drop lol end :: anyways buy it now i will pre-order the final assassins creed title when it comes hope they really take their time on it

text_review: i normally wear a size eleven in vans and adidas i ordered the size eleven in the james lace up and they were way too big sent them back for a 10.5 they arrived and were also too big i held out for a while on getting the ten fearing that they would be too small i bit the bullet a few weeks ago and they were snug but i thought i would give them a try and decided to wear them out of the house no turning back after a couple hours in them my feet would go numb so i took them to a shoe repair shop to have them stretched after three days on the stretcher with leather stretching solution they felt a lot better the night i picked them up however they shrank back and are still too small and are too uncomfortable to wear all day also they arrive with a very cheesy grey finish sprayed on them removing it was pretty easy just about fifteen minutes with a towel and some elbow grease i still have my pair of brown twelve harness frye usa boots from high school and love them but i was saddened to see that these frye boots were made in mexico the grey spray notwithstanding the overall quality of materials and craftsmanship is satisfactory to be expected for the i just wish they fit like my other frye boots oh well if you decide to order them make certain that they fit very well before deciding to keep them as attempting to stretch them has proven to be futile also keep in mind that you will be paying the frye usa premium for frye mexico boots update feb two thousand and fifteen twenty-four months after buying the leather on the inner forefoot of my right boot has failed along the stitched seam while at school the other day where the boot breaks folds with every step btwn my foot and toes i noticed a bit of a different feel ... i looked down and noticed that i could see my sock the leather actually was tearing along the stitching think tear along the perforated line it is obviously way too late to make a warranty claim based on time certainly not miles b c i only wear these two times month idk all things being equal if it were ten years from now and i had the option to buy or not buy these again i would definitely seek better boots elsewhere sorry frye i still have my twelve dingo boots from you guys that i bought in hs but these will not see the light of my kids day unfortunately we had a good run

text_review: good news everyone i have cleared ten rooms of elebits so far and still am not motion sick i know you were all on pins and needles about the verdict and this great news from me the one who gets sea sick in a rocking chair i am the one they always have to stop the amusement park ride for and i get positively ill if i am even in the same room as mario kart played way too often in our living room so reading other reviews about the elebits fun but motion sickness warnings had me fretting but it sounded like a lot of fun so i bought this game used and figured give it a try and yippee here is the way to not get sick turns out the trick is to change the camera options for all you out there self-medicating with bonine to play this hopelessly addictive game there is a scale to set from i think one to ten and i just put the camera speed to one instead of the default 8\ or whatever that has the player spinning like a rogue top now i can run around a room and twirl around looking for these little creatures without getting remotely dizzy the game play is not slowed down at all with the slower speed of the camera this game is so addictive all the other reviewers descriptions are on the money so i do not need to repeat or correct anything they said just fiddle with the camera settings in the option screen and maybe this will help so everyone can enjoy as much

text_review: truly amazing camera i own several dslr cameras with some of the best lenses out there in order to capture all our memories photography is my hobby so i know a thing or two when i see a great shot i needed a small camera to carry with me everywhere so i purchased several but after trying them out they all went back to where they came from until i got my hands on this canon n100 i am very very picky about picture quality so none satisfied this expectation with the exception of this camera i was aware that it is impossible for a small camera to produce professional picture quality but i can safely say this camera bit the odds and took me by surprise it even produces the 3d effect with the blurred background that could only be obtained by dslr cameras with expensive lenses all settings are wonderful on this camera but after using it for almost a year i find myself preferring the auto setting when taking pictures of groups of people because this is the setting that brings everything in the picture into focus and then my most favorite and my mostly used setting is the background defocus this is the one creating the 3d effect with blur the farther the background is from your subject the more blur will be noticed there are two ways to do this once you have selected this setting you can press the shutter or you can touch the screen which is touch sensitive you will not obtain the same result if you touch the screen the spot where the screen has been touched will be the only one truly focused so the rest will be blurred out if you use the shutter button the camera will automatically focus on the face and the rest will be blurred more or less depending how far or close it is from your subject this last one is the best way to create a prof looking picture here are some pictures taken in dark areas without flash ... i used both auto and background defocus settings hope it is been helpful ...

text_review: my jagged path to ubuntu ... i am not a professional developer nor am i that linux savvy before this distribution i have only had some minor linux experience trying to install off floppy disks which the build could not read my modem so i trashed that idea and went back to windows.flash forward a dozen years my heap of a desktop that was almost as old as my daughter took a dump on me since this was my only means of computing at the time i formatted and reinstalled xp off the disk i had for years i came to realize that it did not have any of the drivers for my ethernet card and i could not get online rather than steal someone else's laptop to burn drivers i figured i would give linux one more shot since it has gotten better over the years i ordered this set with my phone since the price was fair.like the low rated review i thought this was a four dvd install but i am not that disappointed that it is not what you really get is a thirty-two bit dvd sixty-four bit dvd a intro to linux dvd and a library dvd obviously i do not need both install disks but i may use the sixty-four bit on my laptop we just got.my ubuntu review i am currently running it on an old dell with five hundred and twelve mb ram connected to a forty-seven vizio internet tv for a monitor yeah i do weird things like this i wanted a pc to net around with and stream content on my tv the install went very smoothly and ubuntu actually found everything on my computer with no issues mint linux could not find my sound card the programs i use for general stuff were already installed or they could be found on the file network and installed easily enough so everything made the transition easier to linux i am still getting used to the feel but overall it is not a bad alternative i looked through some other distros of linux and found some kde builds that are more like windows but they require ram i do not have in the end ubuntu offered the best environment to use given my resources.if you are new to linux and want to jump in this is a good start i had it up and running in no time and can do just about anything i did with windows visually it is not as pretty as the kde builds like fedora and the feel is like windows 3.1 but it is growing on me.if you are wanting to try different distros you can download them and burn the iso to disk yourself and save money anyone with an average idea on computers can do this.download iso fileburn image to diskboot from cd dvd to install many have a try it feature i would suggest playing around on an old pc first so you do not mess up data and keep you are real one handy just in case you need to reburn or look at info.hope this helps.don t be afraid of change look around and familiarize yourself then step right in

text_review: wow this icon ntv forty blk bag seems well constructed water resistant padded very durable and high quality i kept thinking that it should have been selling for 21.99 or more not 1.99 see the six photos i uploaded by clicking on the customer images link just below the main picture of the bag starting from the outside of the bag the dimensions are about seven high six wide and five 3/4 deep there is a padded carrying handle on the top plus a detachable shoulder strap there is a web pocket on each side of the bag and a large belt loop on the rear of the bag possibly a monopod or a small tripod could be carried in this loop there is also a small loop on each of the back two corners in the rear view picture that i uploaded you can see a blue carabiner that i inserted into one of the loops the front flap has a small zipper pocket about four 3/4 wide by three 1/4 high i inserted a usb cable into the pocket for the picture the front flap is held down by an adjustable travato side release buckle opening the travato buckle you will see a zippered front pocket that is about four 3/4 high five 1/4 wide and one 1/2 deep the picture i uploaded shows my charging cable in this pocket plus a couple other items within this pocket are two small compartments for carrying items such as memory cards a filter etc unzip the main compartment and you will a divider held in place by velcro that can be moved or removed the main compartment is about six 1/2 high five wide and three 1/2 in depth i put my in there and had a little room to spare note that a couple of the stock photos have a light green hue but it is just the lighting the bag is black and gray overall i am quite impressed with the bag and recommend it with a five star rating

text_review: this is a great camcorder i had a sony hi eight camcorder which stopped working and the nice thing about these digital eight s from sony is that there is backward compatibility on the old formats.lot s of excellent features but you pay for it in weight and battery use the four screen is excellent and if you have kids its nice to show them with sound what you just captured the color viewfinder also works great if you are used to using that as i am from my old hi eight camcorder it also saves on battery usage if you use that instead of the four screen.from a battery standpoint you really need the 8hour or more batteries that are sold seperately or you will be recharging all the time the 8hr sony battery lasts about five hours on this camcorder i highly recommend you buy sony batteries as they have a chip on the battery which lets the camcorder read how much power is left that feature is great i wish that amazon had better rates on this camcorder though i bought it at another site on the web for about ... yes new they also had it in stock whereas amazon seems to have problems keeping some of the different camcorders in stock ...

text_review: just got it in today have to admit its exactly what i thought it would be and its cool i had a screen protector for my psp before and it sucked because no matter what you did it always had bubbles in the middle this one warns you about that but i put it on three or four different ways and only had maybe one bubble and it got pressed out just fine the only thing i do not really like about the front screen is that the edges will not press down around the buttons and sides it is not a big deal to me though.the back screen is slightly and i mean slightly smalled than the back screen but i think it protects enough to not worry about it that went on easier than any screen protector i have ever had even my phone basically both screen protectors have three layers a bottom layer you peel off so you can stick it the actual protector then a top layer to help it stay flat and so you do not scratch anything when you are pushing out the bubbles this top layer peels off after you are done as for the cases well the vita case is really nice the outer cloth might get warn fast but the case itself is really hard and inside it fits the vita absolutely perfectly it has to straps plus its snug so the vita will not move at all i do not think the net on the top lets anything in it hit the vita either the games case is the only real cheap thing in the package its just a cheap little plastic case but it holds eight games and two memory cards i just wanted it so i know where my games are at instead of keeping little cards all over the place.overall its worth the price i am glad i got it protects my two hundred and fifty dollar vita well

text_review: this is an excellent neil young album which is a relief to be able to say because i did not think much of americana his last one this album like americana features crazy horse but is a completely different piece of work and it is terrific in places i think it comes close to his best which makes it something really special.the overall sound and feel is vintage neil young there are the hauntingly melancholy tunes the thoughtful quirky lyrics and the great chord sequences which made albums like harvest and after the goldrush so great combined with the controlled distortion-driven power of the brilliant rust never sleeps am i showing my age here this album is also a reminder of what a great band crazy horse are the sound is terrific there is some great guitar work and they are tight and gutsy so even born in ontario the only slightly weak song on the album still sounds really good.neil young is often meditating on experience and aging here but he still sounds young and fresh and still has more power and guts than a lot of artists half his age several of the tracks are very long driftin back lasts nearly half an hour and other tracks are over fifteen minutes this of course is typical neil young refusing to bow to convention and doing whatever makes musical sense to him at the time he has always done this and it can be dreadful it sometimes has been in the past but nearly all the time here it is great the huge ramada inn is a masterpiece in my view and more conventional shorter tracks like twisted road may well end up in the list of neil young classics.there is little self-indulgence and a huge amount of real musical substance driftin back could perhaps do with a little trimming but it is still a really good track the last half of walk like a giant will probably get the skip-to-next treatment from me but its first eight minutes or so are quite brilliant.you have to hand it to the man he does not mess about and within six months of releasing the mediocre americana he has come up with a real cracker which i think will stand among his finest albums if you are not already familiar with neil young this may not be the best place to start but if you are i suspect that like me you will love this very very warmly recommended t mess about and within six months of releasing the mediocre americana he has come up with a real cracker which i think will stand among his finest albums if you are not already familiar with neil young this may not be the best place to start but if you are i suspect that like me you will love this very very warmly recommended

text_review: i purchased two of the cactus v5 sets to use as a remote flash trigger and remote shutter trigger and after eight months i can say the v5 s are absolutely fantastic i have triggered many thousands of photographs and strobe firings and the cactus v5 s have worked flawlessly each and every time.one of the greatest features is each unit is both transmitter or a receiver selected by the power slide switch on the side slide it one way it transmits slide it the other way it receives if you only buy a pair you will not see this as an advantage but for those of us that use more than two its a huge feature providing tremendous flexibility for example i have four v5 s and have used them in the following configurations one v5 set to transmit on camera hot shoe triggering between 1-3 v5 equipped strobes set to receive i can set each flash to a different channel and by changing channel on the transmitter select any individual strobe or by changing to a group channel i can fire them all.yesterday i was firing a complicated setup one v5 in my hand to transmit two v5 set to receive and plugged in to the camera remote shutter port three v5 on my camera hotshoe mount is set to transmit and has a bounce flash daisy chained on top and finally four v5 is set to receive at my umbrella reflector when i press the button on one half way two focuses the camera when i push one button in all the way two trips the camera shutter the camera hotshoe tells three to fire the bounce flash and the flash connected to four i hope that made sense with any other brand to do what i did in my second scenario i would have needed to buy a second transmitter but with my cactus v5 s i just flipped a switch i am going to buy two more to increase the number of flash units i can fire wirelessly and i am considering buying more after that just to keep on hand as spares i expect to be using my v5 s for many many years

text_review: prepare to be dazzled by an artist at the height of her powers jessica williams brings to the keyboard a prodigious technique an unerring sense of rhythm inventive phrasing and a knowledge of musical history--in short everything required to master the art of improvisation on all alone she explores a world of different moods from playful to pensive as she interprets tunes like in a sentimental mood as time goes by and do not explain then she cooks on her own compositions the sheikh and the quilt williams also has an uncanny way of evoking her musical mentors in original compositions like bill's beauty for bill evans and toshiko for toshiko akiyoshi she even recalls the beloved john coltrane in they say it is wonderful and too young to go steady songs he also recorded to which she adds new dimensions if you like piano jazz you will love this recording jessica williams proves she is all alone in a class by herself--one of the great artists of the keyboard

text_review: serif page plus is in my opinion an outstanding dtp program at a reasonable price unless you are a professional that needs expensive quark or adobe indesign this is a worthy alternative worth looking into another alternative that surprised me is art explosion publisher pro since both are reasonably priced i bought both and where one does not meet my requirements the other usually does one thing you surely want to do when you use these inexpensive programs and have a need to use them for professional projects that require a service bureau or printer is to make sure that they can use your creations that is very important as for serif page plus you will find that the learning curve is much easier on your nerves than quark or indesign if you know little or nothing about these professional tools you might want to start here to get your feet wet and then when you are ready for the others you will have a head start on what you will need to know to create and complete your project while you are looking at serif page plus be sure to look at their other programs ... especially serif photoplus and serif draw i believe you will be pleased with this software

text_review: the clash put out a lot of great music in the few years they were together in five short years that the core band was together they released three regular length records a double album and a triple album all of these records are essential listening i am leaving off cut the crap for obvious reasons they were great musicians with a lot of different influences and they were not afraid to show it a lot of punk bands owe a great deal to the trailblazing ways of the mighty clash that being said if you want the most concise collection of clash music this is it clash on broadway can be a bit bloated the essential clash breaks it down to what the casual listener needs and what the rabid fan can do with as a deserted island compilation everything you need is here the first album is a classic and should be in everyone's collection but all the highlights are here white riot white man ... london's burning complete control ... all classic tracks that show the fury of punk circa one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-seven and the power of joe strummer's limited voice and of course the wonderful reggae remake of junior murvin's police and thieves the track that showed other punk bands both past and future that punk need not have constraints that was the clash's mo never pigeonhole yourself it must have been difficult to pick tracks from london calling as well considered one of the greatest rock records of all time every track is amazing just as the debut cd this one should be in everyone's collection i believe the band did a great job in it is choices except for the exclusion of spanish bombs this is my only gripe about the cd i think this is an essential track that was left off one should pick up london calling simply for this oversite only six of sandinista's thirty-six tracks are picked for this compilation however the tracks that have been picked by messers jones guitar vocals and simmonon bass display the diversity of this experimental record magnificent seven shows how the clash had their pulse on the musical trends of the day and delve into rap ivan meets g i joe has drummer topper headon on vocals police on my back is a straight ahead rock song with great siren-like guitars stop the world and somebody got murdered are both slower-tempo songs and the street parade is an overlooked pop gem off the record four tracks from the a-side of combat rock their most commercially successful record closes this collection along with one track this is england the best song from the mostly forgotten last record from a splintered mick jones-less clash cut the crap both hit singles combat rock and should i stay or should i go are here this is by no means a complete representation of the clash's music there are a lot of singles and b-sides most are fantastic that are not included but this is one great compilation pick it up and embrace the magic that was the clash

text_review: listening to this album reminds me of how much i miss impetus and transnational speedways those cd's were stolen out of my car not too long ago and i have not gotten around to repurchasing them yet after pitchfork i definitely need to re buy it is really neat to hear tracks from clutch that i have never heard before wicker arcadia etc along with old favs bachanall passive restraints etc and a wink wink from the evolved clutch what would a wookie do etc the raw energy on the reissued tracks really gives a good feel of how intense a live clutch show is raging guitars frantic pounding on the drums and vocals barked out like a madman who just needs to tell you his crazy a story even though clutch has toned down the aggression and vocal effects over the last couple of albums they remain unique and diverse as ever its great to be able to get a different feel from each clutch album that i listen to i can thrash out and bang the steering wheel stomp my feet to the rythm on the old wash board or nod my head to the groove and smile these guys are the sh t if you have not experienced the real deal yet move the mouse up and click buy on as many albums as you can sit back and let the music take you

text_review: my son purchased this camera to replace his film camera which is only six months old and now sits in a cupboard and is never used the camera is very stylish and will fit in the pocket quite easily so there is never an excuse not to have your camera with you after being used to an slr which i was until i purchased the fuji s5000 last year the camera initially feels like a toy but do not be fooled this is a very powerful piece of equipment and you soon get used to its compact size nikon has always been there or thereabouts as the top make by people in the know and this little baby carries on their traditions of quality lenses and useful functions not gimmicks the image quality of 3.2 megapixels is more than adequate and the 3x optical zoom nikkor lens is a delight nikon have now gone down the road of including 14.5 megabytes of internal memory which is a very good idea there are enough pre-set modes to satisfy most situations you will encounter the only gripe i have is that nikon always used to include batteries and sometimes a charger with their coolpix range and for some reason they have stopped this the camera comes with a software disk and and an easy to follow manual if you are trying to decide out of all the cameras available which one is for you you will not go wrong with this one

text_review: while some hardcore h2b fans may prefer the these monsters are real seven which is an absolutely beautiful piece of art to be sure this lp was the real monster that the innocent tinny-sounding single only hinted at while not every song is a classic per se it is an extremely powerful album that is a force to be reckoned with the shimmering buzzsaw-thick guitar production is nothing short of jaw-dropping and corin's vocals are just what the doctor ordered as a kid in high school when this arrived into the world it was definately a refuge from all the typical things one deals with and it bravely offered hope creativity and intelligence in this dream nightmare we call life riot grrl was a very real thing and we should not take that for granted now the message was is ultimately a super positive one and of course the music is as exciting today as it was then strangely h2b would eventually release the sub-par directions single following this seemingly taking a step backwards maybe they were old songs written even before the monsters seven .. before corin formed sleater-kinney and conquered the world over again with the help of her wonderful bandmates of course if you are still reading this but do not know if you should buy this cd buy it ps while i read a long time ago kill rock stars was planning on putting out a h2b cd with both singles and a slew of excellent compilation songs b-sides i do not think it is materialized yet so you would be wise to dig deep to find these compilations as well on krs records k records yo yo etc cuz they are friendly and magnificent have fun

text_review: i just received my new street fighter x tekken arcade fightstick v s in the mail just a couple of seconds ago ever sense i found out this bad boy was coming out i had to have one i have had many fight sticks in the past but none compare to this beast words can not explain how it feels the weight of the stick is perfect the art work is off the chain the buttons are nice and crispy and the feel of the over all stick is unreal i now see why japan and china be winning all those tournaments because of the great quality and feel of this thing if you are a real big street fighter players like me this is the stick that you would need to crush your rivals or friends lol i would advise only for serious players though mastering a fight stick takes time and alot of work the hand positioning on the stick the finger layout on the buttons how you perform your combos its alot of work trust me over all like i said this would be great for expert fighting gamers all around mad catz you guys have done it again i have been buying your products for years and i must say that you guys have really went all out this time great product great response time from the stick to perform killer combos i am very happy with my purchase i bought this fightstick for street fighter x tekken and now that i have this thing i can not wait until this game come out in the next couple of days people if you dont have one you need to get one a.s.a.p.game time

text_review: so many guilty pleasures will always come go in this well-shown music industry yet with all the manuifactured artists today we often forget about guilty and simple pleasures from the past generations that continue to influence music from all around the world that goes true for so many acts from the seventy s especially barry manilow his songs have really brought out the best appeal to all around this great globe as the first u s artist to have a album debut at one on the billboard charts barry has been one of the few crowning acts that just keeps having very well near perfection with greatest hits records a few years ago arista and barry achieved surprising status upon hits with the recognized ultimate manilow from two thousand and two now it has been shown again.the essential barry manilow is a reflected look at the legendary barry manilow's career on two cd's the compilation is the first of arista acts recognized from sony's essential series since the merger of sony bmg the songs here are reflected graciously with so many of manilows biggest hits recognized including his classics i made it through the rain the legendary copacabana the guilty pleasure piano ballad mandy weekend in new england somewhere down the road and many of his other greats the collection has been remastered nicely and is delivered quaintly well yet for some who have bought any earlier barry manilow collection this one might want to be a good addition for some where others may just consider the earlier ultimate manilow collection considering all twenty tracks from that collection are also here.nevertheless barry manilow just keeps coming back with his great pop songs issued all over again i just absolutely suggest this package for anybody who is interested into barry manilow and his great songs he just cannot keep smiling without you.songs b album cover b 1/2+ price b-mastering b overall b

text_review: i am rather ashamed to admit that though i have always respected her obvious musical talent from afar i would somehow managed to escape fiona's charms all these years ... until the other night when i could not resist any longer after being intrigued enough by the samples i would heard here and on her myspace page i purchased the idler wheel ... that same night and proceeded to listen to it three times straight through the first time i was bewildered by what i was hearing as it was difficult for me to connect with in the same way it is difficult for me to connect with the avant-garde jazz of john coltrane or thelonious monk even though i could definitely appreciate the artistry involved in the music's construction the second time it all made a little more sense but i still was not totally feeling it toward the end of my third listen however i realized my cheeks were starting to hurt i would been smiling from ear to ear for about a good thirty minutes straight.this is an album that works so perfectly as a whole work of art it is hard for me to cite specific highlights most of the songs are dependent on the ebbs and flows of what came before to have its maximum effect so i definitely recommend listening to this album straight through a few times or at least in large chunks before deciding this is not your thing like some fans are saying as a fan of more guitar-driven rock it is not really my thing either or so i thought then i just put my headphones on let go of all my preconceived notions of what it should sound like and let fiona bring me into her world a world that to me is almost like some weird parallel-dimension 1940s in which she is the billie holiday of that reality only one who plays a mean piano with odd time-signatures curlicue melodies household object-based percussion and insanely varied vocals and lyrics that make you feel her wide spectrum of emotions even if you do not quite fully understand them.fiona can go from singing about love to anger to sorrow to despair to paranoia to neon zebras within the span of a couple songs and the result is intoxicating if you just give in to it and let her take you there her voice ranges from angelic to maniacal and everything in between sometimes all within the same song leaving me feeling almost exhausted at times but by the time i get to the excellent kaleidoscopic and insane hot knife which closes the album i am usually ready to take another ride the production on the album is very sparse with rarely more than piano and percussion framing fiona's voice but that only helps magnify the range and authenticity of emotion coming out of her and the result is as close to perfection as i am likely to hear this year or any year the idler wheel ... is not always an easy fun ride but i can almost guarantee that if you let it it will be a fulfilling one there is no higher compliment i can give than that it is not impenetrable some works of art are just deeper and take longer to sink in and those are the ones that tend to stick with you longer and affect you more profoundly this album will one day be considered a masterpiece i am sure but i am just thankful to have finally discovered her beautiful work even if i am about a decade and a half late hopefully she does not take another seven years to resurface next time though thankfully i will have a few new-to-me old albums of hers to tide me over in the meantime and i am sure that if her next album is anywhere near as brilliant and inspiring as this one the wait will definitely have been worth it the live dvd included with the deluxe version is very high-quality and well worth spending the extra cash for as fiona is in top form at least as far as i can tell considering i am a fiona apple newbie

text_review: i purchased this game in clearance at target after playing ultimate destruction for the gamecube and loving it might i add i had high expectations that this game would be very similar but with next gen graphics etc but boy was i wrong.this game is not even sort of bad it is absolutely awful first off the thing i loved about ultimate destruction was the diversity of combat and unlockable moves and the ability to combine sweet combos to make massive destruction hence the name on your enemies the combat in this game does not even come close remember those awesome moves like turning a bus into a surf board or running up the face of a skyscraper and pile driving off of it into the ground below forget it you will not find any of that here except for clunky tedious what feels like broken and unfinished combat i could go on forever about how much of an absolute garbage pile this game is but lets move on to the story and missions.now in all fairness ultimate destruction was not perfect but man was it a blast you actually felt like you had the power of the hulk at your finger tips i enjoyed the story a lot as well it felt like it was coming straight from one of the comic books sure a couple of the missions were a bit blah but even the worst missions in ultimate destruction look like flawless pieces of art compared to the garbage in this game.it s difficult for me to even comprehend in my mind and interpret it accurately in words that is how awful the gameplay story is in this game to better make you understand i actually forced myself to try and finish this game and i could not bring myself to do it it feels written scripted by a two year old the missions are so bland go here or go beat up those guys that you want to stick a magnum and blow your head off now to defend my statement many games have those sort of tedious missions which i would not have minded but add tedious missions onto god-awful gameplay mechanics that make you want to drill your eyeballs out and you got yourself a jolly good time.my only question is how how does a game where you get to play as the freaking hulk turn out so bad i have no idea ... all they would have had to do is copy ultimate destruction with hd graphics and i would have been the happiest person alive.heed my warning or ignore it but i pity the fool who pays ninety dollars for this game i cannot even believe this putrid pile of poop is even selling this high as for me i am going to pull out my gamecube and play ultimate destruction again i advise you ro so the same

text_review: cyril scott 1879-1970 had the misfortune of too easy success early in his career and mounting neglect for the rest of his life from as early as one thousand , nine hundred and thirty he was being written off as an imitator of debussy who had nothing more worth saying does this adventurous cd confirm or refute this view though a lifelong lover of his music i have to confess that the muses scott's first mature symphony is like the curate's egg good in parts but unacceptable as a whole it starts well with a sinister and brooding opening movement but the middle movements are underdeveloped and the choral finale is a watered down version of the general dance at the end of ravel's daphnis and chloe the second piano concerto of one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-eight is representative of the far more individual idiom that scott developed when he returned to composing in the late 1940s the harmony has an acrid complexity the phrases are brief and there is none of the effortless note-spinning that led colin matthews to dismiss his earlier music as vapid unfortunately the work never establishes a convincing relationship between the soloist and the orchestra and is full of striking gestures that lead nowhere the recently recorded second string quartet played by archaeus quartet on the dutton label is a far more attractive example of his late style that leaves neptune which is a revised version of disaster at sea a long tone poem depicting the sinking of the titanic that was written in the late 1910s there was a tardy first performance in one thousand , nine hundred and thirty-three when the critics panned the work as mere film music scott responded by removing the more crudely programmatic parts of the score in a revised and renamed version of the work which was published in one thousand , nine hundred and thirty-five but has gone unperformed till now i am happy to hail it as a masterpiece the tragic atmosphere is sustained throughout and the writing is beautifully diaphanous and full of highly original orchestral effects which evoke the surge and the spray and the careering bulk of the doomed ship with uncanny vividness there is nothing finer in scott than the bleak epilogue depicting the bare and icy ocean as night sets in in the wake of the famous film and with the original title restored could not this work achieve a belated popularity certainly this skilfully crafted and richly sonorous recording makes the strongest possible case it and the neapolitan rhapsody available on a marco polo cd seem to me the two strongest works by scott for orchestra alone

text_review: this ontario canada based celtic quintet has all the sounds you  d find from across the sea but there is definitely a canadian-tinge to their music yes the pipes and whistles are irish or scottish but there  s a bass backing that says they are canadian-bred four of the eleven tracks on this forty minute cd are instrumentals three of them originals and the other is a set of three traditional reels the band goes all-canadian with the sole a capella track  the four  minute version of stan rogers   barrett  s privateers  the band  s prime vocalist and songwriter  joel guenther sings his award-winning song  something i cannot see  in a voice and style not unlike that of sting this is my favorite vocal track while  from the instrumentals  i  d have to choose the title track which leads off the cd it  s an original by the band  s bagpiper ross griffiths with a tip to the scottish highlandsthere is one new humorous song william macgillavray that sounds like a traditional pub song but i missed some of the humor as the lyrics were lost in the mix i was told this is the band  s third studio album but this is the first i  ve heard of them based on this release i  m sure i  ll look for more i hope you found this review both informative and helpful.steve ramm  anything phonographic

text_review: i used to play world of warcraft but quit about six months after the cataclysm expansion a friend told me about this game and i was skeptical i really enjoyed knights of the old republic i enrolled in the beta testing weekend after thanksgiving and preordered to get early access it was definitely worth it for world of warcraft players this is the next evolution of the mmorpg it has real storytelling with graphics and actual dialog with npcs they have really done an excellent job of combining story elements and good group activities the classes are well balanced each faction has two force-using classes and two blaster-shooting classes each has an option for dps or tanking healing the best part is that each class gets a companion that follows your character around you can also send them on missions to gather resources so you will not have to spend so much time farming finally there are no cheesy in-jokes to distract you from gameplay i have not reached the end-game yet so i will update this when i get there.for traditional role-players this is a great game on its own plus you can group up when the mood strikes you for extra fun group quests and heroic areas are clearly marked so you do not stumble into elites if you go far off the beaten path then you will find tougher opponents it plays similarly to the knights of the old republic and the mass effect series you will not regret buying this game so far i have not run into too many of the typical mmo nerds that call everybody noob and complain about everything overall the gameplay is really well done bioware has done an exceptional job at making this game visually apealling fun to play and challenging

text_review: been searching for awhile for a nice carry on with airline restrictions so tight i wanted to make sure it would not have to be checked i also wanted it to be durable easy to pack and hold as much as possible lightweight not tip over when i carry my laptop in the front pocket wheel easily even on rough areas and the handle must retract all the way in and be adjustable so many handles stick out some when retracted which causes length issues with the airlines airlines measure total length luggage manufacturers measure only bag size so it makes a difference when purchasing a carry on how much the handle and wheels go beyond the bag this piece was perfect never tips with my laptop in the front pocket i always make sure i pack bottom heavy in the bag wheels very easy even on rough parking lots or sidewalks i got the purple not a purple lover however saw it at a luggage store and color is not purple but beautiful plum eggplant color and with the black trim is really classy measurements are perfect even counting the wheels for domestic flights amazon price was the best and shipping was fast all in all i am very pleased with this piece of luggage and plan to get the larger check in size also

text_review: it has its issues for a game to be good i have one requirement do i get angry when playing it i can honestly say that at no time have i gotten angry while playing to give an example of what annoys me to no end when playing an fps in cod ghosts if i join a game in progress i will spawn into the game directly in front of an enemy player if i join in a game in progress i will be on a team that is already well behind the winning team score with no chance of making a comeback rage quitting hosts constantly one out of every three spawns will put me in front of an enemy cod players in general.in battlefield depending on the game mode i can choose when and where i spawn if someone rage quits who cares the game is server hosted a badass player on your team in battlefield with an insane kill count did it with skill tactics and teamwork not with a killstreak reward.there are bugs there are issues the bugs are annoying because if you played medal of honor warfighter it had these bugs as well i know dice only developed the engine for warfighter but it does not change the fact that these bugs exist in both games the issues are mainly with the battlelog service on the three hundred and sixty and one it seems to be down constantly this prevents your loadouts from being available to at times being unable to join a game.dice is an awesome company and i truly believe that in the near future my problems will become moot.also remember even if infinity ward manages to balance ghosts their community is still the largest collection of dbags in gaming

text_review: is not there any minus star rating if there was this game definitely deserves it made in the same gameplay as indigo prophecy dialogues puzzles and arcade challenges it is the worst adventure game i have ever played indigo prophecy was amazing this one is the total opposite totally boring having to watch adam walk around the island almost in real time is like watching paint dry you even have time to go to the bathroom brew some coffee or even cook ... walkthrough for this game is a must so you will not have to walk around pointlessly guessing your next move if it did not take that long i would not suggest it but get the walkthrough before you reach for your pills some of the scenes are too dark for you to find items you might interact with or need later in the game some of them are really in the surrealist realm there is no way you would guess that you might need something and end up dragging adam back and forth the arcade-style puzzles are nerve-wracking you are better off playing it on a n old pc where you will not worry about breaking the keyboard or smashing the screen it takes forever for the game to load once you lose the arcade challenges and it takes forever to reach the challenge you last lost.the characters got on my nerves most of the time and the dialogues are in bad english and childish.thank god i borrowed this game from a friend and did not have to pay for it a total waste of money.my advice if you must try it ... borrow it

text_review: i was a bit skeptical about buying an aftermarket battery grip for my new canon eos rebel t2i 550d in other parts of the world but since using it i have nothing but good things to say about this part i recently took a short vacation to mt rushmore in the black hills of south dakota and had this grip installed for the entire three day trip i took hundreds of photos and a lot of video note also that i am not an old-school photographer that likes to use the viewfinder but rather prefer to use live view screen mode which eats the batteries much more quickly the batteries that came with the grip lasted for the first two days before running low i had another set and was able to keep on shooting i also like the included aa battery tray which gives you the option of powering the camera with six aa batteries which could be a real life saver in a pinch i would rate the feel fit finish and quality of this part to be on par with the camera itself the plastic and grip are nearly identical to the camera the controls function perfectly and make portrait position photos more comfortable than i have ever experienced i have large hands and the comfort factor is the biggest reason that i purchased this to begin with as the normal landscape position is more comfortable as well anyone who has picked up the t2i 550d knows instantly that it is not a heavy camera and actually is a bit on the lightweight side this grip with two batteries actually improves the balance by adding heft and size which can create a much better user experience the only thing i would caution is to consider buying the package with four batteries to allow for change-outs if you do not already have spares that said i highly recommend this product over the one hundred and seventy oem grip from canon which does not include extra batteries and even if you do not have the spare batteries you can get by on aas if you need to update 11/10 two thousand and ten i have now been using this battery grip for about four months and still have nothing but good things to say the rubberized grip has held up well with no noticeable signs of wear the battery life has not seemed to have diminished with time and use there have been some negative comments by other users but i still stand by my original comments update 4/12 two thousand and eleven this part has continued to hold up well the only thing i have noticed is that the printing on the grip by the buttons has worn somewhat as opposed to the printing on the camera itself which has held up with no noticeable wear clearly the manufacturing process at meike is not up to the same level as it is at canon that said i have enjoyed flawless performance from this part and it has not left my camera since i received it the batteries have held up equally well

text_review: well i like small portable flashes i have gone through a few sunpak one hundred and twenty-one s they are really cheap so i do not mind and contemplated a leica sf or contax tla two hundred flash which both use awkward batteries eventually this fuji flash came out promising to be compact with good build quality and manual controls i found one slightly used on ebay i have a x100 though my primary camera is a mamiya seven medium format film camera.pros awesome build quality seems to match the x-pro one and certainly does fine on my x100 takes aaas ... not quite as convenient as aas but still a lot better than those crazy batteries that other similar flashes take ttl metering on the fuji cameras is quite good though i use it mostly on manual controlling the flash is a breeze for this i would give it five stars really excellent and easy to switch between manual and ttl it works really conveniently as an off-camera flash triggered by your camera's built-in flash i love this feature my old nikon dslr had it and i cannot wait to use it more with the fuji although i suppose with a hotshoe extension cord you could retain ttl like the nikon somehow had comes with a leather case and a little tripod adapter as it should for over two hundred both nicely made it locks into the fujis with a little button release ... very nice feature it seems to still mount on all other cameras though it will not lock into the hotshoe.cons like most of the x100 s controls the exposure dial on the ef-x twenty is very loose and prone to being moved accidentally it is a little bit too big for the x100 from the photos i have seen it looks pretty balanced on the x-pro one and it feels like nothing on my mamiya seven but on the x100 it is a little heavy compared to the camera the auto-startup and shutdown when you turn off the camera the flash turns off too okay cool but if the camera is on and the flash is off and you try to turn the flash on itwill start up for about a quarter of a second and then just go back off after six or seven times of this it will finally stay on if the flash is already on and then you turn on the camera the flash will go off i am not sure if my unit is defective but that is pretty annoying i discovered that if you turn them both on at the same time they work.overall this flash functions pretty well on the fuji cameras once you get it turned on i really wish this flash had an auto setting with a mini exposure chart on the back like the sunpaks do they can be used with any camera really easily i guess if you only shoot digital manual mode is a fine alternative i use it plenty on film too is it the perfect flash for any camera it is just okay for that it is really small and portable much stronger and higher up than the x100 s flash and would make a good addition to any kit i use flash a lot and this one is probably the best option for the x100 and x-pro one unless you need to be bouncing light

text_review: customer service is highly problematic i couldn  t find a customer service phone number there  s no support website with faqs or searchable knowledge bases only a web form for submitting questions before purchasing i submitted a simple question about the length of the ac cord and possibilities for extension cables my auto-reply email promised a reply within twenty-four hours three days later i submitted another one after which i finally received a totally unhelpful reply which ignored my question about cable length and said  i don  t know  about extension cables by that point i had already ordered the camera the ac cord is actually very long which pleased me but everything else that followed was extremely disappointing to connect to the camera the instructions say to use the id and default password at the back of the camera i tried dozens of time and received authentication errors each time i couldn  t log into the camera finally i tried entering  admin  for both username and password voila luckily i didn  t wait for customer service to respond to my question about this  three days later i still haven  t received a reply.the biggest problem with this camera is its very weak internal antenna there  s no possibility of adding an external antenna the camera needs to be very close to a router or extender to work properly i have the camera closer to a router than one of my computers which uses a usb wi-fi adapter the computer connects beautifully to a router upstairs but the movo camera can  t even connect properly to the extender in the next room the router upstairs is utterly hopeless for the camera judging by the signal strength indicators inside the user interface there shouldn  t be a problem connecting i think the camera  s signal strength indicator bars are totally misleading there  s not enough signal strength to do anything with this camera totally useless video appears as frozen images because nothing moves unless the camera is within fifteen feet of a router or extender.even if i could place the camera where i need to i wouldn  t be able to use the motion detection feature this feature doesn  t even work in the user interface clicking on alarm text_review: i preordered this with my om-d em5 kit on amazon the second it was released february seven two thousand and twelve while the om-d is still nowhere to be seen no big deal i guess it is been only seventy-one days of wait after all the mmf three arrived last week and i unpacked it last night.first thing first all 4/3 to m43 adapters are mechanically the same there is no chip no electronics there are only pass-through electrical contacts the long story some mmf history you can skip to the end if you do not feel like reading the whole thing ): the mmf one came first it came at the time when there were almost no m43 lenses available and when a m43 user had to rely on his her 4/3 lens collection it was also the time when olympus was still expecting to be able to solve in a fast way the issue with m43 cameras being slow to focus with 4/3 lenses i am not inventing this af part it is all in the interviews with olympus techs popping up here and there throughout the years they really did not expect it to be that difficult the mmf one was awfully expensive for what it was but at least had this beautiful metal construction which sweetened the pill a bit then came the mmf two this was an adapter first released in a kit with the 4/3 40-150 mm lens it was a great deal as basically one of the items whichever side you look at it ended up being free given that the kit was at a mild one hundred and ninety-nine msrp.the mmf two was even more awfully expensive than the mmf one it weighed half the weight of the mmf one not a bad thing in itself but it had a flimsy plasticky construction to not help things once the mmf two 40-150 mm kit was discontinued that is once the m43 version of the 40-150 mm was released the price of the mmf two alone went to a whopping one hundred and ninety-nine msrp one hundred and fifty street price for what is basically a piece of plastic.to its defense by the time the mmf two was released olympus had already realized that making regular non cdaf optimized lenses focus fast on a m43 camera will not be that easy especially the swd lenses gee by that time they actually had problems with slow af on their main camera lens m43 combos problem which was only solved months down the line with firmware updates.it was by then clear that the 4/3 lenses in use with the m43 cameras will be only the cdaf optimized ones which all weigh close to nothing anyway so it was fine.enter the om-d em5 camera.this one is the hot one in oly's m43 lineup it is the first m43 camera body to be weather sealed to olympus credit they also released the mmf three adapter with it the mmf three is weather sealed and this is where it becomes interesting the weather sealed 4/3 lenses are for the most big and heavy well not all but most of the really interesting ones anyway so one would expect this adapter to have at least the mmf one s metal construction and solid feel.alas it was not to be the mmf three is a flimsy plasticky thing just as flimsy as the mmf two the mmf one construction is nowhere to be found it is basically an mmf two with an o-ring on the male side which is proof that this thing is expected to be used only with the 14-54 mm mk2 the only oly 4/3 lens to be weather sealed and cdaf optimized and which is not very heavy i know i know one should always handle a lens camera combo by its heaviest part meaning you are not supposed to carry your 35-100 mm zuiko with a panasonic gf three on it by the camera body of course not.still a heavy lens can put strain on the adapter when shifting in a bag you can in the heat of the moment shift weight between your arms and have a few seconds when the load goes on the camera body side you can ... stuff happens i would prefer a strong adapter vs a weak one any time i am not saying it will break on the spot i just do not feel secure using this thing with a heavy and expensive lens.the one that still laughs at all this the panasonic dmw-ma one lumix g 4/3 dslr mount adapter this baby is still selling is still a panasonic branded mmf one and still costs one hundred and fourteen the short story all 4/3 to m43 adapters function the same there are no electronics there just electrics the olympus mmf one expensive and the the panasonic dmw-ma one the least expensive of all brand name adapters have solid metal construction the olympus mmf two has flimsy plastic construction the new olympus mmf three is a weather sealed mmf two not a weather sealed mmf one there is a chinese alternative the jjc something which is even less expensive than the the panasonic dmw-ma one and is said to be a copy of the mmf one not of the mmf two the jury is still out as of whether the mmf two is actually flimsy enough to cause concern as with everything olympus it is up to specs and does what it is intended to do it is just that it has that flimsy feel and look update just stumbled on this description on the global olympus website released february eight two thousand and twelve :\ four thirds mount adapter mmf 3this adapter has the same function as the mmf one and mmf two adapters designed for use in mounting a four thirds lens on a micro four thirds camera body the mmf three features the same dust splash-proof construction as the camera when one of the twelve dust splash-proof zuiko digital lenses of the shg super high grade or hg high grade series is mounted on the olympus om-d by means of the mmf three pictures with incomparably high image quality can be manifested even under severe environments.the adapter has a detachable tripod mount so safe operation is possible even when a large-aperture lens is used love the detachable tripod mount part something definitely got lost along the way didn'tit :d enjoy this announcement while it lasts i doubt it will stay there for a long time ...

text_review: wow ... where to begin as a musician music lover and music collector i can say without reservation that intimacy ranks with some of the most sincere genuine and extraordinary music i have ever heard i have just listened to the cd for the third time and i am simply overwhelmed by what kem has produced this is music for musicians music for those who really appreciate the craft yet also for those who simply enjoy music for the sake of being entertained i will not go song by song but three of the cuts express to me the musical genius that is kem one is human touch a sultry intoxicating groove with the kind of subtle musicianship trumpet echoing in the background the occasional right-on-time keyboard riff that has come to be kem's hallmark then there is if it is love a spectacular duet with maurrisa rose whose amazing voice meshes so well with kem's that you have to wonder why it took so long i am reminded of luther's ability to find the perfect female voice to compliment his own and finally we get to golden days which brilliantly pairs kem's vocals with jill scott's profound spoken word all over a scintillating latin jazz 6/8 groove the result as kem says grown folks music if you do not buy another cd this year you need to have this one in your collection unlike many other artists who find success in their first one or two albums kem did not succumb to the tendency towards more commercialism in his music no he did not seek to make music that is radio friendly but guess what radio stations are going to play it because well this is just beautiful real music

text_review: i installed premier two thousand and fifteen every thing seems to have worked fine the program backed up my earlier version files fine and converted fine amazon shows that quicken will update fine from two thousand and ten forward i updated from two thousand and nine and i do not see any problems but will have to look further but on first glance seems ok i decided to upgrade since i have not changed in a number of years product reviews sometimes reflect the experience or lack thereof of the user i am reasonably computer knowledgeable and am pleased with the program so far will update going forward if any problems pop up but starting out quicken premier has worked well i use turbotax every year everyone knows the problem this year with the change in deluxe luckily intuit did follow through with the free upgrade to premier where necessary in my opinion intuit could be a lot more user friendly going forward have spent some time putting in accounts and had some trouble with update five but backing up and reinstalling was effective and the update worked fine i see now that update six has caused problems and quicken took it off their servers until they can fix the update i think the program code could probably be better i would guess it is smart to hold off on patches when they are first released any new code can cause unexpected problems quicken is no different too much reworking and yearly updates to get may be a negative but overall the program is working for me it does not handle every transaction well i had difficulty putting in ee bonds there seems to be no simple way to set it up and have it track interest still i am reasonably satisfied but could always be better i know many are frustrated but it would seem to be difficult for any program to handle so many different transactions 5/11 fifteen update update quicken's update five which was installed with a popup dialogue box caused the program to lose some functionality i deleted the program under windows programs and features and then used quicken's clean ui to further clean the program from the computer i originally used just quicken's clean ui but that did not work by itself so the reinstall worked fine and i did not reinstall update five i will hold off on that now as the program seems to work ok changed to three stars because the update caused problems with the program update i installed the release patch five as requested by a popup the release patch has caused problems with functionality working on it so far no luck updates can cause problems

text_review: i have used pcs forever that is until about eight months ago i bought a macbook running tiger and a new laptop pc w vista at the same time i became familiar with the macbook pretty quickly and actually found myself using it over the pc ninety of the time then i upgraded to the latest os of leopard and have been using it since the end of october i have been gradually going back to the pc more and more as leopard is really more complicated than i expected i am considering going back to tiger but i have sunk so much money and time installing the new os in the macbook i think i will just wait until they fix a few of the problems and go back to the pc for a while if you have to choose between vista and tiger ... go with tiger but if it is a choice between vista and leopard ... go with vista until some of the gripes in leopard are fixed imho if you want to know what those gripes are just do a google search on leopard and grab a cup of coffee ... your in for a long read sure there are those mac people who will defend the os but there are fewer than you would expect even mac loyal sites are posting tons of complaints instead of praise to me being familiar with both pc and mac it is obvious that apple is trying to be more like a pc it is a shame because that is why i liked tiger ... it was not microsoft oh well bill gates wins we all lose

text_review: funnily enough i started listening to this album before i even reached adolescence after expressing to my parents an interest in dion and the belmonts most of the time i would just listen and laugh at some songs silly or over-serious treatment of otherwise serious occasions love potion nine always tickled my funny bone as did who is that lady and especially bang bang other songs were heavier ike and tina's two-faced proud mary and the glory of love which always seems to linger to dwell in my ears in a way similar to fats domino's slow and penetrating croon and somehow walk do not run alone managed to instill in me the ability to see beauty and fun in a song that does not have well-known choruses to carry it through.not all twenty-four of these sweet songs are really legendary in style presentation and content they did not cause shifts in musical paradigms or provoke deep contemplation there is nothing here that you will not be able to hear on your local oldies station if you wait around long enough but to dismiss this stuff because of its relative simplicity would be too hasty a move for lovers of sound.this is a great album when you are in the mood for the kind of sounds produced before rubber soul blew brian wilson's mind and yes a little bit after as well ): lightweight simple often though not entirely upbeat ... i have found that it is good to unwind to and it never fails to provide the same laughs and smiles as when i was a kid all the way from eddie cochran's visit to his local congressman to cher falling off her imaginary horse to the highwaymen's perfect quieting closing.in the words of jan and dean it is not very cherry it is an oldie but a goody ...
