text_review: when you buy a new console you have to think about the following available features past games present games future games reliability and cost of ownership after some research and thinking you will see that in the year two thousand and nine and beyond xbox three hundred and sixty is simply a bad choice compared to the ps3 features ps3 wins this elite bundles gives you two cheap mediocre games the ps3 on the other hand gives you a blu-ray player built-in wi-fi 7.1 surround sound support more advanced hdmi support and more past games xbox three hundred and sixty wins xbox three hundred and sixty has better games from two thousand and five to two thousand and seven this is because xbox three hundred and sixty has a one year head start and the ps3 presented early programming difficulties for developers it should be noted too that games released in two thousand and five to two thousand and seven now look old and dated compared to the likes of metal gear solid four killzone two and uncharted two on the ps3 present games two thousand and eight to two thousand and nine ps3 wins multiplatform games look a tiny tiny bit better on xbox three hundred and sixty but the differences are so insignificant that game critics score ps3 and xbox three hundred and sixty versions the same however ps3 exclusives tend to look better sound better and receive higher critical acclaim uncharted two on the ps3 is now receiving a ninety-seven average rating among twenty-four publications in fact ps3 has the two highest rated hd exclusive games uncharted two and littlebigplanet future games ps3 wins the ps3 is a more powerful console using higher capacity disks blu-ray while xbox three hundred and sixty is less powerful and uses lower capacity disks last-generation dvd in light of current games and console capabilities the ps3 has a brighter future than xbox three hundred and sixty if you want to play games with the best graphics the best sounds the most content due to blu-ray disks the largest multilayer shooters or the most mmos you have no choice but the ps3 furthermore if you want games that make you feel like playing a blockbuster movie metal gear solid four killzone two uncharted two heavy rain then the ps3 is the best.reliabilty ps3 wins we all know that xbox three hundred and sixty is still the most unreliable console in the market jasper or not after three years owners of xbox three hundred and sixty are more likely to have to pay for repairs than owners of other consoles cost of ownership ps3 wins owners of xbox three hundred and sixty are more likely to pay higher costs for accessories wi-fi hard-disk drives upgrades batteries for controllers they also have to pay fifty a year just to play online paying for repairs after three years of ownership must also be considered microsoft seems to do everything possible to nickle and dime their customers cost of ownership is something you must consider if you want to buy this bundle for kids so all in all this bundle does nothing to make xbox three hundred and sixty a better choice than the ps3 slim

text_review: david greilsammer is an artist worthy of attention his ability to touch the keyboard of a modern steinway piano and make us believe we are sitting in a salon in mozart's day so characteristic of the style the embellishments and the cadenzas that even on a modern instrument have all the grace and clarity of the original harpsichord performances here he performs with the conductor-less suedama ensemble a student orchestra based out of the 92nd street y in new york city of which greilsammer is musical director the concerti selected for this very well recorded cd include no five in d major k one hundred and seventy-five no six in b flat major k two hundred and thirty-eight and no eight in c major k two hundred and forty-six we can only hope that this foray into the rarely performed concerti continues on subsequent cds.greilsammer and his ensemble offer vivid frolicking and when called for very soul searching performances greilsammer uses his own cadenzas and for once they sound more like mozart than most other soloist-written cadenzas there are moments in these three works that suggest the seeds of some of mozart's symphonies and operas were already planted hearing these early works written as a teenager offers the listener a deeper appreciation for what was to follow in mozart's prodigious output david greilsammer is rapidly becoming a champion for taking risks in music and we are fortunate for his arrival on the artistic scene grady harp january eleven

text_review: i have used tax cut in the past and have been satisfied but i read about download install issues with tax cut this year and decided to try turbo tax i found turbo tax to be very rigid for example my wife donates to twenty-five thirty different charities each year with tax cut they just required the name of the charity and amount turbo tax requires an address for every charity if i left the address off tt would not allow that donation to be added now i have the cancelled checks for all these charities but i had to look up every address on the net in order to enter these deductions into turbo another example is that my wife has a sar sep for her business that retirement plan allows a catch-up deduction which the standard sep plan does not allow turbo does not provide a sar sep option and would not allow me to enter a catch-up deduction to the sep calculation tax cut does not support a sar sep either but tax cut gives the option to enter the deduction amount for sar sep that you self-calculate so these are two examples where i had to go through extraordinary efforts to work through turbo's rigidity they seem to think that if turbo does not support it you do not need it at least allow me to add or over-ride at my own risk there were others that i will not go into here i also was disappointed with intuit's itsdeductible web site this site is advertised as a place to enter your charitable deductions for non-cash deductions it provides estimates of donated item's value again it would not allow me to over-ride a value if i knew my item had a higher value i had no option to change it so i figured i could export the data to a spreadsheet and make modifications wrong again there were questions on the site asking how the information could be downloaded but no answers intuit wants to lock up your data so you cannot get away.tax cut also does the job with what seems to be less rigidity i will probably go back to tax cut next year

text_review: i absolutely love this tripod mount ... and here is why if you have not done so i would highly recommend googling fstoppers iphone fashion shoot it was basically a shoot done to prove that it is not the camera but the photographer that creates beautiful images that shoot was my inspiration for buying this accessory but in the real world sometimes when doing portrait work pre-shoot prep i do not want to have to take out my camera the thing is heavy shoot download from memory card and then sort through it is much easier to whip out my iphone and snap a couple of shots show them to my assistant or text them to someone i decided i needed a tripod mount.buildthe istabilizer is very well built everything about it feels well made the clamping mechanism is strong and definitely does its job what i like particularly about this mount is that it will fit iphones with cases on something most do not as well as other smartphones this is a plus since not everyone has an iphone obviously resultswhile i use this primarily for stills it works nicely for a few short tutorials i put on youtube having a fluid ball-head tripod makes this thing a blast to use with the iphone and will greatly improve your shots i know that this is quite a big accessory nowadays for street reporters allowing someone to throw a smartphone on a tripod and get hd footage that is good enough for on-the-spot news reports i definitely enjoy using this even if it spend most of its time in my gear bag there are cheaper alternatives but this really is an excellent choice recommended

text_review: do you need a basic but docx xlsx pptx capable version of real microsoft office openoffice not doing a good enough job for what you need are you put off by office two thousand and thirteen which does not offer three product keys for your trouble are you even more put off with microsoft turning office into software as a service with office three hundred and sixty-five well you are going to have to accept some compromises namely the hated ribbon and not having all the office apps but there are z number of people who have late windows xp early windows vista era pcs that are perfect for secondary production running windows seven from a retail upgrade disk-and when you do the clean install upgrade for windows which you will eventually have to do due to windows rot you are going to need office and you may never get up the budget to where you want to invest in office two thousand and ten or later for such a low-end often barely aero-capable pc so this is perfect as long as you temper your expectations.with properly set expectations and a legal copy of office two thousand and seven home and student you can now get down to how it works.it works by running basic word excel powerpoint and onenote tasks it is not going to wow you like a new version of office but a common thread i have read in hundreds of reviews for various versions and editions of office is why do they break what works in the previous version when they release a new version well by buying an older version there are no surprises as regards what office can and cannot do because it is been around for however many years it is been since the date the version in question office two thousand and seven home and student which is seven years as of when i write this was made.what can it actually do well word's fully featured as long as you are using it for home or student use excel is fully featured as regards the base program again the same caveat applies powerpoint will get your presentations done although you will miss some of the customizations of later versions onenote is fully featured and it along with powerpoint have the caveat that they are for home or student use the only thing that really lacks in home and student versus let us say ultimate which i use for troubleshooting through over-engineering is the microsoft office tools-you cannot expect fancy things like business contact manager and the accompanying copy of sql server two thousand and five express.in case you are wondering i am reviewing this for my aunt and uncle who sat there and bought a pc in may of two thousand and nine and thanks to a certain ability i have to troubleshoot combined with them buying retail windows seven home premium upgrade through the best buy fulfillment of the windows seven upgrade option that was current at the time along with retail office two thousand and seven home and student that they beat out of hp's customer dis service-albeit with having to pay for it i get to and thoroughly enjoy troubleshooting their pc whenever it is having an issue because i am on a mission to keep them off of the crack windows that is windows 8/ rt /8 one rt 8.1 windows phone 8x windows phone 8.1 x and i thoroughly enjoy every time i can fix their pc that uses this software.office two thousand and seven home and student was a change for them at first from the wordperfect office suite they were using on their old xp computer a dell dimension two thousand , four hundred they replaced it with an amd athlon sixty-four x2 seven thousand , seven hundred and fifty 4gb ram 500gb hd hp pavilion slimline s5120y but then again so was vista and then seven they did not have too much trouble with vista but windows seven home premium combined with this version of office makes them able to do everything they would ever want to do with office and a pc when that changes they will upgrade-and so far it is not changing i just think that office two thousand and seven whether lowly home and student or mighty ultimate or something in between like professional did not deserve the reputation it got as regards the ribbon people were and some still are so angry about the ribbon that they do not like office because of the ribbon i know i am not as qualified as some people to speak due to my aversion to command line interfaces whether of the old school dos unix variety or whether of the newfangled windows powershell variety but i know this for a fact once i properly configured their pc with windows seven home premium retail upgrade on a clean install and reimported their programs files and settings they were using it productively as could be until a virus hit that forced them to pay someone way too much to repair their computer i was able to set it right and from the moment i first showed them how to do basic things like bold underline italics margins indentation in other words showed them where microsoft office two thousand and seven home and student put the tools they were using in wordperfect office they have been happily using office with the ribbon i hate to discount those who have had negative experiences with office two thousand and seven because i do not like most change-especially not the licensing restrictions growing ever tighter since two thousand but i have not had any problems with the ribbon either.so with the ribbon discounted for us and our family we can now move on to infinitely more pressing matters which is how does office specifically two thousand and seven home and student perform in real world tasks well it does not make you have to renew the usage rights to it every year it supports the docx xlsx pptx trio and it has a user interface that aside from being different is actually usable if you can figure out what each button on each section of the ribbon is for which tooltips really help with that and they are on by default in summation for the reasons outlined above microsoft office two thousand and seven home and student is worth the money if you can get a legal copy i recommend it as long as it is needs match up well with what you need out of specifically microsoft office take this as you will two families experiences with office two thousand and seven one ultimate one home and student which is positive and we continue to use office two thousand and seven to this day

text_review: i was a turbotax user for years but the price increases for the two thousand and fourteen tax year were way too much for me so i switched to h r block basic it seems to have all the tax forms of any full featured tax program at a fraction of the tt price h r imported all my information from last year's tt files without any apparent trouble like tt you can do an interview or fill out the forms i had no problem navigating the program it is just as annoying as tt in that it wants you to register although you can avoid doing so with the requisite number of extra clicks my review is preliminary as i have not done much with the program yet i did have an installation problem that i wanted to share i got the disk inserted it in my cd drive and the disk was read in the normal fashion i clicked on the tcauto.exe file to install the program and it ran but when i clicked the install button i got an error message software did not install correctly i ended up calling h r and got a friendly guy on the phone none of the usual things worked while he was off looking for an answer i navigated to the installer folder on the disk and ran the exe file there the program installed normally that was good because the helper was out of ideas i report this in case others have the same problem

text_review: i have tried many different noise canceling headphones and determined that the quiet comfort three are the best on the market at first these headphones sound like a piece of crap but after you break them in for about a week the sound is gorgeous when i first got these headphones i was stunned at the level of noise reduction to test them out i turned on some music on my home theater system then connected these headphones to a zune hd before the music on the zune even started playing i was amazed at how little i could hear from my home theater system when the music began playing i could not believe my ears i could not hear a sound but the audio quality was not the best and my ears felt like there were being sucked in after about five minutes of use i noticed i yawning quite a lot the next day i went out and bought the beats by dr dre and took them home to test them when i first put them on i noticed hard and striking bass the base in these headphones were actually better then the bose there was also pretty good treble as i started listening to these headphones a little bet more and the results were not to good in some songs the treble and bass were perfect but in other songs there was way to much base i did a little research on the beats and found out that these headphones were made for hip hop as stated by dr dre himself who is the creator of these headphones said that when he herd in the club by fifty cent was when he knew he had created the perfect headphones being an audiophile i was not really wild about this idea so i went back to the bose one thing i did like about the beats was that it has a mute button on the side when i started using the bose again i noticed that they sounded a lot better then they once did i was yawning significantly less my ears were not a sucked in and that the bose were a lot smaller and lighter the the beats so i returned the beats and kept the bose

text_review: if you are in the market for screenwriting software do not buy movie magic screenwriter version six i have used movie magic since the ninety s it is fundamentally a great tool for writing screenplays and i have written several using it however the reason you should not buy it is because this company does not seem to be putting anymore money into updates the windows version is buggy beyond belief and i have been waiting for an update from version 6.0 5.89 for years there are no definitive answers to when an update will be available and frankly it is irrelevant at this point because there are far more inexpensive options that do the job and do it well the fact of the matter is you do not need all the bells and whistles this program offers and the price point reflects a time when this and final draft were the only game in town that was ten years ago now the price is ridiculously over-inflated when you consider the competition especially for a program that cannot function bug-free in a windows 7,8 8.1 environment no tech support updates no purchase no recommendation

text_review: i have been using bitdefender for the past couple of years i found the two thousand and eight version for three computers for two years at a great price when it was running out i went looking for a similar deal and found one i noticed a couple of unpolished elements when installing there were a lot of dos command prompt windows opening in the background on the screen very briefly i did not have to interact with any of them and they went away almost immediately so there is no harm to it it is just a little unpolished i should also mention that the update for it is big it will ask to download the updated installer then after a few minutes when that is downloaded and run the updates for the program are currently over seventy-five mb i think that is probably the case with many anti-virus programs but just be aware if you are on dial-up you will be downloading for quite some time i uninstalled that old from a laptop and a desktop the desktop went fine but the laptop failed to uninstall i tried to get the uninstall program off bitdefender's website but the link they pointed to was dead eventually i found the cd and reinstalled which failed but the cd had the uninstaller which worked i only mention this because it is a little worrisome that if the last program had those issues that this version might when i eventually uninstall it i like this version of the program it has several different modes ranging from novice hides settings to expert showing all of it and is very easy to change between them my absolute favorite part though is the you are not fully protected system in past programs i have used if you disable some feature you constantly get the little alert icon that you are at risk bitdefender two thousand and ten lets you choose which of those things it monitors for so i did not want the anti-spam because i only use web mail so i told it not to bother me that i would deleted it it may be a small thing but to me it is a huge annoyance saver.so far i cannot tell if the scanner is faster or not it scans at only about a quarter of the number of files per second as the old program but it supposedly has an intelligent monitoring system which lets it avoid rescanning files that have not changed and thus could not have picked up an infection so while it was not that fast on the first scan in theory it will only get faster moving forward it intentionally skipped thousands of files.default is a daily scan which in my opinion is complete overkill unless you have a kid in your house if the resident protection is running all the time you can get by with once or twice a week thankfully the scheduling is very easy and you can even set the scans to take low priority which is a nice touch.in terms of detection bitdefender is not the highest rated scanner but it is far from the lowest it is an excellent budget anti-virus package and more than adequate for most people's needs considering how reasonable the pricing is i would happily recommend however since i have only used it a week or so if it does do anything really weird i will update my review to mention it.update 8/ 3/10- finally had to use my printer and guess what bitdefender has killed it i cannot use my network printer so i am dropping this review a couple stars i killed its firewall and turned the windows one on again guess what i can print again i wasted two hours dealing trying to fix it before i gave up unacceptable behavior in a firwall.ce saver so far i cannot tell if the scanner is faster or not it scans at only about a quarter of the number of text_review: i am a perennial naysayer when it comes to quicken's upgrades yes i agree with everyone who complains about intuit's business model of introducing mandatory upgrades periodically that one is forced to take because older versions become obsoleted but ultimately time marches on and software does need to be upgraded once having accepted the inevitible intuit notified me they would no longer be supporting premier two thousand and seven come april two thousand and ten i sighed a deep sigh and purchased quicken two thousand and ten rental property version for all practical intents and purposes this is quicken premier two thousand and ten with a couple extra bells and whistles so my review is for both products.after installing quicken property manager two thousand and ten i checked every account and report that was critical to me apart from the usual cosmetic gui differences i found nothing amiss the migration of data files went very smoothly and for once there is an aspect of quicken's upgrades worth the hassle now instead of four or five separate quicken files intuit manages to keep everything in one albeit larger file in terms of keeping track of backup files this is a significant improvement.also all settings and functionality remained intact downloading transactions from several brokerage accounts continue to work flawlessly i do not download transactions from banks or credit card companies i tried this once for an existing credit card account and ended up with hundreds of unwanted transactions in the upload if starting with a new credit card or bank account i imagine it would be nice to simply upload the transactions from the financial institution doing so into an existing account proved more hassle than i wanted to deal with so i continue to hand enter the couple dozen credit card transactions a month i deal with having recently acquired a rental property i opted for this version over quicken premier two thousand and ten whether or not the additional functionality of keeping a data base of rental properties is useful to you may depend on how many you have i only have the one and i already set up the transactions in the earlier version i am not sure its even worth my while to investigate this functionality but if you have many investment properties this might be a better way of keeping track of properties tennants income flow mortgage payments and tax related transaction this is the only funtional difference i see between quicken rental property two thousand and ten and quicken premier two thousand and seven i have investment accounts some with transaction going back to one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-two e g a mutual fund that i have been dollar cost averaging into since then so for managing my investment portfolio quicken premier is minimally a necessity on that front my only beefs are that one a graph that used to be available many versions ago is still sadly missing they used to have the ability to chart stock price history and market value on the same graph quite useful to see at a glance how well or poorly you timed the market with your purchases or sales luckily i get close to this functionality in fidelity's active trader charting two investment performance reporting continues to be problematic under certain circumstances performance statistics are annualized so at the beginning of a calendar year you could be looking at some grossly exaggerated performance numbers the same holds true for positions you only held for a short period of time what seems to be missing is a simple report that gives you the actual percentage gain or loss on a specific trade for example let us say you bought one hundred shares of xyz corp at ten per share today and you sold it tomorrow for eleven this is a simple ten actual gain ignoring transaction costs in quicken this is annualized to some phenominally large percentage as if you had earned ten per day for the entire year when analysing individual security performance this can be problematic three exporting to excel has never been a strong suit you can indeed export an account to excel but you cannot subsequently update an existing excel spreadsheet this is a pain it would be nice to develop reports in excel that quicken simply does not provide if you go throught the effort of exporting data to a spreadsheet it would be nice if you did not have to start from scratch every time now if i am simply undereducated in the use of excel then please someone out there direct me to the appropriate feature that would allow me to append a new month's worth of data to an existing spreadsheet via quicken export.now for the biggest improvement in the quicken experience since my last upgrade quicken actually has telephone support staff that call you when you have install or program issues i thought i found a bug in the net worth reporting in two thousand and ten i followed the support links under help and opted to have a quicken tech support person call me on the phone within minutes a very knowledgable support rep called me back and spent about an hour helping me debug the problem this included having me upload quicken premier seven uninstalling quicken two thousand and ten reinstalling the two thousand and seven program to see if the bug predated the two thousand and ten upgrade to make a long story short the problem orininated last year and had nothing to do with quicken two thousand and ten or the upgrade to said program now ultimately i did need to find the single transaction that hosed the report myself i deleted the transaction and reentered it bingo problem solved today i reinstalled quicken rental property two thousand and ten and am getting on with my life still i cannot say enough how stunned i am merely to know that after all these years of non-existant customer support intuit has finally delivered all in all i would say you need not be afraid of upgrading to quicken two thousand text_review: purchased this for my nine year old son for his birthday he loves basketball and i loved that it had the scripture on it to remind him to try and be confident i was worried it would not be boyish enough as most reviewers mentioned they bought it for girls i feel it is definitely gender neutral enough for my son i liked that it was simple and not too flashy but still had some color on it and not just play gray like some others the saying is around the ball on the front and stamped on the back the words bill and jill are stamped right at the bottom of the phrase which i do not particularly like i understand the desire to place a company name etc on the necklace but it looks odd like it is part of the scripture the words are slightly puffy and kind of run together on the front around the ball which is unlike the picture and makes it slightly illegible think bubble letters all touching together i do not know if that is normal for the look or if my son's is an exception the chain is quite long my son is on the tall side and the basketball hangs right at his sternum i will be getting a shorter chain for him soon.overall my son likes this necklace and i like it for the price despite not loving that the chain is longer than i want for him and the letters are slightly jumbled i do believe i will buy another one for my son's friend and hope that theirs turns out a little nicer

text_review: leaving aside a blatant error in the sub-title roaring 20s yes but the 30s were the depression era this is a fascinating and fantastic collection many of these songs have stood the test of time well.as with all music this old it cannot be technically perfect some tracks have crackles and hiss but this is often how these records sounded to listeners back then when recorded music was a novelty people tolerated the imperfections if you must have perfect sound quality do not buy music this old.there are more recent covers of many of these songs and the compilers have included some here which emphasize the limitations of the original ancient recordings i like the puppini sisters and the temperance seven but while these 20s 30s revivalists have made some excellent music i have mixed feelings about their inclusion here still if their presence means more people discover the original music here that is a good thing.there are other less obvious llater covers too including the ella louis cover of dream a little dream of me which they recorded in one thousand , nine hundred and fifty this song dates from the thirties but was revived in the sixties first by the shirelles and later by mama cass.despite some songs being later covers most of the recordings are genuine recordings from the 20s and 30s which capture the spirit of the music superbly i am glad that helen kane's version of i wanna be loved by you was included despite the crackling i like marilyn monroe's cover but helen's presence here reminds me to look for some of her own music hoping that some of it has survived with fewer crackles.whether you are just getting curious about this type of music or you have some already as i do this is an excellent compilation

text_review: which is to say xp is the titanic it sinks and it stinks and all the bells whistles cannot cover it over i bought the upgrade home edition and overlaid it on a machine running millennium--a dell celeron ostensibly it reformatted my machine to ntfs from fat thirty-two however it preserved my entire collection of useless millennium files the first thing i found i had to do was go out and spend price on a new roxio cd burner copier because nobody bothered to mention that the version that came with millennium would not work with xp--and so the industry panders to microsoft and lets them get away with this highway robbery.since installation in january i have had to reinstall the system on top of itself twice it has developed a tendency to crash on any software it dislikes not freeze and shut down one application but just plain halt the machine and reboot no explanation no error message just crash and restart.its only positive is the system restore feature that is a big positive but it is not enough to offset the liabilities i would like to go over to two thousand better i would like to go over to linux if i knew there was a solid windows emulator--i've heard wine is drek and i have got a small fortune tied up in windows-based software some of which does not work anyway because it will not run under xp

text_review: disclaimer i have had this lens for about three days now if anything changes i will update this review otherwise you can assume that i am still just as happy as i am now.before buying this i looked at every available uwa on the market for my nikon d3200 i checked the reviews including the ratings on dxomark's website great technical reference but it is all lab and no field ratings i found various professional reviews and read virtually every user review i could find in amazon and google shopping i looked at nikon's 10-24 mm the other tokina uwa's and other maker's lenses as well of all the lenses this one had the most positive and least negative reviews above all possibly tied with the tokina 11-16 the 11-16 is one f-stop faster and no-one had any autofocusing issues as were reported with some of the 11-24 s however no autofocus issues were reported on the 11-28 either on the nikon 10-24 most complaints were about vignetting and softness at the edges although some disliked the plastic instead of metal mount and that it is made in red china the fact that it costs around 1,000 it can now be found for about seven hundred and fifty not only motivated me to look a different lenses but frankly speaking ... given the reviews i expected more for that kind of money so i decided to take a chance on this lens instead of the 11-16 or 10-24.great choice :) i have shot about sixty pictures so far and this lens absolutely performs to my expectations and a little above to be honest fyi i shoot strictly raw and post process using dxolabs excellent optics pro software standard edition.sharpness is excellent from edge to edge regardless of zoom setting i have seen no sign of fringing even when shooting in dim light at f4 with a 1/15 shutter speed using iso four hundred and even iso one thousand low-light noise and graininess is the same as i get from all my other lenses at the same settings in fact ... i would say that the sharpness of this lens compares very favorably to my nikon prime 2.8 35mm which i absolutely love autofocus works exactly as advertised quite well and quickly but is slightly noisier than my nikons are i did however switch from single-point focus to multipoint during uwa shots and i think that the focusing of the lens was a bit quicker that way but that could simply be a subjective reaction.when zooming or using manual focus the feel of the lens is precise and smooth the shift from autofocus to manual is done by pulling the focus ring toward you which takes some getting used to ... but is brilliant no need to feel around for switches and hope you are not getting the vr switch instead of the a m switch on a nikon the barrel length does not change during zoom it is all internal and there is no zoom creep if you point the lens down or up i do wish that this lens had a vr feature but then again neither does my 35mm from nikon nor does the 10-24 mm from nikon either for me this means that i will need to bring my monopod when shooting uwa interior shots inside historical buildings and mansions where flash is forbidden but honestly that is no big deal i did not have vr during my film days so this was a common requirement.colors are accurate and well saturated i see no vignetting at any setting distortion is exactly what you would expect from a uwa and is easily corrected via dxolabs opticspro which has a module for this lens or you can use their stand-alone viewpoint product which costs less but gives you greater control over perspective corrections note viewpoint only handles jpgs so you will still need to have a post-processing software to export your raws you can also use adobe's lightroom to fix perspectives as well but that is a completely manual process if you shoot raw and do post-processing you really should take a look at dxolab's products especially opticspro.lastly the lens has a solid professional feel to it unlike the plastic nikons and some other brands it is reminiscent of my old series one lenses back from my film days ... there is no dust blowback from zooming into the camera since the zoom is internal and the docking collar is steel not plastic which is nice because it reduces concerns about fragility when spending five hundred on a lens.to sum it up this is probably the best uwa lens out there running at f four especially when you look at the cost i would buy this again :) if you want to see some of my tests go to mercerpics at smugmug and look for the tokina test gallery.postscript i took the lens with me today for a visit to my seven month old grandson along with my 35mm prime nikon lens now this should be no surprise to anyone ... but inside without a flash f four was a tough aperture to use due to slow shutter speeds at iso one hundred having said that about half the shots i took using the 12-28 still came out very sharp especially when shooting at 28mm i switched to my 35mm and ran it at f 2.8 simply because my grandson is a very active baby and i was getting too much motion blur with the f four tokina if you are planning on using the tokina inside without a flash you need still subjects and a monopod if shooting low iso s of course otherwise boost the iso which is not really a big deal on the new generation of dslr's they do a great job of keeping detail and reducing noise it is kind of hard to see a difference between iso one hundred and iso four hundred unless you are pixel peeping :) the reason i mention this is because when i use vr nikon lenses it is like picking up two f-stops ... and it is easy to forget that is not the case with either the tokina or the nikon prime lenses since i am planning on using this lens for inside architecture shots in somewhat dim historical homes running this through it is paces at extreme parameters in advance was a good idea outside shots in the sun were unbelievably sharp and clear fyi :) still loving this lens

text_review: 3.5 four stars pros compact it is barely the size of my ear nice looking nice silver finish very high tech lightweight if the ear loop is comfortable for you you could probably wear it for hours cons the directions for set-up are horrific fortunately the motoblu customer service is very good the two people i spoke with had thick accents but they were very knowledgeable and able to walk me through the proper set-up steps fyi i was pairing the h700 with a motorola phone so you think it would be seamless not so once again the directions are very inaccurate i never did get a blue light when i was pairing the phone only purple and i had to hold the call button while opening the boom mic which the directions did not mention oh and like a reviewer stated before the directions point to the small motorola icon on the headset and say this is where the blue light will show it is actually the ring around the call button that lights up this is not a reason to find another headset ... just be prepared it is quite simple to get up and running once you have proper instruction lol and i also got a red light when the headset was charging not a blue one mental note to self call motorola and have them hire different monkey for next version of directions sound is decent but not like talking listening directly from the phone i have not heard other headsets so i cannot say if it is better or worse than another model but it definitely takes a little getting used to on a positive note i asked my friend if he could tell i was on a headset and he said no the ear loop is a little uncomfortable for my ears not big or small just average it is very light but the loop just does not fit great this is most likely going to be different for every person this headset is worth your time but i am not sure i would wantto pay full price for it how and where you get it is up to you hope this info is useful

text_review: i give win eight and this upgrade version four stars because though i do not like it . . . yet . . . i am coming to understand slowly why microsoft needed to make this painful transition and to see just how difficult what they are trying to do is i upgraded from a factory installed version of win eight on a new toshiba satellite i7 laptop to win eight pro because i needed the domain network connectivity i would be called a power user but i am not a network administrator nor a systems expert so this is anecdotal information from my own experience only i hope this post helps but proceed with caution on this advise the most important thing i can pass on . . . and which i did not do is to make sure you are connected to the domain you want to access when you start the upgrade process preferably via a hard wired cat five cable i figured i could do the upgrade install at home and connect later bad idea second know what types of computer names are acceptable for the domain you will be connecting too and of course know your network log in info lastly after the upgrade is complete do not stop updating just keep running the windows update utility again and again and yes again until you are sure there is nothing left to get from the windows update site win eight takes getting use to but it is the right direction for microsoft to take they had to make this painful design jump as some point or risk becoming increasingly irrelevant in today's market but like with xp to vista i am already ready for win nine with the hope it will be a another win seven winner

text_review: simon rattle has recorded a lot of 19th century music and most of the results have been dismal there is little to recommend by rattle in pre 20th century repertoire a few haydn symphonies some pretty good brahms bits of mahler ein heldenleben by strauss which is just at the cusp of the 20th century alright so rattle is not the conductor to go to for the great classics however when he records modern music he seems fully in tune with it is sound and style plus he has less competition on the market to boot here is a collection from a trio of composers that seem forever destined to be tough nuts to crack as far as their music being loved and achieving mass exposure they are never going to achieve popularity at the same time anyone with an open mind and open ears can be enthralled by the works contained here schoenberg's creepy mysterious five orchestral pieces webern's ethereal and far more compact six orchestral pieces rattle plays them all with nuance and feeling the real reason i bought this disc is the lulu suite and it is a breathtaking haunting compilation from berg's great modern opera arleen auger is the soprano soloist and she scores great on all accounts her contribution is limited to two tracks so people who are afraid of operatic singing need not worry rattle and his burmingham orchestra are the true stars comparing directly rattle's take on the lulu suite against abbado's with the lso on dg i consistently find rattle more involved more refined and sharper when the music needs more violence the digital recording by emi is also expert and scores over dg's analogue sound for abbado which lacks some atmosphere rattle made this record back in 1987-88 and it stands up to any competition on the market

text_review: i have heard more recordings of the merry widow than i can count and many of them are enjoyable none however has the infectious charm and elegance of this one thousand , nine hundred and sixty-two emi version true the performance could probably have been accommodated on a single cd with very few seconds to spare and yes there are some cuts but what is presented here constitutes something so special so illuminating and so magical that it hardly matters von matacic shapes this cream puff of an operetta with even more verve that otto ackermann did on the previous one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-three emi recording also with schwarzkopf and one can almost feel the fizz of the champagne throughout the entire performance elisabeth schwarzkopf was born to sing the title role and in my humble opinion no other soprano comes within miles of what she accomplishes here her idiomatic dialogue her vocal shadings and her musical instincts are balm to the ear she easily surpasses her previous monophonic emi performance of nine years earlier and that was a great one nicolai gedda also surpasses his earlier work on that legendary one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-three recording offering singing of very great lyricism and beauty eberhart wachter was a very fine baritone and made some wonderful recordings his singing here however seems to me to be a little gruff a little crude and peppered with too much speak singing especially when heard in close proximity to schwarzkopf and gedda still this was is one of the greatest recordings emi ever made truly a worthy entry to the great recordings of the century series and it showcases the artistry of schwarzkopf magnificently this would definitely be one of my desert-island recordings with the announcement this morning that elisabeth schwarzkopf passed away this recording becomes even more legendary it is a beautiful memorial to one of the greatest sopranos of the last century

text_review: years ago pre hd i had signal issues with cable strength to a couple cable ready analog sets i am 400ft off the road another sixty ft or so from a pedestal to the house i installed a motorola four way amp fixed it all then a storm blew it out comcast eventually buried new cable from pedistal to house.that fixed it all now with adding hd i had issues with some channels on a comcast xfinity hd unit the unit is the furthest 75ft from the systems entry point a two way splitter to a modem four way splitter that goes to two analogs two sony lcd's one on the hd unit the other straight cable to coax input the instructions suggested to install the unit at the entry point of the cable i installed the amp in the room w hd unit the channels that were the usual issues were acting up i installed the amp all was fixed did another a-b test and all good so time will tell if issues return or if installing at end of 75ft cable run before hd unit causes other problems then i will install at entry point either prior to four way or between four way house cable but initial results are good.instructions were thorough but no mention of the grounding screw i have no easily accessable ground in the room i would have one at the entry point

text_review: for a long time i depended upon mcafee products to protect my computers i have no idea what is happened over there but maybe they have gotten fat dumb happy because this product is so bad it nearly rendered my computer non-functional scans are extremely slow hours long sometimes and the incessant scanning during typical daily use sucks up so much processor power and memory that you will relive those days of yesteryear with a two hundred and eighty-six microprocessor 14.4 dial-up speeds just to be sure i was not doing something wrong i actually uninstalled reinstalled the product twice with mcafee's assistance the problems did not go away and god help you if you try to stop the scan mid-way through because it might just crash your machine it did it to mine twice then there was a two hour reinstall recovery process.in short if you use this product you may become a slave to your security software check consumer reports and you will see what i mean about the slowness of the scans i switched to trend micro ... so much easier to install run scans are very quick one last thing once you actually become a mcafee customer just try finding any sort of useful contact info on their website and once you do it will lead you through a long series of irrelevant questions before you have the privilege of waiting in a ten minute phone queue.mcafee i am through with you you have been uninstalled

text_review: four hundred cd's or about four thousand songs on a little machine the size of a deck of cards the ipod is what they meant when they say technology will make things more conveinent for us in the future i put all my cd's about two hundred and a bunch of my dad's music as well that took up 8.5 gb so i still have about 10gb left the functional capacity of the 20gb ipod is 18.5gb.about the whole musicmatch vs xplay vs ephpod debate i downloaded all three i have been using mm with the new dell i got so it made sense for me to keep on using it i reccommend to future buyers that they give mm a chance and not spend the money on xplay right away yes xplay is not free any longer just the trial version was free a while ago mm is kind of weird though sometimes changes you make to the tags in mm will not make it to the songs in your music library.the sound the ipod produces is great just as good or better than music from a cd player i do not like ear-bud style headphones they sound fine but i prefer my ninety over the ear sony's the ipod sound just as good with those huge headphone as with the ear-buds the touch-pad is very cool a little tricky at first but you get the hang of it soon enough

text_review: i have tried the steam-type humidifiers evaporative types mechanical rotary sling-types devilbiss and ultrasonic units they all have their ups and downs but this is the best one i have ever used it is also the most expensive but the value is good because of its good design ultrasonics need water with low minerals or else you will get white dust municipal water might be ok but mine is not if you have well water you will definitely need the mineral reduction cartridge it eliminates the white dust for me entirely the puck-shaped carbon cartridges that go in the water tank also help to reduce the chlorine smell from city water together with the pre-heater quiet fan and very good flexible controls standard on this unit it is a very manageable and predictable humidifier i have used the air-o-swiss ez-cal cleaner for it so far and cleaned it well after the cleaning light went on and it cleaned the unit just fine the heater helps to evaporate the mist more quickly but you may still find you need to keep the unit higher up on a stand to prevent a small damp area on your floor i fill it twice a day and it runs non-stop at the top setting in my house because i have a large area to cover i would recommend it for the area suggested in the listing about 500-650 sq feet max they are pricey but good so if you have a larger area you may need more than one

text_review: canon has kept the price of this little gem reasonable i bought it over a year ago and use it more than any other camera it fits nicely in my shirt pocket so i frequently have the camera with me on trips i always carry an extra battery with me because the battery indicator is not very reliable when it falls below full charge it seems to go from half full to zero in no time canon needs to work on this i have a dslr of comparable megapixels that takes slightly better pictures but it is hard to tell without looking at a large print or screen view color reproduction is as accurate as i can tell outdoor especially skin tones are the best i have seen i do not mind the lower level high definition video videos look pretty good on a large tv and unless you are after an academy award you probably will not miss the full one thousand and eighty hd it could use an optical viewfinder because you almost cannot see what you are shooting in full sun unless you shade the display but the optical viewfinder would come at the expense of the ultra compact size and i would rather have the small size also because of the size the controls are tiny and you have to get used to this eventually smart phones will have these photo and video capabilities unless there are large advances in ultra compact digital cameras i think most people will use smart phones instead so they will not have to carry around two gadgets in the meantime i will use this little camera

text_review: this game is great fun if you are interested in fantasy colonial times or in building towns villages and empires if you are looking for a war game i would not suggest it it is pretty basic strategies that win this game and most of it has to do with economics and improving your village not your army although that has something to do with it obviously in the previews they show large armies with columns and rows of soldiers and stuff ... yeah that does not happen i mean unless you spend a while organizing them to march in formation or something the fighting is not visually satisfying i guess is what i am saying but if you do not mind that or if you like the sims games but you have always wanted more control or like colonial times horses and forests better than cities houses and cars than this is for you if that is the case than this game is a blast the strategies are pretty easy to pick up and the visuals are amazing one complaint i have and part of the reason why this is four stars instead of five is that i still cannot figure out how to switch between countries i can only play as the british i want to play the spanish or the dutch or something and the menus are a little hard to navigate other than that i would highly suggest it

text_review: my friend wanted a digital camera he was looking at still units but after he starting talking more about movies than stills i talked him into a video camera over a still camera this type of product has been out for awhile but most of them have been primitive needed tons of light and the videos were of generally low quality i have canon slr units their digital sensors are some of the best in my opinion so i started checking out this camera most consumer sites have glowing review after glowing review on the fs100 we have had this unit about three months we have used it quite a lot under mostly daylight conditions where these units most often fall down is in the amount of light they need to get good pictures my old tape camcorder can easily get good video in candle light this one is not quite that good but it is dang close most often with these units low light means unacceptably grainy images ... this unit does pretty well with that from what i have seen at least in middle quality mode the book states minimum light something like one hundred lux which is around dim room light after i got this i took it to the target parking lot at night and shot some video under just the parking lot mercury lamps ... i was looking for two things ... grainy images and color shifts caused by the non-daylight colored lamps in the parking area lighting i happened to catch a guy riding across the parking lot on his bike at a pretty good clip and tested the camera by tracking him across the lot and zooming in and out all the while ... the image was a bit grainy but it was acceptable and surprisingly good for a camera of this variety at night and under non daylight colored light ... i e canon's sensor is pretty darn good my first canon slr is pretty brain dead when it comes to mixed lighting situations but they seem to have straightened up their act in later products in that regard white balance logic there is a competing product of this type made by samsung the price isgenerally a bit lower than the canon i have looked at that unit but not had a chance to use one on that unit folks are saying the buttons are too flimsy another reason i went with this one we use this camera to shoot a lot of fast action sca heavy fighting i find that the default auto setting does not result in a fast enough shutter speed to catch very fast action this unit has a mode that allows you to choose the shutter speed while the camera chooses the aperature ... i fixed the blurred action by setting the camera shutter speed to 1/250 or faster and that has cured that issue completely i have not shot in full quality mode ... really do not need it ... middle quality mode is pretty darn good even displayed on a large flat panel although i am sure a true hd video snob would sniff indignantly at it this camera supports sdhd so you are not limited to two gig memory cards the sixteen gig cards are currently out like three hours in middle quality mode and thirty-two gig cards are also available but still too expensive if you get this camera i suggest you buy an image bank handheld self-powered device with notebook hard drive in it so you can clean off your cards and reuse them this camera does not have touch screen i really do not miss that at all the joystick is very serviceable i find the menus easy to navigate and the camera has a good variety of settings if i did not mention it before the camera can also take still images that are very acceptable overall what i think about it i like the camera i think if it was up to me i would redesign the zoom lever yes it is under your fingers as you hold the camera ... but i find it a little bit awkward especially when zooming in higher magnifications i would prefer to have the zoom on the back where i can hit it with my thumb canon does their usual thing of monopolizing batteries and accessories for this camera by not releasing tech specs so other companies can make products that work with it batteries are outrageous at eighty bucks plus each you can find them on amazon for around sixty but that is still outrageous in my book you can find knock off batteries on ebay that power the camera but they do not have the internal electronics and thus the camera cannot detect the charge and they will not charge on the camera one of your first purchases should be two sixteen gig sdhc cards they are not too high if you shop around four gig cards will suffice to start but get the biggest ones you can get and stick with a quality manufacturer as well i did not pick high speed cards for this camera i have not noticed lag caused because the camera buffers were full and could not write to the card fast enough ... at least not in mid quality mode ... high quality may be another issue what i am saying is i do not know if investing in the high speed memory cards is worth it for this item like it is for my professional slrs this is a great unit especially around the price that amazon has it for it is great to not have to digitize your movie you just pop out the card and play it with windows media player this unit also does not use any kind of custom format like some of the other cameras do it is stock mpeg two right off the camera so you do not have to translate it before windows can play it or roxio can burn it onto a cd dvd yes i would buy this again

text_review: the d70 is the digital slr to record daily life and life events with a six megapixel resolution limits the size of prints you can make with it to about eleven by seventeen if this is not a problem for you then this is your digital camera if you want to be able to make larger prints with good resolution then you need to spend a great deal more money for a higher resolution digital camera about 5,000 or stick with film i keep my old n90 for these purposes the d70 comes bundled with the excellent and compact 18-70 nikkor lens and one en-el three battery to get started with the camera i suggest the following in addition one extra en-el three lithium-ion battery two 2gb 80x compactflash cards with write acceleration wa technology one cf card reader for your computer firewire or usb connection depending upon your needs as time and money permit you may want to add the following a telephoto lens for wildlife and sporting events the 70-300 mm f4 -5.6 g af nikkor is a great value and complements the bundled lens nicely if money is not an object step up to the 70-300 ed or the 70-200 f2 eight with vibration reduction a good macro lens such as the af micro nikkor 105mm f2 eight polarizing filters for both the kit lens and the telephoto get nikon filters there is no sense in spending money for nikkor lenses and then putting junk filters on them a bag to carry all this stuff this will get you nicely started further down the line you may wish to get the following a speedlight either the sb six hundred or eight hundred a tripod and ballhead be sure to check prices at b h photo as well as those shown here they have a tremendous selection and have long been known and trusted by serious photographers in addition i would suggest that anyone who buys a d70 join nikonians there or literally tens of thousands of people who are more than happy to help you with any question you may haveabout nikon cameras lenses and other equipment as well as help you with your photography skills and bet of all it is free go to nikonians.org

text_review: there are a lot of football games out this year like espn nfl 2k5 madden nfl two thousand and five and of course ncaa football two thousand and five i have played all of these games and in my opinion you need to think of what you want in a football game before buying any of them if you are a die-hard nfl fan looking for a realistic but still strategic football game in which starting a team franchise is not much of a plus for you save your money and buy the 20.00 espn nfl 2k5 if you want a beautifully enhanced a i to rough it out with madden nfl two thousand and five is your best bet due to the much more intelligent a i mainly line backs and defense backs madden is also made better due to the ingenious franchise mode madden has always dominated franchise so you should always expect the best from them in that department now on to ncaa football two thousand and five this game has a few big changes that make it unique from any other football game the first is homefield advantage this makes it possible to pump up the crowd in a game and ice or lower your opponents composure each player has a meter in which their composure is shown players with lower composure have a much better chance of being shut down than a well-composed player this makes homefield advantage very valuable so in all honesty ncaa football two thousand and five is agreat game that any college or professional should own

text_review: i can connect to the camera when i select the camera as my wireless network on my phone or tablet but never through the home wireless network which is why i got it in the first place if you have time to tinker with this constantly scan the qr code and contact support after watching their tutorials give it a shot i spent over an hour trying to connect the device but it would not connect not all the text on their app is in english so there are a few things that i did not understand i attempted to connect the device using two different wireless networks not the same router with an iphone six ios 8.2 and a 3rd gen ipad ios 8.3 but it would not connect the connect status would go from zero and up then when it reached eighty-one to ninety it would say the connection failed the first time i was a little over ten ft away from the router but then i moved closer the other times and that did not work either i watched each video including the advanced video on the website that the paper in the box suggested i made sure the lights were flashing the way they needed to restarted the device reset it when i was not sure what else to do i got to borrow a similar type of camera different brand and that connected right away strange.update i called support very nice guy and i was told that there was a limit to password length due to a previous revision in the app he mentioned he would ask the app developer but he was not sure when it would be fixed i am not changing my password on my router s or devices to accommodate the camera sending it back hopefully there will be updates on the app

text_review: the batteries and charger do work in that the chargers charge the batteries hold more later a charge and fit various lights monitors etc and therefore provide needed power for said devices i bought five sets of the dste 2x s giving me a total of ten batteries and five chargers funny how that works is not it out of the five chargers only all five of them work that is a good thing out of the ten batteries only a few will hold a full charge overnight not so good but having written that the batteries do work and will recharge fairly quickly considering the price this not a bad deal it would be better if the batteries could hold a full charge overnight but that should not be a deal killer other brands run out of steam quicker and do not bounce very well a couple of the dste's have jumped out of my hand and hit carpet and concrete without much harm they still work they are however 7.4 v not 7.2 v like some even cheaper batteries this is good because most of the smaller led lights chromo neewer yongnuo i have run an aputure amaran 528w with two of these for a reasonable over an hour amount of time require 7.4 v if you use 7.2 vs your light will not be as bright nor will it run as long.bottom line while not exactly perfect factory replacements you can buy a lot more of these for less than the cost of one oem battery

text_review: i would have easily given this play food set five stars but for two details that bothered me with the wooden serving tray the first is that it is pictured both on amazon and on the box it came in as being solid wood it is not the bottom of the try is mdf that said it may be mdf created with e zero glues as i can detect absolutely no formaldehyde odor from it and i have a nose for vocs often much to my dismay the second detail is that there was a sharp shard of wood which had splintered up on the edge of the tray we glued it down with some elmer's time will tell if that holds it or if we will have to disfigure the tray by removing it and sanding it down however now that i have gotten those relatively minor gripes out of the way the rest of the set is pretty fantastic there are two main courses a veggie burger and a fish we are vegetarians so this is more food for the girls cats and bears and so forth which is something they really desired i might add both pieces cut into six and seven pieces respectively they are quite easy to cut and unlike many velcro-attached play foods the velcro is inlaid allowing the pieces to be flush with one another thus when the items are put together they look like whole solid pieces and do not just fall apart the veggie burger is finished with a durable chip-resistant matte paint stain and has grill imprints on one side the fish is unfinished wood and has grill imprints as well both are lovely the veggie burger can be adorned with a pat of butter the fish with a small slice of lemon these are not velcro attached the side dishes include four each of green beans fries and carrots these are are simple and easily-recognizable the fork and knife are natural wood with blue-stained handles and seem quite durable there is also an attractive thin cardboard insert with a lettuce bed and a few tomato slices which jazzes up the not-as-attractive-as-advertised mdf-bottomed serving tray sadly i am not convinced this piece will last very long as it is just too bendy but i suppose it would be easy enough to make your own variation to replace it the scale of the food is almost relative to our haba erzi and plan toys play food collection probably a wee bit larger but a wee bit smaller than something like melissa and doug nonetheless i could see it pleasing fans of both it does have the distinctive advantage over melissa and doug of no reeking of formaldehyde and other mystery chemicals and claims to have been processed in an ecologically sustainable and socially responsible manner bottom line no doubt i would buy this again save for the tray this set is beautifully crafted and very high quality it will last and last it is got a fantastic array of play stuff for an unusually fair price oh and my five-year old daughter played with it for two hours after it arrived today so it is got her seal of approval

text_review: i like puzzles that make sense and these did you push a button you see the result without having to hunt around for what is going on for example in mysterious journey two there is several puzzles where you have to form a circuit or connect one side of a grid to another by clicking on dials ... very straight-forward puzzles draw the grids out and it is not difficult to work out on paper in another you find your way across a fog enshrouded pathway very cool by plotting the path from below.while there is very little having to combine information from several sources to figure out a puzzle it does occur once or twice druing the main part of the game and again at the end and there is a few math-based puzzles too in varying degrees of difficulty hey that is what universal hint system is for still gamers with more experience than i might not have much problem wtih them.an earlier reviewer mentioned that half the time a puzzle led to nothing just an area to look out of i am not sure where the reviewer is referring to but i did not find that to be true you open a door and there is something to find learn about in a cut-scene see or do behind it.the storyline is interesting and well developed and the ending is satisfying.as far as graphics i am not a tech person but i found them to be very pretty i wish i could have roamed a bit more in a few places the graphics looked just too inviting to simply view from afar the landscape is filled with bright colors and intriguing designs this is not click and point so you are able to move about freely.the music is not great but at least it does not detract from the game the voices are fine a cut above most games the mechanical voices are done with a bit of special effects a nice touch the computer-rendered people move fairly naturally you have little control over settings but in my experience the game ran fine athlon 64x2 geforce 7600gs i wish there were more games like this puzzles clues that are scattered hither and yon only to make little sense is not my idea of fun i would recommend mysterious journey two to anyone who wants an easier game that does not over-tax their brain.rce 7600gs i wish there were more games like this puzzles clues that are scattered hither and yon only to make little sense is not my idea of fun i would recommend mysterious journey two to anyone who wants an easier game that does not over-tax their brain

text_review: originally released in one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-six get closer is the 8th proper seals crofts album and incredibly despite its gold-selling status as well as the presence of the top ten soft rock staple that is the title track it is taken over thirty years for this album in full to get cd release in the us if not the whole world if you read through the original album liner notes before listening you would come across some seemingly discouraging signs only eight songs with a total duration of less than thirty-five minutes plus an album-closer that runs well over six minutes a closer look and you will see two songs copyrighted one thousand , nine hundred and sixty-nine and an additional one copyrighted one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-two and in fact the opening song sweet green fields had already been recorded way back in the 60s by the knickerbockers famed for their infamous beatles knockoff lies all of this inescapably gets one thinking that jim dash were probably burning out and or under pressure to crank out an album before the start of a tour and or to meet a warners brothers deadline maybe they were under pressure hardly an unlikely scenario in the record business but despite all of that get closer somehow ends up being the most consistently engaging album seals crofts made during their 1969-1980 run a fantastic album that is carefully crafted flawlessly professional yet still passionately sung and played the opening sweet green fields is a marvelous epic with edgy verses a feel-good chorus and a soaring bridge section it is followed by the title track--the odds that anyone reading this has never heard the song is so slim that i suppose i just as well refrain from comment but suffice it to say that it is a great soft rock anthem regardless of how sick to death of it you might be and understandably so and carolyn willis co-lead vocals help underline its gospel leaning the next track red long ago is another brilliant epic with a simple yet irresistibly dreamy looping piano line played by david paich andbracing dynamics the closing track on side one in vinyl terms provides some respite from all the preceeding drama with a relatively short and lightweight albeit really fun and catchy tune called goodbye old buddies which was written by parker mcgee the same guy who wrote i would really love to see you tonight and other songs for england dan john ford coley ); mcgee recorded his own version of this song for his lone self-titled album also released in one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-six but the seals crofts version with a typically excellent lead vocal spotlight from dash crofts is easily the preferrable version side two opens with baby blue which starts off sounding like a rather pedestrian 70s mid-tempo pop-rock ballad albeit pleasant but then goes on to achieve greatness with its out-of-nowhere wistful yet bouncy bridge section punctuated by a memorable lead guitar line million dollar horse despite somewhat strange lyrics is a beautiful heartstring-tugging ballad as is the poetic do not fail which is even more poignant it is somewhat incredible to think that james seals had do not fail waiting in the wings for five years before it finally appearing on album maybe they would tried to record it earlier but were unsatisfied with the results especially considering some of the lesser compositions that were used on earlier albums the album ends with passing thing which has some french lyrics not to mention a lovely melody although it is mostly another one of their instrumental showcases giving jim dash a chance to duel it out on acoustic guitar and mandolin respectively only on this final track does it really feel like jim dash were padding the album to compensate for lack of material but it is still a thoroughly enjoyable piece displaying all-around impeccable musicianship and it is interesting to hear the honest-to-goodness drum machine that crops up on the second half of the track yes they did indeed have them back in the 70s although it hardly sounds like what you have probably come to associate drum machines with in other words they are hardly foreshadowing 80s dance-pop or 90s electronica as usual get closer was produced by louie shelton and if the album sounds a bit more steely dan-ish than you remember that is easily explained by the fact that seals crofts were using many of the same players including larry carlton guitar jim horn saxophone and future toto members david paich keyboards and jeff porcaro drums rhino flashback has provided a long overdue cd reissue of this must-have album although in typical fashion of their flashback division rhino has unfortunately skimped on the packaging no musician credits etc although in compensation the list price is ultra-low in the end this is a great album from a great duo that has been known to get an unkind and unfair bad rap over the years get closer is seals crofts best

text_review: bond are four young classically-trained babes based in britain who play violins viola cello but no you cannot quite categorise them as classical because their classical instruments are blended with dance beats and electronica and the lovely bond lasses themselves dress in tight revealing outfits rather than typical classical-concert dresses let us call these girls classical pop electronica then like the bond girls themselves their debut album born is quite a curiosity but it is an intriguing one---a fine exquisite whirlpool of the classics with top forty sensibility and while looking at the four women on the cover inside photographs is entertaining enough bond obviously have no qualms about flaunting their sex appeal god bless em you have to give them credit where credit is due the girls can play victory is the obvious lead-off single a supremely catchy instrumental that gives you a darn good indication of what bond are all about in one shot but the rest of the album is just as fascinating and i find myself thoroughly entranced by the groups expertly honed pop classical confections but being such a curious group in today's music marketplace only time will tell if bond truly have a long future ahead of them or if they are destined to be a one-album wonder but born makes one thing clear the women of bond have great musical talent to match their great looks and they can only get better born is a very impressive debut by a talented up-and-coming group that you should definitely keep an eye on in the next few years

text_review: triggerfinger is a power-trio from belgium that has been steadily getting better and bigger over there from their self-titled two thousand and four album and on to two thousand and eight s what grabs ya in two thousand and ten came the band highly-anticipated third studio album if you are not familiar with triggerfinger's sound think heavy guitar-based rock not unlike say the child of a foo fighters queens of the stone age black sabbath merger all this dancin around eleven tracks fifty-one min kick off with the furious title track and we are off to the races let it ride is anotehr short take-no-prisoners song on love lost in love singer-songwriter ruben block starts deviating from the straight-on rock and that is actually good news as we get to hear different sides of the band all night long is an outright slow song with block's vocals heavily distorted the epic feed me closes off the first half of the album nicely the second half of the album starts with a blazing cherry check out in particular the intro there are several longer songs as well including the eight min slow-burner my baby's got a gun and the six min album closer it has not gone away which in and of itself sums up the album nicely.in all this is a very good album i might have left off the weakest song so as to get a slightly shorter and more concise running time but it is a minore quibble by reputation the band really shines in concert they released a live album in two thousand and seven faders up live and are about to release another live album live at high voltage later this fall i have not gotten the opportunity to see them live but i can only hope they will tour the us at some point as an aside triggerfinger is one of a core group of up-and-coming belgian bands worth checking out see in particular also the black box revelantion and customs
