text_review: office three hundred and sixty-five is microsoft's latest bright idea for how to get us to subscribe to the software we once bought for forty-nine a year you get office two thousand and thirteen on a pc or office two thousand and eleven on a mac plus more-robust versions of the tablet phone versions of office than you get for free you also get 1tb of space in microsoft's cloud and the ability to sync a doc from anywhere you edit it sort of like a keychain usb drive except no physical drive plus some skype minutes 1tb of space is nothing to sneeze at and paying an annual fee for drive space is industry standard practice.for me the installation on the pc went fine even though i had word two thousand and ten already i am happy with the features added in two thousand and thirteen over two thousand and ten particularly for excel the ipad version is about as good as you might expect and with office three hundred and sixty-five you get to edit docs from onedrive.so far so good but does it make sense to go for this version if you have lots of devices get office three hundred and sixty-five home which supports installs on five devices if you do not trust cloud storage and do not need onedrive and syncing search out the regular home and office or home and business versions one purchase price covers you forever or until hardware os incompatibilities end that dream.if at the end of my subscription year i have actually used onedrive a lot i will renew using my own money if i like the two thousand and thirteen version of office enough but do not use the cloud storage i will buy a permanent license for two thousand and thirteen ... assuming they still sell such a thing i hope they do at the retail level rental software benefits the vendor far more than the buyer

text_review: well after reading all the great reviews on these headpohones i decided to give them a try as i feared they are a gimmick these headphones have a vibrating thing that sits on the back of your neck while it is designed to simulate the heavy bass of a real home theater system it ended up making me shake my head both uncontrollably and because i feel like such a sucker for purchasing these things the shaking mechanism produces no actual sound of bass just a rythmic pulsing sounds cool it is not and to top it all off the headphones are rather uncomfortable i do not recommend these for long listening sessions but their bulky clumsy design makes them difficult to walk even a short distance with so sitting down seems to be the only venue for listening to be fair however these headphones produce some fairly decent sound midrange sound seems almost absent however and everyhing seems to have a slightly high pitch to it with the vmss bass system turned off the drivers still manage to produce some decent bass but not enough that i would justify the ... price tag and the so-so mid and high range sound is nothing to die for either and for the aesthetically-conscious teen like myself these headphones look absolutely horrid i do not think i would walk around with them unless i was in my grandmother's nursing home in short if you want to buy into a gimmicky product then go ahead and purchase the brain shaker extreme headphones but if you are like me and you want a pair of portable decent-sounding phones look elsewhere

text_review: at first impression ms office two thousand and seven appears to be much improved unfortunately i have not been able to fully evaluate it because of the time devoted to technical support initially i experienced errors that prevented the calendar and mail to display later it was only the mail and this happened sporatically i use ms hotmail as one of my mail accounts and this account would not appear from time to time and could not be displayed i found it necessary to restart office which sometimes worked and if not i would restart my computer naturally this is very frustrating when one has a lot of work to do then add the time on the phone with support sometimes over an hour and it is intolerable i truly began researching macs out of frustration and may yet be compelled to change os after numerous calls to support including a number of times when support was given free control to solve the problem the best that support could say was we will keep your issue open and i will do some research to find out what is causing the errors bottom line is that it was not resolved my fear has been that there are other issues lurking that i have not discovered and will not have free support when they appear support did say that as long as the current issue was not resolved i would have free support for that issue but what about the other parts of office seven i switched from palm to ms os when i purchased a treo if office seven is continues to be a problem i will be stuck with the phone and software note palm treo is available with palm desktop software as well as ms i am beginning get an appetite for fruit ... maybe an apple

text_review: any supremes fan should rush out and purchase this it has different takes with different leads on many of the songs and different arrangements on some it is three cd's of the mary scherrie susaye unfortuately motown aka berry gordy did not push support put the finances behind the supremes diana ross who i love has said that berry has gotten a bad rap but there are too many other artist who felt the same way that mary wilson felt such as gladys knight who left martha reeves who left eddie kendricks the four tops left the isley brothers who left bonnie pointer left was promised to be the next diana ross after even the diva left.now back to the supremes one thousand , nine hundred and seventy s article many of the songs could have been released others remixed for the disco era bend a litte give a little the harmony reminds one of en vogue can you imagine that and this was before en vogue you are what is missing in my life the final release has mary wilson and scherrie payne freda payne's sister sharing lead but in this special three cd release there are three different takes one with mary singing lead the second with scherrie singing lead and the third with both singing lead and all three are excellent no one outshines the other.there are many hidden surprises on this three cd release expensive but worth it

text_review: after opening the package i noticed the male end of the adapter only had one black band instead of two two bands are necessary for a stereo signal to produce sound for both sides of the headphone as a result it was obvious that it would only produce mono audio despite the product clearly being described as a stereo jack in the product description.even so the mono sound barely works as the female end is not a proper fit and as a result there will be either no sound or lots of static--very poor build quality.upon closer inspection the product does not even match the first two pictures of the product but looks almost identical to the third picture taken by tyler jones in which he also claims his adapter only produces a mono signal.avoid this product other info bought this from oem world and left a negative review for seller after receiving a bad product seller contacted me and offered refund new adapter i asked for a new adapter and removed my negative review months later i still never received the new adapter or any contact--should have left the negative review :/

text_review: my wife and i just bought a wii for christmas and we bought this game after seeing a lot of mixed reviews but were intrigued by the concept as of right now i am about halfway through and have been very pleased the storyline is unique and the game play is entertaining i think the pros well outweigh the cons a lot of the negative reviews have focused on the camera but i have played a lot of 3d games and epic mickey's camera is consistent with other 3d games pros great storyline and unique concept entertaining game play that offers a wide variety of options lots of quests and variations based on your decisions which result in a high replay value the different moral variations mean that you will want to play through the entire game more than once the paint and thinner concept is fun if not entirely original i e super mario sunshine cons camera can be frustrating but no more than would be experienced with any other 3d game aiming the paint and thinner brush can be tricky its also important to remember that even if you aim at something you can see from the camera viewpoint you are shooting from where mickey is standing for example if the camera is positioned high above mickey and you can see where you want to spray that does not mean the paint thinner will actually go where you are aiming because a wall or the ground may be impeding mickey's line of sight i have read some complaints about the dark theme of the game it does have a darker tone than one might expect from disney if you are looking for a cutesy kids game for someone under the age of ten you might want to avoid epic mickey

text_review: do not buy or use family tree maker twelve if you want a family tree that everyone can see looking forward to finding long-lost cousins and distant relatives do not they will only be able to see your tree if they buy memberships how about your family then they can see the tree--but only if you personally invite each and every one of them anyone whose address you do not know and future generations well tough luck to all of them they will just have to buy expensive memberships in ancestry.com.yes ancestry.com does believe that for a few bucks they earned by selling you their new software they own your family tree they bought out the family tree maker name so if you have the old software you can no longer use it to update your family tree instead you are forced to buy their new software which requires people to buy memberships there they sit raking in money by requiring paid access to the data that you put together.if that were not bad enough it is a buggy program that syncs with your computer do you know how dangerous that is instead use myheritage.com it is free and anyone can see it use your old family tree maker software to convert your ftw or ftm file to a gedcom file and you can use myheritage.com to import the ged file you created like the old family tree maker it is free and anyone can see it i am disgusted with ancestry.com today i am sending my software back and demanding a refund

text_review: rhythm games are not my sort of thing that is why i found myself surprised to be enjoying this game so much the main advantage that this game has over its competitors is a good story with gameplay features borrowed from professor layton and extremely catchy beats i found myself humming the tunes from this fairly shortly after playing it for the first time.the plot of the game is focused around a young frenchman called raphael who goes around by night disguised as the notorious phantom r an art thief of great style and sophistication the police are baffled at the ability of this young redheaded thief in a fashionable suit and fedora to disappear undoubtedly they asked the random redheaded civilian with glasses and no hat for information but he did not see anything it is that kind of game raphael is searching for his father who went missing years before during his pursuit he finds himself entwined in the risen emperor napoleon's dastardly plans to take over the world fortunately his men are susceptible to timed dance moves.sound ridiculous good it is meant to the plot is one of the most entertaining things about this game amusing and insane it takes our heroes on a tour of paris and its environs and paris is very much on display here the city looks gorgeous even in the 2d that dominates the gameplay when you do get to see a cinematic cutscene in glorious 3d no less it really sours.the rhythm games are cleverly based around this plot for example when sneaking into the louvre you have to follow a beat to hide behind convenient statues and avoid the guards when fighting napoleon's men you have to punch them as they bounce at you in synchronized fashion when eluding policemen on roller skates you have to jump or duck to avoid capture and my personal favorite you get to defend yourself against your archrival's pi child charlie who attempts to apprehend you by kicking a flaming football at your face they are all fun not a little bit silly and have a catchy beat.the parts of the game not revolving around playing rhythm games owe a very large debt to professor layton not so much the puzzle aspect but the way that you move your character along a map and use the touchscreen to interact with the characters and scenery on it they even have playcoins you can collect by tapping random areas of the screen the character and street designs are very nice these are seen at their full effect when the cutscenes start these cutscenes are beautifully animated and really capture a spirit of adventure i wish they would make this into an anime so we could see it all animated the 3d is used to good effect in these especially the first cutscene which has raphael dancing around a room filled with chandeliers the rest of the game does not use it much and it is often easier to just turn it off.most of this game takes place on the bottom screen the top screen has a map and is used for all the wonderful 3d cutscenes but when traveling you pay attention to the touchscreen in battles the top screen becomes important these battles alternate between having you tap buttons on the bottom screen with your stylus and hitting buttons no you do not have to do both at the same time that would be horrifyingly difficult.the downsides to the game are fairly minor but annoying the rating system is messed up the game does not record your best scores only an average of all your scores this means that if you want the game to save you getting an a-rank score you have to get it right on your first time which is almost impossible another flaw is the grading system for these ranks it is too heavily focused on what your last move was you can get a perfect score right up until the end and then flub only the last note dropping you down to a c-rank it is very irritating.if any of this sounds compelling try the demo it is available for free on the nintendo store this is one fun game even for non rhythm game fans while the game does not always add up to the sum of its parts nevertheless it provides a fun ride.do store this is one fun game even for non rhythm game fans while the game does not always add up to the sum of its parts nevertheless it provides a fun ride

text_review: the changlings produce a form of music that is both modern and medieval it unites a traditional celtic style with modern instruments a middle eastern flair and a deep dark gothic mood the vocals are clear and beautiful ranging from ethereal to haunting the musical backing is very full and complex with every part precisely orchestrated and executed while still producing a freely organic sound it does not just compliment the vocals but seems merges with regeana's voice to form a sound greater than the sum of its parts if you have heard the original changlings cd the only one still available this cd will be familiar but with a much darker undertone the music and vocals are still haunting and will linger in your consciousness long after the music stops i would not consider any of it spooky rather than approaching the mystical unknown it immerses the listener in the dark murky depths of the human experience the album seems to follow only incidentally the theme of a space voyage as though it was only an afterthought individually each song is very strong collectively they are less impressive than they would be without trying to follow the space theme none the less it is definitely a top notch work of art this cd ranks near the top of my list of favorites along with cd's from aenima mirabilis and mercurine

text_review: this review is going to be much like my review of the two thousand and nine edition of norton three hundred and sixty because except for the removal of the backup features the two programs are quite alike for the same reason i am not going to be so nice to symantec the makers of norton three hundred and sixty and norton internet security this time around i want to be clear that i am only referring to the windows xp version in this review i may post another one for windows seven users once my new system arrives.the main problem is this you absolutely cannot trust the firewall to work correctly on your system as configured as it is too permissive this means you run the risk of losing valuable personal information and or damaging your computer in the default set it and forget it mode it has continued to fail in almost every firewall test i have thrown at it as it does a horrible job of detecting and blocking potential threats on its own even a free firewall program provided by comodo performs better than norton internet security.the only way to make the firewall safe is to do the following steps one open the norton internet security homepage by doubleclicking on the icon in the system tray two in the box named network click on settings three scroll down to smart firewall click configure next to advanced settings four turn automatic program control off and advanced events monitoring on5 you will get a warning that it is for advanced users congratulations that is what you will become soon six hit apply to accept if your settings are correct it should match the image i uploaded to amazon.from this point forward it will start to ask you before you start a program or access the internet much like the previously referenced comodo firewall it will seem annoying at first however the interruptions will become less frequent as it learns the programs that you have designated as safe you may not recognize each individual file but you can make educated guesses for instance if the file is located in the directory of the program you just started up it is a high probability the file is legitimate because norton has started including file directories in its popup alerts it becomes much easier to locate files you are unsure of from there you can check the properties of the file to make sure they match the program's vendor microsoft or otherwise it just depends on how accepting you want to be after a while the interruptions will become infrequent unless you install something new or more importantly something uninvited is trying to access the internet without your permission it is not a foolproof method by any means but it is much safer than the norton three hundred and sixty and is two thousand and ten default which seems to be to allow anything you run to access the internet and or your computer as long as you perform these steps the firewall performs quite well.fortunately i can say that the antivirus works much better it even identified and quarantined a few of my firewall leaktests before i was able to run them no virus protector is one hundred safe however so the best way to protect your computer is still to practice safe surfing when i deliberately tried to run some questionable files one of them managed to make my computer unbootable and norton never stopped it the same thing happened to norton three hundred and sixty this brings me to another issue i sent that file to symantec months ago with specific details about what it does yet even now norton does not catch it i am starting to wonder how much they are paying attention to the files we send them maybe they are being overrun by the number of people submitting iexplore.exe as a potential virus.the database is still a mess of unnecessary messages that are service related rather than virus related there does seem to be some realization of this so this years version is a little less confusing with links to the database regarding particular issues youmay click on cosmetically norton has changed to yellow over black instead of black over yellow there is a nice buried feature called optimize to get there you need to flip the main menu to the performance history and click a tiny link of the same name not sure why it is tucked away but for this aging system i did notice some improvement in startup times symantec will honor the remaining days of a subscription to a former product and add them to this year's product but you will have to contact them it will also transfer your settings and identity cards and passwords however it will not use your identity card information on new websites per support you need to delete them in spite of the import and start over i also find it takes much longer to login than it did using norton three hundred and sixty almost a 10-15 second wait not sure if that was due to the import or a problem with the program.norton internet security two thousand and ten says on the box that it supports pop three and smtp now for its email scanner that would cover almost every email scanner on the market in symantec's world however that only means outlook and outlook express according to a support guy named kumar he says that in spite of the many popular email programs on the market norton continues to support only outlook and outlook express but he could not really explain why symantec appears to be flat out lying maybe he was stoned i will ask harold next time.one new feature that does not impress me are the constant popups saying i am the first person to run this program or that quite odd considering i get these warnings even after downloading a file from the symantec website you can remove this annoyance by clicking web settings then turning off download insight you have to turn it off completely otherwise it will simply delete any file it considers a risk one of these days symantec will realize we do not like it when they do that.in short this version of norton is not much of an improvement over last year's version and there were a ton of areas where they could have made improvements.lack instead of black over yellow there is a nice buried feature called optimize to get there you need to flip the main menu to the performance history and click a tiny link of the same name not sure why it is tucked away but for this aging system i did notice some improvement in startup times symantec will honor the remaining days of a subscription to a former product and add them to this year's product but you will have to contact them it will also transfer your settings and identity cards and passwords however it will not use your identity card information on new websites per support you need to delete them in spite of the import and start over i also find it takes much longer to login than it did using norton three hundred and sixty almost a 10-15 second wait not sure if that was due to the import or a problem with the program norton internet security two thousand and ten says on the box that it supports pop three and smtp now for its email scanner that would cover almost every email scanner on the market in symantec's world however that only means outlook and outlook express according to a support guy named kumar he says that in spite of the many popular email programs on the market norton continues to support only outlook and outlook express but he could not really explain why symantec appears to be flat out lying maybe he was stoned i will ask harold next time one new feature that does not impress me are the constant popups saying i am the first person to run this program or that quite odd considering i get these warnings even after downloading a file from the symantec website you can remove this annoyance by clicking web settings then turning off download insight you have to turn it off completely otherwise it will simply delete any file it considers a risk one of these days symantec will realize we do not like it when they do that in short this version of norton is not much of an improvement over last year's version and there were a ton of areas where they could have made improvements

text_review: as of this writing rome two is well over a year old and the digital download on amazon is being offered for sixty i managed to snatch it for fifteen during a holiday sale and even then i am still disappointed with this game.the good looks very pretty it actually runs well an issue this game had at launch steamworks community.the bad very simplified and boring game mechanics compared to its predecessors and especially compared to other games in the genre predictable and unengaging ai battles though pretty are still very fast you will spend more time in empire management again a concept other games do better limited multiplayer population it takes forever to find a game still prone to performance issues and graphical glitches unsatisfactory dlc experience be prepared to shell out cash for additional repetitive campaigns reskinned official factions and the privilege of portraying blood in a war game.rome two was plagued with issues at launch that is documented this is the revamped emperor edition it optimizes game performance fixes the majority of bugs and provides an additional imperator augustus campaign the latter can basically be viewed as a save point where you can take command of a large and already established roman faction at a later point in history.if you have never played a total war game before and are very interested in the setting do yourself a favor and wait for a sale and do us all a favor and avoid pre-ordering attila for that matter do not expect historical accuracy here history buffs

text_review: my new dell eight thousand , two hundred desktop came pre-installed with xp and after using it for a half a month it has been very very stable and the look of the operating system is really great the os can be in your face at times but you can change the way everything looks and make many things nonexistent so you never see them the os starts really fast and i have not seen the dreaded blue screen at all also my application opening times have much faster than with windows ninety-eight or windows me.after getting the feel of the os i decided to upgrade my dell laptop which was running windows me the upgrade went very very smooth and i did not have any trouble during the install after having the new os on my laptop just for a few days i have not seen the constant windows me crash and my laptop starts faster my applications run quicker and my computer looks really cool with xp on it the only draw back that i have noticed with xp on my laptop is that it really uses a lot more memory usage than windows me if you have only 64mb on your laptop which is what i have i would suggest upgrading your memory before or after you upgrade in conclusion i would really suggest buying windows xp because it really is microsoft's best home version of windows yet and it is a really solid product

text_review: i had a wonderful pair of sony earbuds before which were similar to these but unfortunately my cat chewed them completely apart ... those were the best i would owned and i wish i still had them or knew where to find them regardless i had to find a replacement and so invested in the most similar pair of earbuds i could find in the hook style but i tried philips those were god-awful and the left earbud burned out after a short while.so this was my next option once i found it from my past experience and my father's headphones which are sony incredibly ancient and working like a charm i figured i could not go wrong.the cord comes with an extender that is incredibly long i absolutely loved that unfortunately on a road trip no less i had a scare where these earbuds were dying on me too you know where you will need to turn the jack in your ipod in order for the sound to come through properly not good turns out the problem was the extender once i deatched that the earbuds worked fine and have been working fine ever since my issue is that the cord is now unusually short but i suppose that has its benefits and i have learned to live with it.now sound quality i have no idea how to judge earbuds on sound quality so i had to experiment until i found a kind that was decent these are excellent if you try earbuds like these you will never go back to the kind that comes with the ipod i will save you time and tell you now to not bother with earbuds that do not cushion inside your ear unless you absolutely cannot stand that feeling even then i suggest you learn to get used to it because it will change your listening experience for the better the noise cancellation is stellar as well which this style is famous for a little fyi my ipod nano at half the max volume is my standard volume during school it is loud enough that i cannot hear a thing around me but the music but quiet enough that no one else can hear a peep from my music even in complete silence.if you text_review: went to best buy to buy a new wiimote yesterday and saw this game i bought both came back and install it on my dell dimension nine thousand , two hundred which is about as pre-built as you can get right no vista driver problems for me right wrong two two giraffes wrong first i had to tell my antivirus and spyware software about a billion times to let secure-rom install second i installed it and rebooted third my dvd drive no longer works i am not sure what changed between bioshock and this game cause i bought bioshock and had no problem with secure-rom back then i bought bioshock full price and do not regret a single cent because i actually got to play bioshock i finished bioshock without even cracking it although i eventually did for a second play-through cause who wants to find the dvd everytime right review updated funny thing i never did install dead space again on my system i just cannot risk having securerom on it again since i actually do tons of work on it so here is a review of a cracked version of the game as opposed to the boxed copy which now sits next to other games i do not play anymore poor hl2 i think ea should have an option when you insert the disk that lets you chose between installing their drm version or downloading a cracked one i am joking but i totally am not the game runs nicely on my dell dimension nine thousand , two hundred which ran bioshock and cod four on high just fine if you compare it to pc exclusive titles you can tell the textures in this game is low quality nevertheless it has a nice polished look the controls are fine i tried it with my xbox three hundred and sixty control but just cannot bring myself to play any kind of fps without keyboard mouse the game forces the mouse turn rate so your character cannot magically turn one hundred and eighty degrees in half a second this did not bother me and i actually think it is a nice way to add some realism into the controls the overall experience is effective and addictive if not for the reasonthe developer stated they said it was mostly about psychological fear with help from shadows and music the game is actually mostly about enemies popping out or dropping down from ceilings they said it is about strategic dismemberment it is strategic the first five times by then it is more like habitual dismemberment shoot limbs for maximum damage does not require more iq than boom headshot nevertheless the game just flows very well and lots of little things are put into it to keep you in the game world ninety-nine of the time it is obvious the developers put a lot of thought into the interface and controls it is something new to the genre that future games can learn from so now having played the game i plan on replaying it on easy so i can just wack the enemies to death and then on hard to give myself more of a rush i think it is worth the money however a big part of the reason i think that is cause i played a cracked copy put together by the pirates which installed the game and not secure rom so i am very conflicted about the whole thing i definitely do not want any more secure rom nonsense but at the same time i am happy i bought the game to support more games like this on my pc i guess i will continue to buy games with secure rom if it is good enough like this one or bioshock but i will still be playing the vastly superior pirated copy instead everybody wins i guess at least everybody who is honest enough to buy the game and then smart enough to download a cracked copy too :/

text_review: first off this phone case is extra slippery i was willing to deal with that since i loved the way it looked when i first bought it the pieces fit together perfectly i had no issues with the gold piece slipping off like i have seen in other reviews it is a bit bulky but i figured that as long as it was protecting my phone i did not care.secondly the recessed buttons take some getting used to i absolutely hated it at first but eventually i was used to it.thirdly when using flash for the camera the case is thick enough that it affects this and gets in the way it is an issue i have had with other phone cases that are too thick that when you take a photo with flash the pic comes out messed up because the case is getting in the way and gives the picture this white layer this minor problem was not a huge deal to me since i rarely use flash for my pictures anyway fourth and what made me annoyed enough to post a review is that the plastic on the left side where the volume buttons are is very thin and fragile i am careful with my phone but the plastic piece on the side somehow broke off and i have only had this case for a couple of months it is a pretty case but i was expecting it to be pretty and more durable since it is not coming from a random completely-unknown cell phone case manufacturer it is disappointing that this case could not last i would not recommend a spigen case especially since i know of other people who bought other models for iphone six phones that broke as well

text_review: though the learning curve felt a little steep at first it turned out that it was not so bad and now lightroom two has totally changed our workflow for the better previously my wife and i would keep all our photos in dated folders and simply keep groups of edits in finished folders but this always felt kind of clunky and keeping up with and finding particular sooc or finished images could be confusing especially when creating multiple versions of photos it did not take long to learn how to take advantage of lightroom's organizational tools to better keep track of everything and i particularly love the virtual copy feature that allows you to create and easily manage multiple versions all while taking significantly less space than creating real copies of the files we are still learning all the editing capabilities we have not taken the plunge into photoshop cs yet but we are photoshop elements users most of what we used to do in elements is now easier in lightroom it used to take so long to open every photo in elements and make necessary improvements but now we can easily apply certain changes to large groups quickly or even go through one at a time far more quickly than before and for any of the few changes that must be done in elements which so far has just been healing-brush-type work it is just a couple of clicks away to create a virtual copy and open it in elements i think what is both the most daunting and impressive about lightroom is the flexibility there is a huge number of organizational tools provided and there is no one way to organize your photos and your workflow with them especially when you integrate it with other tools this felt a bit overwhelming at first but as you learn about what is available you can really start to develop and tailor your own workflow to fit your preferences and needs there are a few small drawbacks i have had the application crash a few times and some operations are pretty slow particularlyexporting a large number of edited photos which is the main downside to the nondestructive editing scheme however it is getting about time for a new computer so hopefully a newer faster machine will improve the stability and speed

text_review: and really first ice run of my life we got four inches of snow then an hour of thirty-four degree light rain then an immediate drop to twenty degrees everything froze solid an inch of ice covered every surface around this is in south korea for reference i was excited for my first frozen run with my icebugs bought them two weeks ago because i knew this was coming three miles including a four hundred foot high hill that had a nearly half mile downslope that was frozen and poorly lit at five am ice covering eighty-five of everything the few road intersections where it had been heavily salted made up the rest asphalt and nary a slip was had surefooted even confidence inspiring the only part that was treacherous were the solid ice balls up to four in diameter strewn through my poorly lit path stepped on a few of those and tweaked my ankles slightly but even with the reactions to those the pytho 2s never so much as skidded and they handled the asphalt with aplomb just the weird sound of the studs clacking they sounded like suckers on glass being removed quickly or bubble wrap being popped either way great buy the only downside was the insoles which seem thin and really kind of weak i pulled out my brooks ghost insoles and put them in instead perfect fit and they are exceptionally comfortable five stars all around love these things oh and they are water resistant have yet to get so much as damp on me and i have run them through slush and puddles too and look pretty cool on top of it love these shoes

text_review: i am a huge nikon fan and already own the d70 which is great however i noticed that during the times when i just wanted to snap a quick picture the d70 definitely was not the camera to do it with while it is a phenomenal camera when it comes to really customizing your pictures i do not know if i have ever had a really great picture come out while using it on auto indoors with the flash on my pictures were all washed out with the flash off everything had a red hue i bought a little point-and-shoot hoping to remedy the problem but it was not much better of course the first time i heard of the d40 it was in a nikon commercial talking about giving them to a town ... i visited the website and thought ha yeah right a couple months passed never really thought about it much .. until the other day when i was in best buy and decided to browse the camera section there was the d40 ready and waiting for me to get my hands on it i took a few practice shots in the store and was amazed that the photos actually looked good no washed out look from the flash or red pictures like i would get from the d70 when it was on auto i spent about five days arguing with myself over whether i should spend the five hundred on a camera i practically already had before i went out and bought it the d40 is tiny compared to the size of my d70 and the weight difference is pretty incredible too while it is not a compact point-and-shoot it is not nearly as hefty as most of the dslr's out there all of the practice shots i have taken around my house have looked fantastic even the shot of the pudding snack pack on my desk ;) the only negative thing i have to say about it is that i was hoping the batteries and memory cards would be interchangeable between the forty and the seventy but they are not the batteries are different and the d40 takes an sd card while the seventy takes a compactflash card other than that i am more than pleased with the nikon d40 if you are looking for an incredible camera that can be used as your everyday point-and-shoot yet still give you that optional control over your photos get this one sure it is a little pricey but it is worth every cent

text_review: i will say up front that for me this is a high-priced item i am not an audiophile i just want good sound that will fill the room both for tv watching and listening to music after reading reviews i decided to pickup this speaker for use in my finished basement for a few reasons first i have brick walls so running a bunch of speaker wire is not easy and will not look great and second because we do a lot of entertaining in that space and having bluetooth capability makes it easy to play and control music this speaker fits that criteria and i am very pleased with how well it performs.out of the box i was surprised by how solidly built it is i had read the specifications but i have to say i was surprised by the weight it just feels like a quality unit my intent was not to use it as a portable device so it is weight and size does not bother me.from the other comments common concerns with this speaker and probably all single units this size seem to be stereo separation and bass i did not expect amazing stereo separation from a single unit but sitting in front of my tv where this speaker faces i am really impressed at how this nearly does the job of the two bookshelf speakers it replaced which were spaced four apart i have no complaints as far as that is concerned as bass goes i am equally impressed by the lows this puts out very happy about that.for design the thing just looks great i assumed it would look nice but sitting on the shelf it really stands out it goes perfect with our decor and has both a modern and classic feel so i would not hesitate putting it in any room i will take performance first but it is a bonus that it is so attractive to look at.as someone else mentioned the inactivity power off is a bit of a double-edged sword for me truthfully i would like this to happen when i leave the room and forget to power it off and i am glad it does work that way but it would be great if i could auto-activate it back up when using my computer or phone not a huge deal more laziness on my part.overall i am incredibly happy with this unit it is perfect for my need.vate it back up when using my computer or phone not a huge deal more laziness on my part.overall i am incredibly happy with this unit it is perfect for my need

text_review: okay so the heavy metal cartoon has not aged well the soundtrack fares a lot better once you get past the fact that aside from a few tunes such as sabbath's mob rules there is not a whole lot of heavy metal music here instead most of the songs on the cd are better thought of as late 1970s fm rock songs this is the type of music aor used to play before it mutated into classic rock and stopped playing anything recorded after one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-three all of the songs here are vaguely trippy hard rock some with fusion aspirations and some trying out for progressive it is fitting music because the original heavy metal magazine was full of post one thousand , nine hundred and seventy psychedelic artwork strong points include journey's best ballad open arms blue oyster cult's veteran of the psychic wars a couple of former eagle don felder songs and cheap trick's reach out the heavier side is represented by sammy hagar sabbath and grand funk railroad i have no idea how devo got in here and i wish they did not for the most part however this is a very solid cd music like this was swept aside by punk on the one hand and mtv on the other at least until trip hop managed to sneak some of the laid-back grooviness in through the back door

text_review: we upgraded to enterprise edition thirteen the other night and it went very smoothly we downloaded the new software put it on the server and then did our five workstations not a hitch we used the connection diagnostic tool to open the correct ports in firewalls etc.my comments about the new version i hope intuit is reading this ): one graphics are not nearly as pleasing as the old version yuck to the black background two we have two checking accounts and had it set up to show one account's checks in blue the other in yellow we then order checks in those colors hopefully the color coding keeps us from writing a check on one account with checks from the other the new program puts a little bitty colored border around a cross hatched check pattern a mistake can more easily be made why would you take away such a great little feature three contact fields used to be just one big field so we would put in for instance accounts payable john smith the system is taking this information and putting the first word as the first name etc to give us a record showing first name of accounts middle name payab only allows five characters and last name of john that makes for some screwy invoices four invoices are nicest with the invoice number on the upper right now it is in the middle of the invoice that is harder to use.so kudos to the techies that made the upgrade smooth i know that is a difficult thing to do less happy with the graphics types

text_review: after doing extensive research i too came across the viper five thousand , nine hundred and one just like many of you are looking to do now a couple pointers best buy is prob one of the only places that will install a product like this most smaller establishments do not want to mess with something and be liable for something you did not buy from them buying this online is the best way to go but be forewarned first my particular product from sigmaenterprieses came intact but upon installation was discovered either the remotes or alarm module was non functioning this one troubleshooted by swapping the module with one from the shelf the installer noted that there should be a quality control white sticker that covers the opening of the box if yours does not we weary second if you have a newer car say circa two thousand and seven and on then be on the look out for added component costs i had to consider a flcan module that does not come included in this package and is set for a range of models of cars oh and btw all the name brand companies of alarms and modules are all produced by mainly one company directed electronics the module allows the alarm to talk with your car's computer that controls all functionality of door locks windows basically anything electronic third key chip the newer cars including this guy's two thousand and eleven subaru have encoded keys since the idea of auto start is to trick the car's computer into believing a key's in there its much more difficult with these types more than likely you will have to purchase a 556uw this module allows you to place a key in it and wrap it with some type of wire that is able to read the chip inside your key which in turn sends a signal to the flcan just the installation alone with these parts can cost you upwards of four hundred i am in the middle of having the non-functioning components replaced either through sigma or some other way and will post a further of the product when this mission is accomplished

text_review: if you are reading the comments on this product i am betting you are already an owner and you have returned here to hopefully bask in some glowing reviews if this is you let me say that i really like you and want to be your friend you clearly have a lot of expendable income and a willingness to part with it in the total absence of reason.if however you are still using generic cat six cable that is widely available for even passive lust for this product probably means you have a fundamental lack of understanding of how packet data standards like usb and ethernet work years of reading how high end analog cables revealed the previously-obscured aural treasures has left you thinking that any cable must have some bearing on sound but you see ethernet is different there are frames preambles error correction stop-bits encoding buffering and lots of other stuff in there this is to say nothing of the fact that it is all carried over four twisted pairs in a five-level pulse amplitude modulation that is light-years removed from your precious digital audio signal it is beyond measurements or double-blind listening tests audible differences are simply not possible and they know this.the five star review reflects my absolute awe of the marketing department at audioquest you guys saw an opportunity and you took it there are many technology companies that should take a note not only did you invent a high-end ethernet cable you created an entire line of them with somehow tiered performance brilliant

text_review: daft punk is one of my all time favorites their four singles and video series for them were genius and amazing but three stars was probably generous for this cd because it disappointed me a little i am still confused about whether they are treating this as a new album since it was so marketed in the us unlike alive one thousand , nine hundred and ninety-seven if they are it was a dissapointment if it was meant to be a bunch of extended clublike versions of their previous songs then it is alright dont get me wrong the only new songs on the album ouverture and aerodynamite are great and distinct style like discovery daft punk but the club mixes and experimental songs i could do without parts of the club mixes are great but they repeat and run on like an average techno song something i have never known daft punk for the american influence is clear on this album too with the presence of rap on the neptunes remix and slum village both songs are terrible and i try to forget that aerodynamic was destroyed and rap put over it i also have to mention that the romanthony version of one more time is possibly the worst song i ever heard and i am quite surprised its even on the cd with how bad the singing is artists change but this wasnt change it just kinda seemed like they were trying to get you to spend money to top it off i thought i would finally have access to their website only people who buy their cds can go there and when i loaded the cd it took me to a webpage advertising their interstella five hundred and fifty-five figurines forcing me to sign up for some advertising scheme for it kinda disappointed but im trying to tell myself this was just to hold us over for now

text_review: the teares of the muses the new york university collegium viol consort directed by margaret panofsky with kathleen cantrell and campbell rightmyer sopranos and morwaread farbood organ has just released its cd ein lammlein 17th century german passion music the cd is both very well constructed and very moving in meditations on the death of christ and its significance the viol consort margaret panofsky and caroline marris treble david fenton tenor jeremy brandt-young bass christina brandt-young continuo bass has been in residency at st michael's episcopal church in new york city since two thousand and seven members include both nyu faculty and students and nyu community viol players the central work on the cd ein lammlein geht und tragt die schuld is a lament in five sections on christ's death written by samuel capricornus 1628-1665 for two sopranos viol consort and continuo the opening work o traurigkeit o herzeleid for the same combination is also by capricornus the two pieces were published in one thousand , six hundred and sixty in a volume titled zwey lieder von dem leyden und tode jesu two songs on the suffering and death of jesus the works of capricornus are not well known although according to the article in new grove they are deserving of more study and performance like schutz who praised his work and tunder capricornus often chose to employ the viol consort with his vocal textures he is known to have written theatre music now lost however his gift for expressive detail is evident in the two works presented here the two texts are by different poets the first o traurigkeit was written by friedrich spee von langenfeld 1591-1635 a jesuit priest ein lammlein is by paul gerhardt poet and hymn writer the texts share an exclamatory quality setting off emotional gestures oh great woe oh sweet mouth oh wonder o traurigkeit has a simple structure of eight five-line stanzas with consistent rhyme and meter the opening sinfonia is repeated after the fourth stanza capricornus does not linger over the text after an opening duet each voice has a solo verse delivered almost conversationally in spite of the solemnity of the subject the sorrow of christ's death and the sins of mankind in verse five there is a striking harmonic crunch on the word mourn beklagen ); in verse seven the viol consort is brought in making brief exclamatory exhalations as the body is lowered into the grave with gentle triplets from the singers ein lammlein a longer work has greater variety a basic ten line stanza is established and then disturbed in the first two sections the opening section the longest contains a bit of dramatic action god asks jesus to go forth and bear the sins of his children and christ responds that he is willing to carry the load the second verse o wunderlieb o liebesmacht marvels at christ's sacrifice the two stanzas are shorter the viols again repeat their introductory sinfonia between the two verses and then play in the second verse highlighting the falling gestures of the voices at the pouring forth of the lamb's noble blood the final three sections are a personal response to the sacrifice and love that the crucifixion represents the speaker desires to keep christ as a friend to relinquish the gold of arabia and its spices to be nourished and guided by christ and finally at death to be placed at his side the beautifully bejeweled bride is splendidly bedecked by the full consort of viols these two works each full of interest easily stand by themselves however the cd is enhanced still further with works for viol consort one also with voice by a variety of contemporaneous german composers between each section of the vocal music after the final chord of o traurigkeit the viols enter with a chord of almost identical sonority thus beginning schein's suite no one from banchetto musicale the ensuing instrumental texture viols out from under wraps is further enlivened withornaments on the repeat--trills starting on the note graceful turns and connecting passagi carefully considered and placed are evident throughout the recording and suggestive of a distinctly germanic style after the dialogue between god and jesus the intrad and lamento by david funck provide a brief but likewise dramatic interlude with fast-slow stop-start motion suitably exclamatory the third interlude transcribed from scheidt's organ chorale and variation no five da jesus an dem kreuze stund prepares by its use of chromaticism the fourth interlude tunder's exquisite an wasserflussen babylon the opening phrases of the five viols establish a rich tonal world which the singer enters with another different lament the hanging of the harps on the willow trees the final interlude a small gem from the st matthew passion by johann sebastiani 1622-1683 o welt ich muss dich lassen oh world i must leave you borrows its melody from another famous song of leavetaking innsbruck ich muss dich lassen from the first the singers captivate with expressive open wonderfully blended sound the themes of the recording are complex and interesting and these singers make repeated listening a real pleasure the continuo team is also very fine the bass viol is consistently attentive to the gestures of the music the viol consort functions impressively as a single entity coordinated at repeats and moments of heightened emotion yet each individual voice is clear the liner notes by margaret panofsky are thorough and provide a springboard for further research texts and translations are well laid out and easy to follow although passion music is associated with a specific time of the year the uplifting quality of the music and performance on this cd belongs to a timeless season

text_review: i had a couple of older model canon elph's and wanted to upgrade thinking new had to be better this camera just did not live up to expectations or what was promised by canon first and foremost i got a lot of odd looking colors in my shots some looked fine but others looked cartoonish i was using the complete auto mode so it is not like i had the wrong settings picked i mean i would hand the camera to a friend they would look at the screen and say why does she look like a cartoon in this one just not natural and not appealing i also experienced autofocus issues where more shots were blurry than with my previous elph the lack of sharpness was a big issue on most prints just too soft and fuzzy i agree with taking fourteen megapixels and going down to ten to make the photos easier to handle and store but not when it affects picture quality to this degree maybe twelve was a safer number still ten megapixels and you cannot get a nice sharp 4x6 print out of it that just should not be happening as far as video goes i also had a focus issue at times with a moving object my son was running around the backyard catching lightning bugs and i lost the focus a number of times and had to move the camera around to jar it back into clarity all in all i would pass on this one

text_review: well i have to say that if you are considering a an online rpg then ac is one of the better ones if not the best however there is one very important factor which has forced myself and quite a few other to leave the game the problem was not with the game itself it is as addictive as they come but instead lay with the technical side of the game the first big problem was with the game server downtime ac goes down regualarly for three hours each day this time is as you would guess during the off-peak hours of the day which is great if you live in the us however for international players guess again this was not the problem which caused me to cancel my membership however it was after i switched from a telephone connection to a cable tv connection that i became locked out of the server i spent a good four weeks trying to get any kind of technical support from ac and microsoft my search for help included four chat rooms and over twenty letters sent to two support email addresses i never once met a systems operator who did not reffer me elsewhere nor did i ever get a single reply to the e-mails i sent the bottom line is microsoft will not be able to help you if you have problems they will send you to a seperate ac support center the ac support center exsists but will unfortunately ignore you so if you have worries about system compatibility or a non-telephone internet connection especially through a cable tv line it might be safer to go with everquest or ultima i would have liked to be able to have words with the support team about this but alas could not find one

text_review: apple needs competition as it stands without any real competition apple will continue to practice their dirty business techniques and hold back features that consumers want need in their products knowing that people will buy them anyway then offer those features next year as new upgrades what am i talking about the camera taking 0.7 megapixel still shots for starters this is absolutely unacceptable for two thousand and ten i know that the ipod's camera is not meant to be a replacement for your digital camera but at 0.7 megapixels it is pretty pointless if you ask me i think they just took the old cameras out of the older ipod nano's and used them the more i think of it the camera upgrades in the new ipod touch are the cameras that should have been introduced last year in the 3rd generation ipod touch there is no reason why apple could not have put in the same five megapixel camera w led flash as they did in the iphone four the only reason they did not to save this feature for next years upgrade oh yeah perhaps because they chose to make the ipod touch 0.07 slimmer than before too because everyone was complaining about how thick the ipod touch was right i am sure if apple would have introduced the new ipod touch 4th generation as being as thick as say the iphone four with the better camera fitting inside nobody would have been complaining that it is too thick second enough of the glossy metal backs apple we are tired of the scratch prone backs it is getting old sure there are tons of cases out there but again if you would have made the new ipod touch follow the design of the new iphone four we would not need to worry about that highly scratch prone backside of course come next years ipod touch update refresh we will see this new design being implemented you will see hear apple say ... we have a brand new design .. completely changing it is looks .. etc next issue why still offer the 8gb 32gb 64gb models that is three straight years now oh yeah because apple does not have any real competition in the ipod market to rival this so they just keep it here until they have to upgrade it to 32gb 64gb 128gb pricing for flash memory of these sizes would not have significantly increase apples costs they could have done it if they wanted to but did not way to think first for your mass amount of consumers apple of course the new ipod touch does have some good new additions that are welcoming thus the reason for two stars not just one upgraded to the new retina display nice touch no complaints there the cheap little front camera for face time again cool nice touch however this is just as beneficial to apple as it is to the consumers apple would love for consumers to use their video chat face time and get more and more people using their products to be able to communicate with their peers think about it iphone four users using face time with ipod touch users and soon the ipad two will have cameras thus face time with those users .. and by then i am sure apple will allow face time to work with their laptops imacs too how perfect for apple .. all of their products will offer face time it is an old strategy but it will work it will sucker users into their little game even though ichat has been around the typical consumer is brainwashed by apples buzzwords and marketing tactics finally and i am almost ashamed to admit this this review is coming from an apple user fan i love apple i love their products but i do not like the little game they play with consumers holding back features now just to introduce them later for their next generations this is dirty business but without any real competition it is what they can afford to do knowing that people will buy their products anyway i for one have held back for years buying an ipod touch first it was because they were not offering enough storage then because there was not a camera now well there is sort of a camera but still it is just not offering all that it should i do not will not buy any product or service that lacks features i want that is the power of being the consumer and trust me i will not cave when i feel that the ipod touch offers all the features i want if i still see value in that product i will buy perhaps next year perhaps but i am sure they will do some similar type of holding back on a feature it would not surprise me time will tell of course if consumers exercised their powers chose not to buy into apple's little game it would force apple to make offer better products for their consumers but that is just asking for way too much from the average consumer they will buy just about anything apple offers and then re-buy it the next year .. and then the next year .. etc sad

text_review: for starters the toy's display in the box is impressive i would say adrenaline pumping the oversized shark and basic ship design scream open me first at least that is how my almost seven year-old approached it it took about five minutes to fully liberate the toy from its package so you will want to come prepared with scissors or a clipping tool the mega rig pieces are quick connect and easy to take apart and reassemble the almost seven year-old had no problems with assembly and could do everything on his own i needed to consult the instructions to see how the harpoon and crane went together the four 1/2 year-old needed a little help with some of the attachments gets frustrated keeping up with older brother the shark ship comes with several action pieces like the harpoon crane and shark cage along with two characters captain and diver so it is good for imaginative play the happy hum of kids creating their own shark capture stories is music to a busy mother's ears the shark has a moveable jaw so he can swallow objects which are retrieved through a slit in its belly high cool factor for my boys the shark's fins and tail are soft and bendable making them look sharp but not be a safety hazard there are so many combinations the possibilities seem endless there are enough pieces for siblings to share with less quarreling than with a single toy it is a toy my kids come back to play with again and again they even work it into their adventures with lego minifigures and other toys we have not tried--and probably will not try--this toy in water but on land it is excellent

text_review: several years ago i picked up a used copy of this at videogame store and i was surprised by how much i enjoyed it to tell the truth i would never even seen most of the wrestlers on the game but i still thought it was very cool the wrestlers did and do look kind of cartoonish but i did not and do not care about that the game is a bit slow but that did not really bother me either i played it a lot the part of the game that i enjoyed most was the create-a-legend mode this was the first wrestling game that i would played where you could actually assign your created wrestlers all of their own moves as opposed to having to give them move-sets of existing wrestlers like you had to on another wrestling game or two that i would played before this one i thought it was fun to play as my wrestlers and open up new moves that i could give them i have got created wrestlers on two three memory cards the maximum number you can have on each of them i also enjoyed playing the referee and watching the computer wrestle i only ever opened like one or two of the locked wrestlers and thus never finished the career mode but i never cared that much this game does not seem to be very loved at least not by reviewers at this site but i thought it was one of the best wrestling games i would ever played in fact i still think it is one of the best i have ever played even though i have not actually played it in quite a while now i thought it was about time this game got another good review and a little more love

text_review: performance excellent good to know that this stick uses sanwa parts a common gripe with madcatz in the past was that their products did not perform well and or hold up well alleviate your fears this stick holds up well when put to the test and it performs with the precision of being at the arcade.value at one hundred and fifty this is not cheap for gamers however if you are even remotely serious about fighting games then the one hundred and fifty price tag is well worth it consider how many quality fighters have come out and are scheduled to come out this generation street fighter iv kofxiii soul calibur five street fighter x tekken blazblue continuum shift extend etc plus i also use this stick for playing retro games on psn xbl you know old school games like double dragon r-type etc it is great as a throwback to when i actually stood at an arcade cabinet in the late early ninety s and played these games.hesitant about the purchase my advice is to give it a shot worst case scenario is that you do not use it as often as you though ... which in that case you can put it up on ebay and get most of your money back i used a te fightstick for my xbox three hundred and sixty for about two years until i sold my three hundred and sixty i got one hundred and thirty for my used te fightstick on ebay i just purchased another te fightstick for my ps3 now and have zero concerns with anything regarding the purchase go for it

text_review: after around one month of using this bag extensively i can say that i have found it to be almost exactly what i would have designed for myself i have taken this bag with me on long commercial flights with several connections in the car for short as well as extended trips on four seater prop planes for aerial shoots etc it always also contains my seventeen macintosh laptop as well plus two extra batteries for the laptop i have packed this bag in default mode relatively full with all the gear i would likely need for a trip for both the laptop as well as the d300 the extra one hundred and five mm macro nikkor lens two lens hoods the sb800 flash additional filters batteries etc yes it is of course heavy by my choice of course but the key is that it can and does handle it all well the camera is very readily accessible albeit not with the lens hood which would require my opening the side compartment for access i have the comfort of knowing that i have almost everything on me that i might need for the shoot and the portability of a very sturdy and well built backpack that fits superbly when completely cinched around the shoulders chest and waist the only reason that i gave it four and not five stars is because try as i might i have not found a way to attach even my smallest tripod except for the table top version which is indeed already in the bag to the bag to take with me the cost to step up to the model that accepts the tripod is rather steep whereas it should have been a rather simple addition to a bag of this dimensions to attach a tripod hooking mechanism nevertheless despite this drawback this is the bag that i want with me for ninety-nine of my travels and which has become not only my one camera bag but frankly my one seventeen laptop bag as well now that i can take my laptop and camera equipment with me at all times great job lowepro

text_review: i was looking for a replacement stereo system for my existing pioneer deh-p six thousand , five hundred which was manufactured in two thousand and two i was worried that the audio quality would be worse since that seems to be the way most other consumer electronics are headed.after powering on the stereo i immediately realized i had nothing to worry about this unit sounds even better than my old one.the clarity of high frequencies is about the same the midrange sound when compared to other units i have tested is still lacking a little bit but this unit thankfully has a bass booster adjuster which helps a little bit and speaking of bass this unit has really hard hitting bass on my two three hundred and fifty watt ten s and it sounds much deeper and more accurate than my old pioneer unit.the built in hd radio sounds crystal clear on my four way sony door and rear deck speakers also i had never actually heard hd radio before and i immediately noticed a difference when compared to a normal fm tuner so i am really pleased with that then again i am probably the only person who even listens to fm anymore.the bluetooth works seamlessly and has great sound quality and works every single time i use it since the very first time i connected it which itself only took about thirty seconds.the display is very good as well viewing angles are some of the best i have seen on an lcd screen and it even looks pretty good in direct sunlight.it s very easy to navigate through the menus in my opinion and thw buttons do not feel as cheap as some other units also the system never lags and there are no delays from pressing buttons or scrolling through the different menus and screens.as far as any negative aspects ... i really cannot think of any they would all be personal opinions anyway.so overall if you are looking for a replacement head unit that has excellent crystal clear sound a nice display and easy-to-navigate menus lool no further pioneer is still text_review: have not you wished that your snes controller did not need a wire i sure did after i used the wavebird wireless controller for gamecube ten years later here is the retro-bit superretro wireless controller here is what i think of it the controller functions as if the snes was designed with a wireless capability control pad works great all of the face buttons work great ... but as other reviewers have said the l and r buttons are a little bit too close to the palm it is not the trigger finger using them it is the center knuckle and that can be a problem on pilot wings as that hair-trigger reaction might take some adjustment to master after all it is no longer the tip of your finger that triggers it but your entire finger but that is a minor thing compared to the freedom wireless provides.other reviewers have said that the controller did not come with synchronizing instructions and therefore i looked specifically for those instructions as i did not remember how they said it worked thank god instructions came with mine i synchronized it then ... my battery petered out bad luck but they were old dying batteries anyway laugh my head off i inserted new batteries and of course it functions as it should do you love the snes as much as i do then modernize it with this controller i would suggest a two-pack though i could not afford it but it saves you a bit of money and the hassle of shipping two separate controllers you will love it oh yes might i suggest you get some energizer aaa rechargables that will save you even more money on batteries

text_review: my son is eleven months old and has been using this toy for about three months now he will push it around and walk with it while he is on his knees or feet it was not the best when he started to use it to help pull himself up it would roll out from under him but we were there and would brace it either with us or with a pillow so it was not a problem we were about a month under the recommended age at the time he loves to sit and ride on it too something i figured he would grow into he will climb on to drive and then off when he is done as with all the laugh learn fp toys the music and learning aspects are excellent i love the volume options we have several of the l l toys and it is great that they are all the same type of music although all vary in options and same voice for the learning this toy has been a must take when we visit the grandparents ... the older cousins love playing with it too we have had to change the batteries only 1x and it is been used a lot every day--almost constantly on weekends when we are home all the time my only wish is that the wheels would turn--maybe have a locking straight option then be able to release it when he is really riding on it right now i do not think it will be much fun as a rider since you cannot change the wheel direction one thing watch the weight limit for older kids a cousin who is definately in the weight range looked like he was making the seat sag in the riding position he is four and rough on toys but still in the weight range it is just not meant for his age awesome for babies toddlers one of my sons favorites and i totally recommend this item

text_review: i am not kidding when i say that i have been watching these headphones for a while they have been sitting on my wish list and just recently i decided that i could afford to treat myself a little gift i should not have i just got them today now before i continue to my review i would like to note that when i read other people's reviews i usually discard the opinions of those who have only had a product for a really short amount of time because people usually have not had the product long enough to find the issues that eventually turn up or adequately worked through confusions misunderstandings and hidden tricks i however feel quite strongly that if i do not write this review now while my experience is still fresh i will procrastinate and never get it done.before i open the package i can see that one of the silicone coverings is missing i placed my faith in humanity though and opened the box anyway hoping that it had merely fallen out of its designated slot as i did get them from an amazon warehouse deal nope nada gone fortunately they are not one of the sizes i prefer to wear but this did not leave a fantastic first impression with me i take out the earbuds and admire the look of them they look really nice and i was hoping to get some quality sound from them i was not expecting fantastic sound from them but i was hoping that they would be at least a margin better than decent especially with all of the positive reviews that i have been reading i put them in my ears without connection and i can immediately tell that they do not fit in well this was rather disappointing i have adjusted them multiple times and simply left them in my ears hoping that i would just get used to the feel but they fall out of my ears with even the slightest bump movement or pull i was sitting at the computer listening to youtube music and my left side just falls out so disappointing i even changed the coverings to the smallest sizeand i felt no difference.they are not well noise isolating headphones not unless you decide to blast the music to the point of eardrum damaging and sound leaking i am not an audiophile but i wore them during some sound tests on youtube and i really was not impressed by the quality of sound either maybe this is just because i am used to sony mdr-x five headphones which naturally emphasize the bass but i am not a bass fanatic i want good and clear mid and high tones too.to make matters worse my left side was starting to pop and crackle while i was watching some vlogbrother videos i plugged them in all the way i want my money back discounted price and all so far they are not any better than the cheap 5-10 earbuds that accompany mp3 players which i have worn their only saving grace is that during a 3d sound test they performed text_review: i bought this game without having any high expectations for it and we have been pleasantly surprised for kids this is good family fare and it is easy enough for even newer gamers to play think play dates here where sometimes the guest-child has not played but wants to try true it will not take six months to get through the whole thing but there is a lot of value i think in having some games that are challenging yet relaxing and fun as well i like the fact that the kids have to think as they go through the screens since there are various puzzles and projects that have to be completed so they can advance you could blow through the game by doing just the minimum required but my kids enjoyed really exploring the areas to make sure they had not missed anything before they completed the level.note the very first level screen is an aerial dogfight where you have to shoot down four enemy planes to advance the controls are flight-simulator-style toggle up on the controller moves the plane down etc and my kids had difficulty mastering the movement required to get the plane flying right so they could shoot down the enemies they were starting to get a little frustrated so they called in a more experienced pilot dad to finish that one screen so they could go on once they moved onto the next screen they were off
