text_review: to compare this to other units you need to evaluate surge suppression ratings in both joules and amps as well as look at the clamping voltage when you add it all up this is the best protection you can get for the money.this tripp lite unit has a very high surge suppression rating 3,300 joules /8 5,000 amps you will not find many surge protectors with this high a combined rating it also has a one hundred and forty volt clamping voltage this means that it goes into action when the voltage spikes just a little higher than the normal one hundred and twenty volts in your line some units have higher clamping voltages some in the three hundred volt range which means they are not as effective with clamping voltage the lower the better as long as it is above the normal line voltage one hundred and forty volts is ideal you have to go to the tripp lite site to find the clamping voltage specification it also comes in a sturdy metal box which means it will not melt as plastic will if it suffers an energy surge i bought this to protect the refrigerator in my new kitchen if you have a modern built-in kitchen you may not have space between the wall and refrigerator to mount a surge protector i found space behind the slide out garbage bin which is right next to the fridge and drilled a hole in the side wall of the cabinet for the power cords you can probably find some such fix if your set-up is tight it is worth it for the peace of mind

text_review: like many of my pop and dance cds i bought this for one of my dance classes and i actually listen to it outside of class it is poppy cute and fun and the album has some great cuts here are my reviews of the songs one let us go hip-hop meets an irish jig is the only way to describe this it is really short i wanted more 5/52 c'est la vie this was their first single and the only one that did much in the us it is very catchy most likely you will wake up singing it every other day the lyrics and instruments leave something to be desired but hey it is pop at it is best 5/53 rev it up this song is about a car ride it is actually a lot better than it sounds trust me this is an ok song they could definately have done better though 4/54 to you i belong another single it is a ballad and it is kind of sappy but entertaining at the same time it is got some great harmonies and you can hear the irish influence in the background music 5/55 rollercoaster this is as sugar filled as the album gets lyrics like today's the day we are out to play make this a cheesy classic it was another single from the album it is upbeat and cheery and undeneiably catchy but it lacks substance and maturity 4/56 blame it on the weatherman ummm . . . this is very weird and is one of those tracks where you have to listen to it several times before you start to like it it was their fourth single and a huge hit in europe 3.5 fifty-seven we four girls ok girls this is b witched not korn this song would be awesome recorded by another group but with four twentysomething irish girls with really high voices it sounds kind of strange 2/58 castles in the air this is one of their better slow songs good vocals a pleasant tune definately listenable this might appeal to older listeners more than younger though 5/59 freak out wahoo this is a great danceable track i really love the intro and the voices are just great once again horrible lyrics platorm shoes too high for hip-hop but that just adds to the fun 5/510 like the rose this is b witched being really mature this is a beautiful ballad that can bring tears to anybodies eyes actually i have no clue what it is about but it is still got a beautiful melody and is a nice slow song it is my favorite on the album five five hundred and eleven never giving up this is my second favorite track on the album it is upbeat and sugary without being too childish it is got a great beat and is very danceable it really should have been released 5/512 oh mr.postman um no just read the title 1/5 overall this is a great fun album no matter what age you will not be able to resist b witched's charm it is such a blast to find a band that is one hundred happy instead of a lot of the depressing music played today

text_review: i am a veteran of home video editing biz i used several tools before ulead was one of them i bought cyberlink pd delux eight a few weeks ago and made two home dvds of my family vacation dvs with total two hours of playing time from my experience i found there are some very good features with pd compared to ulead it is very intuitive one can almost plug and play without refering users guide there is not one anyway or i did not find one available multiple video audio tracks a lot of cool transfers fancy stuff easy to render and burn dvds the only headache i had was that the software crushes a lot during editing my system is windows vista thirty-two bit 4g ram 1ghz 20g storage space my video card is a little bottle neck with windows 3.4 index rating it is not perfect for video editing of course but no reason for software crush either or at least there should be a waring message telling me that my system is insufficient no such warnings the software just crushes in middle of my project sometimes just after i click on a button it was very frustrating then i did everything i could to free up enough memory and clicking on buttons like stepping in mine field yes you have to click and wait till you see your project name on top changes from xxx.prj to xxx.prj that sign means system is still busy saving or doing data swaping and hint-message under your cursor shows up then you can move you mouse otherwise software will crush right away so you must wait at least two seconds after each click of the mouse the 2nd worst thing is that video footage may get lost and leaves some random black holes in the time line cyberlink tech support said it was because my footages were from ups flash card drive and they do not support that maybe that was it the 3rd worst thing is that cyberlink tech support hotline is not free i did not know that when you have any tech question and want to make a phone call for answer it is like those phone-sex lines youhave to pay for it thirty-eight per month i really do not like it or you can email and get an initial answer and go back and forth from there each eamil answer takes two to three days bottom line is it is a good software and price is reasonable but you got to have to invest a really good desktop pc before you start that can be very expensive

text_review: just got this today from a big box store in portland i have only been using it for four hours i was going to buy from amazon but for some reason the projected delivery time was three weeks from now that was too long for my purposes i did not want to go apple i wanted at least sixteen gb this is 14.1 gb formatted which is not surprising pros it is teeny tiny it may be smaller than some apple ipod nanos minimal controls but the menus seem to be well thought out you attach it and it is just a drive no itunes crapola to deal with i drag and drop mp3 folders with band album titles and pre-named numbered mp3 file and i am good to go i have microsoft windows seven pro computer operating system i get good sound with my sony mdr three hundred headphones cost 22.50 twenty-four ohms impedance one khzsensitivity db one hundred and two db mw is capable of putting out more volume that i can stand cons file copy is fairly slow but once you do inital setup and copy that is not so bad while it will drive my larger 63ohm sony studio cans headphones it does not produce a good sound with them bass on the larger headphones is weak unsatisfying so i am not using those headphones with this was hoping to do so for plane flight travel the eq is fairly limited five band does not have a lot of precision or major change effect yes it does something it is just kind of minimal the instructions for how to actually fully shut this mp3 player down powered off are a bit cryptic they say it goes into standby it may be that it never shuts off in the normal pull the plug no power sense it is do able you put it on pause and then hold down option button for awhile i guess a better way of saying this is the manual is minimal ___ other info charges by usb to mini-usb male connector two hours for full charge built in non-user replaceable battery overall you get a compact system i will report back later on how long a charge lasts and durability note you can supposedly play back pictures and movies with this it does display the mp3 album graphics fairly clearly i did not buy it for video still display cannot speak to that i have put many albums of mp3s on here and still have 4gb of space remaining if you can swing it buy at least a device with at least 16gb pre-formatted storage that gives you enough to cover a lot of moods genres of music without being forced to delete this to make room for that currently listening to moody blues in search of the lost chord it sounds good satisfying i give this a solid four stars at this time of initial impression ___ update 7/22 two thousand and sixteen i eventually moved onto a fiio x3 ii with a sandisk 128gb sdxc micro-flash card that is 2.7 x the cost of this sony unit but for me it was a must do reason i had so many song files i needed a bigger playground the fiio is in a totally different league and should be i will say the sony got me through earlier times at a reasonable expense

text_review: lost nite records was founded in the early 1960s by jerry greene and jared weinstein after greene who was still in his teens and working for comped vinyl at a nyc record store came across an obscure forty-five by the capris there is a moon out tonight he made it a national hit by first buying the master tape and then inking a distribution deal with old town records greene and weinstein relocated to philadelphia and partnered in lost nite with local dj jerry blavat aka the geator with the heator eventually lost nite became the premier name in obscure and reissued doowop r b and r r singles.the label's compilation lps were not all that carefully mastered forty-five speed surface noise and ticks can sometimes be heard and especially on their twenty-two song albums output levels and frequency range are somewhat limited lost nite's various deejay collections may have spoken comments that overlap songs wfil fifty-six 50th anniversary golden greats ln-lp one hundred and forty-six is a stereo lp from one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-two exceptions tracks by jerry butler and edison lighthouse are rechanneled mono as is the lp version of house of the rising sun the robin ward cut is straight monaural.dick clark started djing at rock roll pioneer wfil five hundred and sixty in one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-two this was philly's highest rated top forty boss radio station in the 60s known to locals as the pop music explosion listeners all had their favorite boss jock be it chuck browning captain jay cook diamond jim nettleton king george michael long john wade or dave the rave parks who manned the overnite shift in later years fil featured dr don rose j j jeffrey tiny tom tyler big ron o'brien and k c hill among others includes release dates plus peak billboard hot one hundred and r b chart positions where applicable side onevehicle the ides of march 3/70 two n a band of gold freda payne 4/70 three #20 leavin on a jet plane peter paul mary text_review: every wwi flight sim fan has been eagerly awaiting the release of rise of flight earlier named knights of the sky and watching it is progress over the last several years it was expected to be the next great redbaron replacement but what we got instead is a very lean empty feeling simulator that is going to have to add a lot of content to catch up to rb or some other sims much has been covered in the previous comments and i agree with many of the comments good and bad but i will go ahead and add my own list of what immediately strikes me as good and bad or not available yet the best comment was that this is a wip work in progress so just be aware of what you are getting .. and be aware that there is no refund and no way to sell the game dvd down the road or the seven each add on aircraft if you decide you do not like it or get tired of it the on line requirement for single player or multi player is a copy protection system and unless they change things only one buyer is allowed .. so no resale on ebay etc unless they change their policy my general conclusion is that it is inconsistent in all areas so i will comment on the good and bad in each area that i can think of fantastic lighting effects and animated shadows in the cockpit and on objects along with beautiful reflections on water and other reflective surfaces the flight model fm appears to be the best of any flight sims done so far .. it just feels real and comments by fliers of ultra lights and other small planes generally agree it is the best yet the ai artificial inteligence computer pilots seem to be rather docil when fighting and not that well done or not very evasive when shot at .. too easy to shoot down .. the only thing that makes shooting them down hard is the plane you are flying that has this wonderful feeling of bouncing about with every little air currant makes it very hard to aim the cockpits are fully animated with working controls and full 3d .. they are amazing looking but i would like to see a pilot extensions of arms and legs working the stick and pedals as done in some other sims exterior shots show animated pilots and gunners and they add a lot to the feeling of live people in the planes instead of rigid mannequins as in most other sims however the pilots are too small scaled and have been proven to be too small in some forum discussions not a big deal and some still disagree but just one more thing that i feel needs attention dm damage model is excellent with all sorts of plane damage that looks convincing in almost all situations one of the best i have seen terrain is very impressive from high up but scenery objects and textures disappear to close in distance from the player lower down there are impressive looking trees and buildings etc but the colors of much of it look cartoonish with areas of unending prestine grass rivers way to prestine and clean too brightly colored .. the textures are to simplistic if you circle around a tree it rotates to always face you giveing a rather odd look to it over the trenches there is a wonderfull smokey look but the textures are even worse here with continuous non stop craters and at times obvious repeating texture patterns showing along with odd looking grey outlined trenches that look like zippers and other then the explosions going on everywhere there seems to be an empty feeling below that brings up the big problem of this sim it just feels empty like nothing is going on down below if you wander away from the scripted mission triggered event points you do not see anything going on unlike dynamic campaign wwi sims like redbaron or over flanders fields where there are historical events taking place all around you in real time clouds are really well done but very limited in type or looks there are excellent feelings of fog and rain but there are no seasonal terrains yet no snow no frost no spring terrain that is another thingthat will be added later as one of their add ons for free or sound effects are excellent they just seem real and are impressive there are some very well done training exercises with an animated eddie rickenbacker narrating in a very close to real sounding voice figure modeling is good but stilted and not on a par with even older games like mafia plane graphics are beautifully done with full details and many moving working 3d model parts like shutters etc the games interface is beautifully rendered with 3d hangers but very limited in scope and often confusing not well organized and often hard to use like the requirement to leave the game to make adjustments to game settings stick settings etc there is no musical score to add drama to the feeling of the era and very little historical content except for plane information much of the english is poorly translated from the russian which can look silly at times or be hard to decipher so is rise of flight the next great red baron replacement not by a long shot they are going to need to add a lot to get near to that description is it worth buying now absolutely if you want one incredible wwi plane flying experience but with only a few planes and a few plane skins each and very little else to go with it so far i hope people do buy this game and i hope they continue to improve it but it looks like it will be awhile before it feels fully rounded mean while there is over flanders fields which has not received the recognition it deserves and is not widly known about but those who have found it mostly agree it is indeed the currant replacement for red baron created by a group of former early red baron and rb3d mod makers and wwi historians it got undeserved bad forum comments because of it is reliance on the wwii combat flight simulator three game the early phase one and two problems and the requirement to buy it in phase three the payware version three between heaven and hell still relies on having a cfs three game disk available for install but is a vast improvement over the earlier off versions in almost every way the only thing used from cfs three now is the game engine the data base is completely off and seperate from cfs three and there is nothing left of cfs three that is recognizable it has very good flight model though not as good as rof but it is being improved for version four to come out soon and some are going to be surprised it does not have the lighting and reflections of rof but much better varied full seasons with historical weather and terrain textures that are more varied and believable in most cases it has a huge selection of planes to fly including two seaters and thousands of authentic historically researched plane skins a dynamic historical campaign covering the whole war means there is a full feeling of involvement in this simulator with life going on all around you as you fly rise of flight off v3 between heaven hell and another wwi sim called first eagles are all woth buying and playing each having strong points and each a whole lot of fun to play

text_review: i have had this vacuum for almost a year now picked it up from walmart for less than available online i have never needed to contact the manufacturer for support but based on the reviews i read that sounds like it would be a waste of time when this vacuum dies i will happily go out and buy another one of the same model if it is still available here is why ... light weight easy to empty easy to clean exceptional dust pick up best value of any vacuum i have ever owned wife never complains to me about it being too heavy the design and engineering of this vacuum is impressive they have made it so easy to take apart and clean the chambers and filters no tools everything just snaps together with precession that makes me smile every time i clean it i brought it because of the price and five year warranty but i would gladly pay this much money every year to have such a marvelous machine of course it is made of plastic but my 500lb hoover was too and every plastic part on it cracked and fell off during it is short life i paid twice as much for the hoover and the replacement parts for the hoover were going to cost me as much as this shark vacuum if this vacuum lasts for five years i will be amazed but i will not be disappointed if it does not and i will not waste my time trying to get it repaired .. i will keep it for spare parts and happily go out and buy a new one because it is such a great value

text_review: first things first i loved rainbow six and rogue spear i have also played operation flashpoint quite a bit gr is a combination of the three sort of the good the graphics are astounding enough said tutorial is good no bugs on my system.the bad realism is questionable sure the firefights seem real enough with tracers flying and damage and weapons are realistic however since when do green berets go on missions with one rifle and one secondary weapon answer never they go with seventy pounds of gear including rifles backup pistols several grenades and several types of grenades claymore mines night vision knives explosives radios etc etc they carry anywhere from 300-1000 or more rounds of ammo in gr you get one primary weapon e g m16 and one other thing pistol or explosive or binoculars or grenades but only one of these and you cannot mix and match items in the kit you can only choose from certain combinations e g rifleman use the m16 not m4 or mp5 demo guys use the m4 but not m16 etc second the selection of weapons is poor since when is an elite commando limited in his selection of weapons the second single-player mission is a hostage rescue you have got to rescue two guys from two locations about two hundred yards apart so my first thought was to use a silenced mp5 but it is not available even though they are standard weapons for specops soldiers instead you go with the m16 and when you shoot up one location the enemy elsewhere on the map will not even react or put up their guard in any way even though they would have heard the gunshots.third the friendly ai is pretty limited one reviewer called it user-friendly that is true but it is almost too simple and does not provide the flexibility necessary to simulation special operations warfare you cannot control formations stance or rules of engagement and even with the limited control available the soldiers pretty much suck no aitactics no reaction to the enemy no nothing even though they are supposed to be elite commandos.all in all i expected more from tom clancy and red storm this is basically rainbow six or rogue spear transplanted outside and called a tactical shooter combat sim a lot of potential but i will stick to r6 rs for hostage rescue and ofp for combat sim

text_review: my son loves all things trashies ... when i saw this on sale here at amazon i snapped it up this is actually a pretty cool tin the main portion is made of metal it is thin and already has a few dents but still probably better made than a lot of toys on the market there are embossed and painted pictures of the trash pack logo at the front of the bin and various trashy characters along the top rim at the bottom of the bin are castor style wheels they roll in all different directions and are perfect for taking you trashies on a wild ride the bright green split plastic lids open up so you can store your favorite trashies inside the lids have two prongs each on the outer side and three prongs each on the inside to stick your favorite trashies to the lids there is an icky shrimp fishbone band aid and other gross items molded in the outer lid as well this is a nice a size at roughly six 1/2 inches wide by six inches tall the two included exclusive trashies are a yellow spray paint can with green and purple accent paint and another yellow trashy that looks like he is a wooden box crate of some type overall this was an absolute hit with my son for the price here on amazon you cannot wrong

text_review: i ordered this bag for my trip to chincha and lima peru hoping i could fit my canon rebel inside ... well ... you can but it is pretty darn snug once you put your other stuff in there and the only lens that fits is a one hundred and five mm if i had brought anything else then i would have had to also carry a camera bag with me which is why i ordered this one hoping i could bypass all the extra stuff to lug about i absolutely have no complaints about this bag it held up during my ten days trudging around really well and i loved all the pockets inside and out i only used the zippered ones on the outside and only in lima's open markets where it was not busy and easy to keep track of where people were but i just want to make this clear this bag is not as big as it looks there is another version of this bag with fewer outside zippers pockets and a different strap which is about ten fifteen cheaper and they are the same size inside keep that in mind when deciding what you think is important while traveling i really did like this purse though and will probably use it for non-travel as well because the strap is so comfy it also was easy to clean off the dirt when i got home

text_review: we got this after putting up with an obnoxious audio monitor for a year i finally had enough of the static and buzzing so we got this it is perfect for use with one camera the video and sound quality are comparable to much more expensive models but the price is just right unfortunately when we had our second we found that while you can add more cameras to the parent unit there is no way to scan between the cameras it only monitors the camera you are set to we ended up buying the motorola mpb thirty-six with two cameras because it can scan back and forth all night but it does not have vox or the battery life that this unit had i wish this one would scan between the cameras and if they were to make an upgraded version it would be nice to pan zoom and have a temp readout the vox on this is perfect it would light up whenever my daughter cried but never picked up the music or white noise in her room i liked that it clicked a little when it lit up that woke me up but was not annoying the parent unit is a little flimsy feeling but it worked just fine.overall if you only need it for one room this is a wonderful video monitor at a great price

text_review: these are the best headphones i have ever used not that i am a serious audiophile i have had them only about a week but already i have found them very enjoyable i have also used the slightly cheaper closed-back hd two hundred and eighty pros plus tons of various junky cheap headphones the 558s have an excellent sound stage thanks to the open back design listening to music feels like you are sitting in the middle of the orchestra or face-to-face with the lead singer of a band extremely accurate across most of the audio spectrum there is a slight hump in 5-10 k frequencies which means sounds just over typical vocal range are slightly exaggerated bass is accurate but not excessive you are not going to get noticeably better sound for less than double the price these are excellent for listening to all genres of music and for gaming which are my primary uses.you will definitely need a decent headphone amp if you use these with a phone ipod etc or any other output that is not solidly powered this is by design these are not cheap flimsy drivers accuracy requires power when it comes to headphones they sound pretty poor on my un-amped galaxy nexus and only a little better on my iphone four without a headphone amp i am still waiting on delivery of the portable amp i ordered but most people say they sound excellent when properly driven on my desktop computer they sound fantastic even on integrated motherboard sound granted i have a high-end motherboard with a better than average sound system built in i would recommend getting a shorter replacement cord with a 3.5 mm jack the cord is very easy to remove with the twist-lock but will not fall out on accident the standard cord is extremely long not a problem for stationary use but it is poorly suited for portable listening.overall i can highly recommend these headphones to anyone looking for an affordable entry into high-quality audio

text_review: i received this globe a year ago as a gift for my children they occasionally would take it out and spend time with it but only recently has one of my sons started getting serious about independently studying geography so he asked me to update the globe for him that was when what had become a pleasant household educational device became a nightmare when i first registered i was delighted to see that i would qualify for free updates for a year from the date of registration rather then from purchase date so i plugged in my pen started the software and suddenly like others have reviewed found myself with a useless smart pen the program managed to wipe the pen's memory but refused to download the new information into the pen it gave me a dozen different error messages i tried turning off my firewall uninstalling reinstalling everything turning off my antivirus etc ... nothing worked i was left with a dead pen it just made this horrible faint scratching clicking sound i tried updating it on my husband's pc and after a couple of tries finally got it to finish downloading into the pen ... unfortunately it was the 5-8 yr old info way too young for my kids against my better judgement i tried downloading the age appropriate info thankfully it worked after the update was complete it automatically updated the clock.the globe itself is sturdy attractive and well designed and the kids really enjoy it it does not feel or look cheap we keep it on top of our bookshelf in our living room because it looks nice enough to do so oregon scientific really should deal with the software issue because they have something special here but as it is right now it is something of a trojan horse if the pen does not work you will be left with a nice yet way overpriced globe as it stands while attempting to update it you may or may not break the whole thing you should not be afraid to update something you pay this much for i doubt i will attempt to update it again anytime soon and as long as this remains an issue i would not recommend it to others reading through the reviews here it seems this has been on ongoing problem for almost five years now plenty of time for them to have fixed it i hope others find this review my first helpful t i will attempt to update it again anytime soon and as long as this remains an issue i would not recommend it to others reading through the reviews here it seems this has been on ongoing problem for almost five years now plenty of time for them to have fixed it i hope others find this review my first helpful

text_review: i used to have good att service and extremely limited vzw service then att decided that boosting the lte signal to color a map was the way to go and there went my att service as well i have a work vzw device but was useless at my house i live in a rural mountain area so crappy dsl from att also made the microcell a worthless option oh and my geriatric mother lives in the basement floor apartment and yes she needs to talk to her peeps aaarrrggh.then i found this device oh happy day i have a three floor configuration so have the yagi antenna deployed at the north peak pointing west.the 1st panel antenna is deployed at the far south end of the house in the basement on a wall pointing north no issues due to distance and going through three r30 insulated floors and a roof.the 2nd indoor panel antenna is ceiling mounted about seventeen vertical and twenty-two horizontal from the yagi band four was alternating green red operating at a lower level but no component damage per the excellent tech support from weboost i took an extra piece of metal roofing that i had and placed it on the ten rafters above the ceiling deployed antenna also 1/2 sheetrock and 1/2 osb between antenna and metal between the yagi and the indoor unit issue solved i pointed the yagi to the west because that is where the vzw tower is 3.5 miles away att tower is 1.5 miles nnw.bottom line i have 90dbm four full bars on the att device 14mg dl ul and on the vzw device i have 104dbm 3full bars this coverage is throughout all three floors even in the stairwell to the basement.yes it cost more than i wanted to spend but it solved all the issues i did call tech support to verify a few items great service i am only angry at myself for not figuring this out a year ago

text_review: the best summary of this speaker is  solid  both in terms of build quality and sound while it  s not audiophile level quality i  m pleased with the performance and feature set for the price point.the overall look is very nice it  s mostly black with some red accents the grill is metal and has a diamond pattern that stands out well without being flashy the control buttons are all on the top edge and are clearly labeled in red a flap on one the side covers the 3.5 mm input jack and the micro usb input port the other side has a loop to attach a lanyard or clip the body is covered in a rubber-like material that feels nice and offers a matte finish to hide fingerprints there are two large non-slip pads on the base that are very effective in keeping this planted all in all no complaints about the overall design and build quality given the price point.it comes in a decent box with a carry case and a charging cord the manual is very brief but covers the basics which are pretty much self-explanatory it does have voice prompts that tell you  power on  and  pairing  but they are not as obnoxious as other speakers i  ve used with voice prompts still i  d prefer a simple beep rather than a voice.bluetooth paring was simple and easy and i like that it enters pairing mode automatically without having to push any buttons i had no problems maintaining a connection at twenty feet.the sound quality is quite good at low to moderate volume levels the high end is pretty crisp the mid range is clear and there is ample bass however it gets pretty harsh when you turn it up although this has a volume range that  s wider than you normally get with a bluetooth speaker this is not a speaker that likes to get pushed to the max but in all fairness i  ve yet to find a speaker in this price range that maintains good fidelity when maxed out.for the price point about thirty this warrants a 4.5 star rating based on it  s performance and feature set i  ll round up to five stars since the overall aesthetics black and red appeal to me plus the fact that the buttons are so clearly labeled which is becoming rare on lower-end products well worth considering if you  re looking for a easily portable speaker with solid performance sample provided for review a 4.5 star rating based on it  s performance and feature set i  ll round up to five stars since the overall aesthetics black and red appeal to me plus the fact that the buttons are so clearly labeled which is becoming rare on lower-end products well worth considering if you  re looking for a easily portable speaker with solid performance sample provided for review

text_review: the baby banana combo pack is perfect because it has everything you need to get your kids started on brushing all in one place first of all the adorable toothbrush is bendable and flexible so i do not have to worry about my kids biting down to hard on it or falling and possibly injuring themselves like they would on a traditional hard toothbrush then they have paired the darling toothbrush with a strawberry-banana flavored tooth gel that is actually really yummy then i found out the nutritional value that xylitol products have apparently xylitol is all-natural and it has anti-bacterial properties so it basically gets the germs out of my kids mouths with just a simple swoosh of the brush then i found out that xylitol actually helps to build calcium and enamel for my little one's teeth this tooth gel has no fluoride so its safe for my kids to swallow too i really think this product has the best of everything--these products were literally made for each other also having this product has made brushing time such a pleasant experience in our home which it never was before thank you for all of your great products baby banana

text_review: not knowing any better we inadvertently purchased a booster seat that you just placed in the seat of the vehicle and then strapped the child in with the vehicle's seat belt what a mistake from the beginning my husband was not real happy with it because of the way the booster seat would move around and the way our son could scoot himself down in the seat and sometimes put the shoulder strap under his arm we never really felt like he was properly seated in it when someone emailed us a video showing the dangers of a booster seat such as ours that is not tethered in like a car seat with a five point harness system we were convinced and immediately purchased this booster seat this booster seat is well worth every penny it may take some work getting it strapped in the seat of the vehicle correctly but once it is in the right way it does not budge and the five-point harness system gives us the peace of knowing that our son is securely in the seat and not able to move around yet at the same time it is very comfortable and he has no problem sleeping in it without his head flopping around we are thrilled with this seat

text_review: a particularly strong debut for the san fransisco based combo this five piece band greg yanito guitar and vocals eric reedy string bass and vocals bill mckenna electric guitar mikiya matsuda steel guitar billy zelinski drums rips through a set a good ol country music both yanito and reedy sing and compose and they know how to write songs that sound like little classics which also keeps the set varied you will only find two covers gene o'quinn's texas boogie and carl smith's back up buddy smith being an obvious influence on the band.carl sonny leyland sits in and plays piano on four tracks adding a good dose of country boogie and even rock'n'roll pretty baby to the mix there is also some country swing duckin and dodgin a bit of bakersfield women and wine sweet little things and a superb hank williams influenced number trouble free state of mind it is tastefully produced by lee jeffriess and you can hear his touch on some steel guitar guitar arrangements reminiscent of his work with ashley kingman in the fly rite boys.if carl smith hank williams merrill moore wayne hancock big sandy are sweet words to your ears be sure to add the b-stars to your list and it is not only a pleasure for your ears but also for the eyes as it comes in a nicely designed digipack.fred turgis jumpin from six to six

text_review: mariah has had hit after hit over the years but when she finally broke free of sony's restrictive hold on her the first album charmbracelet felt like it was lacking some of the power behind the still great lyrics it left some wondering if maybe she needed the powerhouses behind her but with emancipation of mimi mariah proves she does not need anyone but herself to soar up the charts to number one and stay there sure there are some great collaborations with snoop jd twista nelly on emancipation but the most important thing is that mariah's voice is back on charmbracelet she tried this sultry whisper thing to be softer and a bit more subtle she always has had the incomparable vocal range and that should be exploited here she sings back at the top of her range allowing listeners once again to be amazed in a world where technologically enhanced music and lipsynching has become the norm ahem britney and hillary it is more than refreshing to see mariah still able to compete ... and knock everyone else out of the game the best songs off this album are we belong together the second single for its harmony say somethin the third single for the flow with snoop and fly like a bird for its power and message but in the end they are all excellently done and will have you listening to the cd on repeat it is been in my car ever since it dropped and that is more than two months ago i did not want to like to the floor simply because i do not like nelly but even that one won me over the neptunes produced a great beat that really complements her twista's part in one and only is a bit tedious because he manages to referece rims four times but hey not everyone can be the lyricist mariah is this album really does feel like it sets mariah free she says things on it she never has and never would have before and she tackles it all power ballads gospel dance party tracks and hiphop collaborations

text_review: if like me a few months ago you have a 76cs and are wondering whether to replace it with the 76csx i recommend doing so.the 76csx is surprisingly improved over the 76cs i noticed that . . . . one the antenna is much stronger the 76csx pulls in satellite signals inside my house two the annoying hold level warning on the compass page no longer appears i guess garmin has solved that issue three the batteries stay in place even with severe use in my case on the handlebar of my mountain bike as i traverse rough terrain with the 76cs and 76s i had to install bubble wrap inside the battery cover to get the batteries to stay in contact on the 76csx the batteries have not dislodged to extract them i have found it is better to roll them out than to try to pull them out four the unit will draw power from your computer via the usb cable.in sum i am very glad that i bought the 76csx and sold my 76cs i have one suggestion the screen could easily be scratched on my prior garmin gps receivers this time before venturing out of the house with the 76csx i overlaid a clear plastic invisibleshield film that i had bought from a company called zagg on my very first outing i crashed my bike flying through some sharp branches and twigs the screen was unblemished

text_review: this game is a far better experience than any cod experiences in the past years where their games have become stale run and shoot experiences the combination of killzones cover system and intelligent enemy ai conveys a sense of military realism and challenge enemy's flank use grenades to flush you out of cover while allowing the player to feel like every kill and battle won was earned through precise positioning and strategy all of which equates to an impressive experience of depth despite the shallow and often times stereotypical narrative speaking of immersion playing this game with the playstation move and sharp shooter is a surreal experience it takes getting use to at first and my suggestion is to practice this scheme in the bot zone which is an offline simulated multi player mode this both allows you to calibrate the move scheme to your liking and at the same time allows you to get acclimated to the pacing and class system of the online multi player which has become my new addiction on its own right after playing through the campaign with a dual shock and than sharp shooter i am now an online fiend in cod if your not up to par with getting a high kill death ratio you are seemingly made useless and target practice by helicopters attack dogs and whatever cod mechanism that unbalances the online experience for us non aiming experts in killzone the class base system allows me to contribute to my team without having to be a terminator in one game i had the highest score dispite having one of the worst kdr of my team i was an engineer and medic taking up points fixing weapons depots and setting up gun turrets which did some killing for me and as a medic getting points healing people left and right when the battles around me became intense which was the norm in ever online match each match was highly competitive and never once made me feel like i could not get involved even with getting slaughtered by a mech which is easy to take down as anengineer fixing the wasp turrets to insure those huge mechs do not become too over powering balanced that is what this entire game feels from the difficulty in the story mode which has challenging ai but gives you powerful guns that never allow the task at hand feel just perfect for online is also a balanced experience with every class acting as checks and balances for each other provoking team success to rely on teams with class diversity and team work along with the best move implementation ever seen in a game just started testing it out online and my kdr is steadily improving as a result ... killzone three is the best fps i have had since the first modern warfare and not once have i even mentioned the obvious ... that this game has dethroned uncharted two and god of war three as the best graphics you can find on the console seriously this game sold my relative who was oblivious to hd not only a new tv but a ps3 as well this game has earned my highest recommendation ... just get it psn poetic 1der

text_review: a couple of months ago i bought this album's predecessor above the weeping world based on a recommendation from a fellow fan of dark tranquillity i consider atww a pretty good cd but it never grew on me the way i hoped it would still holding out hope for insomnium i reluctantly bought across the dark and i am so glad i did because this album improves upon atww in every possible way the songs are more atmospheric the riffs while not earthshaking are more interesting the clean vocals which are used somewhat sparingly eliminate the monotony of one hundred growled roared vocals the production is cleaner but the album is in no way over-produced i just cannot emphasize enough how pleasantly surprised i was by across the dark i did not expect anything to beat out amorphis skyforger as my favorite album of two thousand and nine but i think across the dark may have done it if you like amorphis dark tranquillity or opeth then you need to hear this

text_review: cal haskell is the main character of a western series with a twist he is the new sheriff of sorrow michigan westerns of course should take place in the west but this is michigan's frontier and there are plenty of similarities to make it work.sorrow is a troubled town cal haskell and his motley crew of deputies keep an eye on things but sometimes things get out of control just recently a jury has quickly found a black man guilty of killing a white prostitute but cal is told by one of the town's most respected citizens that the wrong man was convicted once cal starts to look into it things start to get real dangerous clearly someone does not want him to look into this and they are willing to do anything to keep their secrets hidden.be prepared the story does not really end once you get to the end this is just part one of a multi-part tale.joe barrett's midwestern twang rings true while he voices this town full of characters men women old and young they all come through with a distinctive voice

text_review: i was very disappointed with this game the basic idea you play a detective working alongside lenny briscoe and then an ada working alongside the jack's latest assistant is sound but the gameplay is a complete anathema to the tv show in the tv show the detectives follow up blind alleys in their quest for the truth in the game if you follow a blind alley you must immediately load a saved game or you will run out of time or simply lose.in essence much of the early game comprises searching for physical evidence and questioning witnesses while trying to save time the fact that it takes fifteen minutes to bag a cigarette butt is extremely stupid since it means that to collect the right evidence and yet not run out of time you need to play the game over and over to figure out which evidence you need and then go back and psychically only pick up the right evidence needless to say key evidence is carefully obscured by a bad user interface e g a house full of drawers that do not open and one that does but needs to be opened using a key that is in the victim's wallet but itself hidden by the user interface interviewing suspects is even worse whether or not you should ask a given question is totally arbitrary and if you do not ask the right questions your game is over but you will have to figure that out by yourself e g one of the first puzzles in the game involves piecing together a torn up business card just having the pieces with the address phone number or name of the company is not enough what is more there is a witness nearby and the only question worth asking that witness is would you move your vehicle so you can find the last piece of that card.remember if you make a mistake you need to restore from backup so apparently the only good detective or ada is psychic and knows for example that the mineral water has a usable print on it but the cigarette lighter does not sadly you may be psychic but you cannot get lab reports by phone orfax or look up people's addresses in the telephone directory.even worse if for some reason an interview with a witness ends without letting you ask a crucial question you may not be allowed to re-interview that witness even if you uncover evidence contradicting one of their statements i would probably have equally nasty observations to make about the ada portion of the game but i refuse to play it further.finally some quibbles it is not a 3d game everything is pre-rendered so it is a 2d game with pre-rendered video of 3d figures instead of live actors presumably to save money i actually thought that the broadband online demo was considerable better than the game itself with a much less fiddly interface

text_review: like many others i had a vizio slide-out keyboard remote that needed replacement my original one lasted about three months a replacement from vizio lasted about two months it would have been one thing if it was just the keyboard part that broke but no the whole thing stopped working after needing to be constantly reset by holding down power and pushing all the keys as instructed by vizio having to do that every time we wanted to use it was a hassle then eventually they stopped both working entirely anyway.this remote is the perfect replacement no it does not have the useless keyboard but as a result apparently it is much more reliable finally after getting by on a cheap universal remote which could not access the main menu or vizio internet apps like netflix we found this product on amazon it looks just like the slide-out keyboard model but is much more sturdy finally we were able to access the tv's complex menus and via again it is nice to have netflix right on the tv once again we have been using this remote for about a month and it has not given us a single problem whereas the original one started getting flaky almost right away.for about eight nine shipped this should be a no-brainer purchase for anyone with that horribly-designed fancy bluetooth keyboard remote in fact we may buy another just to have on hand in case this one breaks down the road

text_review: a suitable replacement to traditional analog cameras at decent price point we purchased four of these as a replacement to our analog four hundred and eighty line setup and it exceeded our expectations we only had to run one line ethernet all the way back to our poe switch no more running bulk cctv cables at one hundred and fifty apiece it cannot be beat you can pay two hundred or three hundred for a better camera but its plenty good for indoor use outdoor wise its a little bit sketchy and we do not recommend it if you use it for night time day time its fine see attached another problem is that this will not fit in the outdoor camera case leaving this exposed to the elements and possible shorter life the onboard ir leds when there is dust flying around will make it look like there is a blizzard due to the ir reflecting off the light into the camera if you have motion detect for night time forget it .. it wont work what we do is turn off the ir rely on building street lights and use it for motion detect hardware we have a geovision card software powering a eight analog camera setup two vivotek outdoor 2mp camera and now four of these geovision 1.3 mp cameras i believe that in the near future the eight analog camera setups can be completely eliminated however as we have six ip cameras we are getting close to maxing out our computer network capabilities contrary to the geovision analog card where most data is processed by the geovision hardware network traffic comes thru the computer cpu so i dont see how we can go above 8-10 without reaching the limit of what the computer can handle other thoughts if you have a fair amount of bandwidth and only getting a couple of cameras you may want to consider using nest dropcam with its cloud recording feature and user interface its a world better in the fact that you can access your videos from afar with geovision you are constrained to its clunky interface and lack of cloud features

text_review: i see references to pink floyd here because of mr gilmour's involvement of course ... but what i just listened to was a dance mix with booming bass beats and music mixed so low in the sound-field that you could not hear much other than those beats you can just about hear david gilmour's guitar over the beats and once in a while something ping-pongs around the speakers crunching sounds inaudible voices etc when the music is more ambient and chilled it seems to never settle into anything at one point an acoustic guitar piece is cut-up into a jittery mess that never comes into focus except for a few seconds before it fades into another phase of this unsettled album for me that is what is wrong here ... even david gilmour's guitar never ever becomes anything but background for more overwhelmingly bass-toned beats maybe the 3d mix will reveal more ... if i ever feel like buying this again to find-out sorry all you others out there but this does not even come close to any of the other orb albums i own maybe i expected more of a floating ambient album ... maybe i will get used to what this is and love it in a few plays but right now it is all too dance beat oriented for me ... and too little ever jells here to say that you have even heard much more than sound-effects under a beat to me david gilmour's guitar should be heard as more than just sound-effects hell maybe my disc is defective seeing how much others love this i cannot say i am happy with it

text_review: update 11/26 two thousand and thirteen rating increased to three stars after trading a few more emails with taotronics support they realized that the link they originally sent me was not necessary theypointed me to my laptop manufacturer's website ... and told me that the support page there would have the latest bluetoothdrivers.this was not exactly correct there were no updates to the bluetooth drivers on this page but there was an update to the bluetoothmanagement application when i downloaded and installed that update the headset successfully paired and i have been using it withan ip phone application on my laptop so far so go the quality is acceptable and the range seems to be good i was evenable to pair it with a second device droid maxx although i have yet to use it with that device let alone answer calls or switchbetween devices using it with a second device was a bit tricky the document did not help much but i think the basic idea is to paireach device separately with the other bluetooth turned off turn everything off and then turn everything back on again and then wait.eventually both devices found the headset and connected i will update this review again after i use it some more beware win seven driver issues sent a link that wants more money to get the right driver the above rating is temporary until the issue i am having is resolved i just received the headset and tried to pair it with my win seven sixty-four bit laptop after the device was recognized by my bluetooth manager it told me that it need to find and update the drivers for the device so i let windows do that it came back and said that it could not update the driver and to contact the manufacturer so i did they responded within a day and sent me alink supposed pointing to the proper drivers in reality the link pointed to an application called drivertuner which scans the laptop and find all the out-of-date drivers i keep my drivers up to date religiously so this got me suspicious so i selected just the bt driver for the headset and told it to download that it still attempted to download all the out-of-date drivers worse in order to finish the job it told me i had to register this copy of drivertuner which by the way is installed itself as a auto-starting system tray app even though i explicitly unchecked the box telling it to do that during installation even worse still in order to register took me to a webpage asking thirty for the license key at that point i had enough exited the webpage and the app which i had to do twice because it minimized itself to the tray and attempted to uninstall the app even that did not go smoothly i had to hunt down and manually delete all the leftovers the uninstaller could not remove needless to say i ran my virus scanner afterwards i have sent a followup to taotronics asking them to simply send me the necessary driver and told them i did not wish to pay an additional thirty to get this headset working.if they send me the right driver and it installs without further funny business i will update this and review the headset itself otherwise amazon will be getting a return and i will not buy another taotronics product again

text_review: i guess i have to be the voice of dissent among these positive reviews i have listened to this recording several times now and do not like it nearly as much as samantha's previous release identity she is going way too far down the smooth jazz road with results that are not pleasant the title track opens with this trend a boring and predictable tune that has little to offer the second track poquita has a nice guitar intro but this leads into the most vapid dancey drum machine-driven junk i have heard in some time please no more of this what follows is an assortment of unoriginal tunes until we get to clouds the stand-out song on the cd this and six of the clock are the best songs on the album samantha is at her best singing more traditional cabaret-style songs and clouds is easily one of her best amazing chord progressions and beautiful melodies interlude is lovely as well though far too short wild is also enjoyable with its unusual rhythmic patterns.finally we have tada yet another remix this is of the title track and all it has is more prominent fake drums plus throughout the album samantha has the occasional annoying tendency to sing slightly sharp this is a problem that has plagued all of her recordings and i suspect it has to do with headphone distortion i have experienced this myself many times in the studio it can be remedied by keeping one headphone off so that the ear hears the voice naturally.so basically sam here is some unsolicited advice lose the drum machine please ditch the less-than-inspiring instrumentals unless like interlude you really have something to say and please no more remixes move more toward the excellent cabaret style you have developed in songs like clouds and like a child and watch your tuning

text_review: this cd was recommended to me on amazon because of my purchases of the locust the dillinger escape plan an albatross and daughters so i expected some really fast and intense music upon my first listen of pizza i was pretty disappointed it is not very fast aside from a few moments none of which are locust or dep-fast its poppy moments are completely pointless the drums sound quite dull the synth work is tacky and a lot of the screaming just sounds halfhearted i would not call it an emotional rollercoaster as another reviewer who happens to be in the band did i guess the synth is supposed to make them nintendocore but they really do not even achieve that very well it sounds a little like a video game but completely lacks any nintendo feeling i listened to it about a dozen more times and it began to grow on me i even found myself singing p i-z-z-a at one point around my friends its concise length probably helps fifty minutes of this would get old quick i never watched teenage mutant ninja turtles so i was not necessarily excited to hear the tnmt theme song at the end and having almost nothing to do with pizza i think the album would be stronger without it i just found it hard to get excited about this album it is a neat concept if you can call five songs that mention pizza a concept it is a little fun to tell people i am listening to horse the band but it will not even come close to touching your grindcore sweet tooth

text_review: pop trash is probably the best work duran duran has put out to date the blend of melodic lyrics cool rhythms and great synth and guitar work just makes it the must have album of the new millenium ... or any millenium someone else not me is the beautiful ballad with beautiful lyrics and even more beautiful music to back it lava lamp i think is the feel good tune of the album as it makes you just wanna get up and dance playing with uranium is a very cool funky track with a great blend of guitar and synth and i see this as a definate choice for a single hallucinating elvis is probably the funkiest song on the album and it proves a real stong track for the middle of the record starting to remember is a little odd in the beats at times but still a strong track with an interesting ending pop trash movie is a beautiful song and i think it was meant to be a duran song fragment is a beautiful short piece although i wish it went longer mars meets venus and lady xanax are my personal favourites on the album both being songs with great melodies and great lyrics lady xanax has sort of a haunting soung to it as lady ice of so red the rose did kiss goodbye is probably my favourite of the two interludes and again i wish it was a full length song last day on earth is a powerful rocking song to end the album with and i think it should be a possible single as well the bonus someone else not me en espanol was a great treat as i think simon makes it sound great no matter what language he is singing in the cover art and the linear art was great and it makes it fun to look at as well as listen to overall this gets a fifteen out of ten on my scale and goes down as my favourite duran album ... stronger than rio great job duran duran and i hope the next is as good as pop trash

text_review: i just got back from a three week trip to st petersburg stockholm copenhagen and paris lots of airports train stations and cobble stone streets i researched for weeks the best luggage to fit the dimension restrictions by the euro and american airlines had the best durability and light weight in order to fill my case for the long haul i chose the teal color to easily stand out and the in-line skate wheel design over the spinner wheels that may not hold up to hazards outside an airport i made the right choice it is the only light suitcase that has total rigid support around all the sides of the case the stand support on the bottom doubles as a handle to lift the handle opens smoothly and worked perfectly the outer pockets are very handy inner mesh can keep dirty clothes separated.the only negatives that are minor and why i did not give five stars the fabric is polyester and will get scuffs i scotchgaurded the fabric and it helped remove the dirt but if you plan to travel al lot then get a ballistic nylon case the fabric is not waterproof the wheel housing is installed with all screws except one rivet so not easily replaced i wish there was a plastic kickplate on the underside instead of a vinyl strip.this case for the money especially the close out price is a bargain i travel a few times a year and expect this set to last for several years by far the best out there for the price

text_review: i am a veteran of inspiration having bought my first copy from the program's then husband-and-wife creators and one of their dads at a computer trade show long ago i have stuck with the program because it offers a quick way to do mind maps particularly rapid-fire an outliner and presentation creator in one simple very efficient and generally bug-free package over the years the company has focused its attention primarily on the k twelve market it seems a natural fit though i think the company could have achieved some degree of success in the commercial market as well however their marketing wisdom may be right the competition for mind mapping software in the commercial marketplace is fierce and there are a couple of microsoft products in this space as well so inspiration ticks on and delivers a very nice product a reasonable price you can put together a simple graphic linked outline or mind map with less than a minute's instruction if that the program comes with a large library of illustrations and symbols you can switch quickly and easily from the graphical view to a traditional outliner view a feature which i find very useful finally you can create reasonably nifty presentations with inspiration as well though i do not use it for this purpose overall if you like having a simple to use but very flexible tool immediately for visual or traditional outlining inspiration is the little wonder that your schoolkid may know about but you do not it is a great little product.jerry

text_review: in late one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-two when i was but a mere lad of twenty-five i flew to new york to attend two concerts with herbert von karajan and the berlin philharmonic orchestra at carnegie hall on the last evening a saturday the only piece on the program was a performance of mahler's ninth symphony while i had heard several versions before the concert including karajan's studio recording from one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-one and the walter vpo version from one thousand , nine hundred and thirty-eight nothing could have prepared me for the experience of hearing this work performed live by karajan and the bpo it was the greatest single concert i ever attended of hundreds bar none it was a performance that has had an almost mystical effect on me the passage of time has not diminished my vivid memories of that concert in fact if you want to come close to what it was like listen to the adagio of this one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-two live recording there are many other great ninths but this one is definitely the desert island record

text_review: background i have two intel macs with aluminum and glass cases one a non-unibody twenty-four inch imac another a unibody 13.3- inch macbook pro they both have core two duo processors and so would not run mac os x 10.7 to a decent level of capability then i heard how apple was going to deprecate the mobileme that i willingly paid one hundred and eighty for so it could stay around for two years now apple is going to throw not just that pittance but the money i spent on three intel macs and a time capsule that did what i wanted to over three thousand out the window so i struck back and keep snow leopard configured in a pleasing manner i am smart about what i do on the internet and like the level of functionality i currently have and decided to supplement my snow leopard with windows seven what version of windows seven deserves to go on an intel mac for me the answer was simple the same version as what i have in snow leopard-not a single missing feature but not installed with objectionable updates which i do not want the mac app store and i do not want a windows app store either so i run windows seven ultimate on my two intel macs with the internet explorer nine and windows seven sp1 hidden and they will stay so as long as absolutely possible with that said here are my opinions of the various features one the new taskbar it kicks butt i had to download the windows seven rc over a 1.5 mbit dsl connection just to experience the new taskbar early and when i got opportunities i bought windows seven that so fat has been fully legal to avoid hassles and yes i know windows seven has windows genuine advantage but if that is going to be an issue i expect that microsoft will inform me of what to do about it the one problem i had was successfully dealt with and they answered another question most kindly my experience has been top notch probably because god gives me better luck i actually pray about things like this and so far god has not failed me two homegroup when all three windows seven computers are on and awake homegroup works perfectly for me i am most pleased with its performance three windows xp mode all three computers have an edition of windows seven that allows it although one does not support virtualization and the unassisted virtualization updater refuses to believe it is needed i use it for microsoft sam and will not be afraid to load applications into windows xp mode should i need them the 13.3- inch core two duo macbook pro has more audio garbling than the imac does the imac has almost none three bitlocker drive encryption i found one nice fellow who posted directions on a way to make bitlocker work without a tpm 1.2 or better chip and it allows me to have access to every feature i paid for i am most pleased with windows seven in that regard four language packs it helps having a laptop and desktop that if i need to can switch languages so i can help people who may need it i have not needed it so far five the geek factor i must say windows seven ultimate gives me great pride that i can have access to not just the basic set of features in home premium but that if someone has a problem with windows seven professional enterprise or ultimate i can help them the features that are also in windows seven professional which i have on an old intel cantrino santa rosa mobile technology former vista laptop that was bought well before the offer to get a free windows seven upgrade but that i used my student thirty offer for-i paid more to get extended download time and a dvd backup plus i got the thirty-two bit version which did not have the installation nightmare of the sixty-four bit version are also so good to have in the toolbox of available windows seven features i love out of the windows seven text_review: i have been using this software quite a bit and i have had minimal problems the worst so far was that i was eight dvds into a set of ten when it said user interrupted and canceled 3/4 way through burning the dvd so i lost eight dvds probably a driver issue or my dvd drive got hot and threw a bad bit or something maybe i did interrupt it mentally ... who knows junk happens in software that tries to support thousands of manufacturers i know this because i write apps for android and you would not believe how many times my games will run fine on one phone and randomly have an issue on some low end or even high end device that i just did not have the money to test i digress.the pros the partitioning power is magnificent i have moved partitions around seamlessly many times i have had several hd crashes do not buy corsair ssds three failures in one year the backups seem quick and are pretty well compressed i flawlessly copied my mac hard drive over to an ssd the ssd failed a day later grant you but see comment above the interface is clean and easy to understand i have made many one time backups although i have not had to recover from those yet hopefully will not have to but i will update this review if i do

text_review: first of all i got lucky on the price of this unit amazon warehouse deals had one for about sixty less than the usual retail price and the only flaw was a tiny ding in the plastic of the ipod dock that comes with the ar30 otherwise this is a completely new unit and functions flawlessly i bought the complete sonata component system ar30 dv30 cd30 and np30 to replace my fifteen year old jvc f3000 compact stereo system a gem of a mini-system which i finally had to retire due to the cd player and tape deck no longer performing reliably i have a relatively short wall and a small entertainment console where my stereo system sits so the small footprint of the sonata components is a necessity for me i love the brushed aluminum silver cases to me this is classier looking than the typical black that most component manufacturers stick with but that is just cosmetic and everyone's taste is different ca also made the sonata system in black made because the sonata components are no longer part of ca's current line in terms of performance i am very happy with the ease of use sound quality and functionality of the ar30 and the other sonata components from a cold start the ar30 is a tad slow -8.4 seconds from clicking the remote on to ready-to-play--but not enough to complain about with 40w per channel at eight ohms it is more than enough to drive my klipsch rb sixty-one ii speakers the volume control maxes out at a setting of thirty-nine and i have never had it over twenty-five so unless you like busting your eardrums you will be fine.each component in the sonata system comes with its own remote and they are all interoperable there are dedicated buttons at the base of the remote for selecting which component to control the dvd remote has the biggest array of buttons and is a little heavier than the receiver or cd remotes all the components have simple clear arrays of buttons on their front panels the receiver controls are basic--there's no graphic equalizer for example just bass treble and balance--but i have not found this to be a drawback since the sound quality is crystal pure the receiver has a separate in out for a subwoofer the input comes from the dvd player and works fine with my polk ps10.the sonata line has been discontinued by ca and has not been replaced by a similar small footprint model the sonata is only 270mm wide whereas the ca topaz and azur current lines are full-sized at 430mm wide so if you are in the market for a compact component system grab one of these now before current retail inventories disappear i bought three of the four components from amazon two new one barely used and i got the np30 used six mos old on ebay with careful shopping i paid just 1,008 for everything shipping included if money is no object in your pursuit of perfect audio then you can indulge in higher-end components than the sonata but if you are on a budget or if you need a second system for a rec room etc the sonata delivers terrific sound at a great price

text_review: when i got my xbox it came with a copy of sega two thousand gt i really enjoyed that game up to a point namely the point when the difficulty curve shot up dramatically and it was no longer fun to play anymore i e impossible to win forza is light-years beyond that game and i am sure most other games in this genre the learning curve is gradual and you actually end up learning a great deal about auto racing yes it is that real it is a true simulation not just a game there is a massive selection of cars and tracks and many different types of competition events career mode is the most fun as you can win cars and money and spend that money to customize your cars do not spend too much time tricking out your cars though because you will find yourself switching between cars frequently in order to get through all of the different events this can be a real learning experience if you have spent the majority of your time in a fwd car switching to the rwd can be traumatic try the porsche nine hundred and eleven a-class at laguna seca or enter the rotary challenge and try to keep that rx7 on the track luckily there is a free run mode in which you can practice with any car on any track an invaluable aid when you find yourself stumped you can tweak each car's setup right down to the tire pressure spring tension wheel camber gear ratios and all that stuff you really can get lost in this game overall this is a game which will remain interesting for quite some time not good news for your family or any hobbies you will end up neglecting for hours on end i am beginning to hate this game because it is so dang fun i just cannot stop playing darn you microsoft
